title: no bake cookies
directions: Bring to boil sugar, cocoa, milk, oleo and salt.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Quickly drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.

title: pepper steak salad
directions: Combine all ingredients into a screw-top jar and blend well.

title: auntie nancy's cheesy corn chowder(serves 4)
directions: Melt butter in 3-quart saucepan.
Saute onion and celery for about 5 minutes.
Add potatoes, milk, corn and seasonings.
(I add extra frozen corn.)
Heat to serving temperature.
Remove from heat and stir in cheese.
Garnish with parsley, if desired.
Makes 7 cups.

title: cattleman's salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Add Milnot to choice of consistency.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix 1 stick of the margarine with the cracker crumbs.
Press into 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Beat remaining 2 sticks of margarine, eggs and confectioners sugar for 15 minutes.
(It must be beaten for 15 minutes.)
Spread over cracker crumbs.
Slice bananas over this mixture, then put pineapple which has been drained in a colander over bananas.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with pecans and garnish with cherries.
Chill before serving. Delicious.

title: chicken fajita dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and microwave until hot.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: colbert place chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute celery, bell pepper and onions in butter.
Boil spaghetti in reserved broth.
Drain, reserving broth again.
Mix remaining ingredients with spaghetti.
If mixture is too thick, add some chicken broth.
Bake in large casserole dish approximately 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with Cheddar cheese (grated), if desired. Yield:
12 servings.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all together.
Put in glass dish.
Mold into a loaf.
Put in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.
Put ketchup on top.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix together. Put in 9 x 13 baking dish. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: strawberry-banana shake
directions: Wash and cap strawberries; drain well.
Place strawberries in a single layer in a shallow pan.
Freeze.
Combine remaining ingredients in electric blender; process until smooth.
Serve immediately.
Yields 4 1/2 cups (59 calories per 1/2-cup serving).

title: deer jerky
directions: Use 11 x 13 x 2-inch pan to marinate meat.

title: popover pizza
directions: Brown hamburger, onion, and salt.
Drain.
Add pizza sauce. Pour hamburger mixture into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese over this.
Combine in a bowl, eggs, milk, oil and flour.
Beat until smooth.
Pour batter over cheese and hamburger mixture.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over batter.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Cut and serve each piece upside down.

title: green chile cheese pie(not a dessert)
directions: Put peppers and cheese in plate.
Beat other ingredients and add. Spread evenly over plate.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350° until knife comes out clean.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: bruce's potato skins
directions: Bake potatoes in oven until done.
Let cool.
Cut potatoes into 3 equal parts and scoop out potatoes, leaving skin intact with a shallow layer of potato left in.
Fry potato skins in oil until brown and crispy.
Arrange skins on a cookie sheet and top with bacon, grated cheese, and green onions.
Bake in oven only until cheese melts.
Use sour cream for dipping.

title: hermits
directions: Sift together soda, salt, flour, ginger, cinnamon and ground cloves.
Mix shortening, sugar, egg and molasses well.
Stir in remaining sifted ingredients.
Add raisins last.
Press evenly over ungreased jelly roll pan (11 x 17-inch) or shape in rolls about one inch in diameter and squash lightly with wet glass bottom to 1/3-inch thickness.
Sprinkle sugar over dough.
Bake for 9 to 11 minutes at 375°.
Cracks in the cookies will remain yellow and appear uncooked, but remove from oven.
Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: breakfast pizza(club member:  terah)
directions: Cook sausage until brown and crumbly. Brown onions and peppers if used; drain well. Spread dough into 8 triangles.

Place on ungreased 12-inch pizza pan with points toward center. Press over bottom and up sides, sealing to make crust. Spoon sausage on crust and sprinkle on potatoes. Top with cheese. Beat eggs with milk; salt and pepper. Pour into crust and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cajun barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.

title: coleslaw dressing
directions: Combine mayonnaise and sour cream. Whisk until well blended. Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Refrigerate.

title: rice salad
directions: When rice and eggs are cold, chop the eggs and add to the rice.
Add all ingredients and mix well. Better if made the day before serving.

title: danish puff
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut 1/2 cup butter into 1 cup flour. Sprinkle 2 tablespoons water over mixture.
Round into ball, divide in half.
On ungreased baking sheet, pat each half into strips (12 x 13-inches).
Strips should be about 3-inches apart. Heat 1/2 cup butter and 1 cup water to rolling boil in medium saucepan.
Remove from heat and quickly stir in almond extract and 1 cup flour.
Stir vigorously over low heat until the mixture forms a ball, about 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Beat in eggs, all at once, until smooth and glossy.
Divide in half, spread each half evenly over strips.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes or until topping is crisp and brown.
Topping will shrink and fall forming the custardy top of the puff.
Frost with Confectioners Sugar Glaze and sprinkle with nuts.

title: flat bread
directions: Heat water and buttermilk together.
Add shortening and stir with dry ingredients to make a very stiff dough.
Roll dough as thinly as possible using whole wheat flour to flour the board for rolling.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a 9 x 12-inch greased pan. Bake at 350° about 40 minutes.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Melt butter in saucepan over medium heat.
Add brown sugar and salt.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Add milk.
Cook 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and cool.
Pour mixture into a mixing bowl.
Add vanilla and confectioners sugar.
Stir on fold/dry to moisten ingredients; blend on whip/cream for 2 minutes. Frosts two 8-inch layers.

title: ice cream torte
directions: Crush cookies and spread in 9 x 13-inch cake pan (save a few crumbs for top).
Melt chocolate with butter.
Mix in powdered sugar, vanilla and beaten egg yolks.
Mix well.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour mixture over crumbs and freeze overnight. Soften ice cream and spread top of frozen layer.
Sprinkle with remaining crumbs and freeze.

title: dane thin pancakes
directions: Mix well.
Put some oil in pan over medium heat.
Pour a little batter in center of pan and roll it around until batter is real thin and out to the edge.
Turn and bake on other side.

title: halibut batter
directions: Beat all together.
You can use water, milk or beer.
Mix until wet enough to stick to fish.
Cut into small pieces, then fry until light brown.

title: blueberry swirl pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix melted butter, flour, oats and nuts; press into pie plate and bake 15 minutes.

title: microwave strawberry jam
directions: Place strawberries in 3 quart bowl.
Microwave high for 4 minutes, breaking up strawberries after 1 1/2 minutes or until mixture reaches boiling.
Stir in sugar and lemon juice and microwave for 8 minutes stirring 3 or 4 times during cooking time until full boil.
Microwave full 1 minute after coming to complete boil.
Pour into glasses and refrigerate.
Do not double the recipe.

title: salmon party ball
directions: Drain salmon.
Remove skin and bones.
Combine salmon, cream cheese, lemon juice, onion, horseradish, salt and liquid smoke. Mix and chill.
Combine parsley and nuts.
Shape into a ball and roll in nut mixture.
Chill well and serve surrounded with crackers.

title: zelinky
directions: Snip the sauerkraut with kitchen shears.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well; chill.
Roll out a bit thicker than for pie crust.
Cut into 2-inch squares and bake on ungreased pan at 350° until brown and crisp.

title: dog biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly beat the egg.
In a large bowl, stir together the egg, milk, vegetable oil and honey.
Use a large spoon.
This is not a job for an electric mixer.
Combine the flour, bran cereal and rolled oats.
Add them to the egg mixture.
Stir until you've created a stiff dough.
Sprinkle flour on a pastry cloth or board and roll dough to about 1/4-inch thick. Use a knife or toothpick to mark bone shapes.
Each about two inches long or you may use a bone-shaped cookie cutter.
Roll up the scraps of dough; roll out again and cut more biscuits.
Place on a lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake for about 15 minutes. Makes about 2 dozen.

title: irish bread
directions: Sift together the flour, salt and baking powder.
Add melted butter.
Blend together the eggs, milk, sugar, raisins and seed and add to first mixture.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan and sprinkle sugar on top.
Bake at 350° for 3/4 to 1 hour.

title: carrot soup with cinnamon
directions: Combine the carrots, onions and 2 teaspoons broth in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover tightly and cook on High for 2 minutes.
Stir in the remaining ingredients.
Cover again and cook on High for 3 to 6 minutes, or until heated through.

title: winter fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit; mix together and chill at least 1 hour.
When ready to serve, add 1 red apple, sliced.

title: care-a-lot candy
directions: Mash butter.
Add syrup.
Pat sugar in little at a time.
When you cannot stir, use your hands.
Squeeze and pound candy until soft and smooth.
Pour in granola.
Mix with hands.
Make into small balls.
Pour into refrigerator.
Leave 1 hour.

title: french dressing
directions: Put in jar and shake well.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix crackers and sugar into melted oleo and press into a 9 x 9-inch square pan.

title: baked stuffed scallops
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Combine cracker crumbs, cheese, salt, pepper, garlic powder and Parmesan cheese.
Place fish in a greased casserole.
Top with stuffing mix.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove cover for last 15 minutes.
If using haddock, bake for 1 hour.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook celery, onion and carrots in broth until tender.
Brown mushrooms in melted margarine.
Add flour and seasonings.
Cook 5 minutes.
Mix chicken and parsley with sauce and heat until boiling.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Arrange biscuits on top and bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Bake leftover biscuits and serve with pie.

title: fiesta balls
directions: Cook hamburger, drain.
Add onion, then tomato sauce and olives.
Mix well and heat.
Add cheese until it just starts to melt.
Toss lightly.
Stuff meat mixture into "hollowed out" rolls.
Heat in individually wrapped foil.
May be frozen individually.

title: holiday fruit cookies
directions: Cut fruit in small pieces; leave pecans in halves.
Sift flour, soda and salt together and sift over chopped fruit and pecans.
Cream butter and sugar until light.
Add beaten eggs and mix well. Stir in vanilla, lemon and cinnamon.
Stir in flour-covered fruit.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets and bake at 300° for about 25 minutes.
Yields 150 small cookies.

title: mary's chex mix
directions: Mix ingredients together and marinate awhile before baking. Bake at 250° for 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Mix all ingredients except berries.
Pour into greased baking dish (9 x 9-inch).
Pour berries on top.
Bake at 350° until brown, approximately 25 to 30 minutes.
Crust will rise up over the top of berries.

title: nut balls
directions: Cream butter; add sugar, vanilla and water.
Mix well.
Add flour and salt; mix well.
Add crushed nuts.
Shape into bite - sized balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 8 - 10 minutes at 325 degrees.
When cool, roll in powdered sugar.

title: red beet salad
directions: Scrub beets and cook in salted water until tender.
Cool and slice thinly.
From other ingredients, prepare a marinade.
Pour marinade over beets.
Let soak for several hours.

title: cheese and olive appetizers
directions: Mix together like pie crust.
Chill.
Work together with hands.
Take one tablespoon and work into ball.
Insert small stuffed olive.
Chill or freeze.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes or until slightly brown.

title: persimmon pudding and lemon sauce
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Pour in milk; mix well.
Add nuts and raisins.
Add persimmon pulp last.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into greased baking dish, cover and set in pan of water.
Bake 70 minutes in a 375° oven.
Serve with Lemon Sauce, hot or cold.

title: fourth of july fruit cup
directions: Clean berries; remove stems.
Place berries in a large bowl. Peel and slice bananas into bowl.
Toss lightly.
Serve this in red, white and blue snack cups or small bowls.
Serves 24.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Add sugar and eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
Sift all dry ingredients together.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Add vanilla and bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until done.

title: delicious bean soup
directions: Soak beans overnight in 1 quart of water, then drain beans and measure liquid.
Add enough water to make 2 quarts.
Place soaked beans, water and ham bone in a kettle.
Cover and simmer 2 hours. Add onions, potato, celery, carrots and garlic.
Simmer 1 more hour.
Remove meat from bone and return meat to soup.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Serve piping hot.
Any leftovers freeze well.

title: grapefruit wedge salad
directions: Cut
grapefruit in halves.
Remove pulp from rind.
Cut enough segment to make 1 cup.
Squeeze enough juice for 1 cup. Add grapefruit juice to apricot juice (drained from apricots) which will be 2 cups in all.
Heat juice and add to Jell-O and sugar. Cool
slightly.
Add
grapefruit	segments,
mashed apricots and pecans to mixture.
Fill rind halves with Jell-O and cool.
To serve,
cut
each	half
in quarters.
Serve on fruit
leaves
or English ivy leaves.
Poppy seed dressing may be used.
Serves 12.

title: fruit pie
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice.
Drain fruit.
Mix lemon juice, milk, chopped fruit and Cool Whip.
Pour into pie shell and cool for 2 or 3 hours.
Makes 2 pies.

title: mandarin orange pie
directions: Mash oranges with condensed milk.
Add other ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: pork chops and potato casserole
directions: Flour pork chops and lightly brown in skillet.
Lay pork chops in a casserole dish.
Cover meat with cream of potato soup. Season with pepper to taste.

title: oatmeal all-bran bread
directions: Pour 3 cups boiling water over all (not the yeast); stir and let stand until lukewarm.
Add dry yeast and enough white flour to make a stiff dough.
Let rise until double; knead down and let rise again.
Place in two greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: best ever meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare sauce in a bowl and set aside. Combine meat loaf ingredients until evenly mixed.
Work in half of the sauce with the meat loaf.
Place the meat loaf in a dish or loaf pan and shape it.
Pour the remaining sauce on top and bake for 50 minutes or until center is no longer pink.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and mashed bananas; mix well.
Combine flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt to cream mixture, alternately with milk.
Add nuts.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, then at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: stuffed manicotti
directions: Chop all seasoning.
Remove sausage from casing and combine with beef.
Brown well in skillet.
Add chopped seasoning.
Saute. Remove from heat.
Add Romano cheese.
Let cool.
Cook manicotti according to directions.
Add 3 raw eggs to the cooked meat.
Add Italian breadcrumbs.
Mix, then stuff manicotti.
Arrange in a baking dish.
Add your favorite Italian red gravy.
Sprinkle with Romano cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Cook carrots in steamer until tender.
Heat together the brown sugar and margarine until sugar dissolves.
Add to carrots and cook over medium heat, turning until well glazed.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; stir yeast into buttermilk.
Set aside.
Combine flour and sugar.
Cut in shortening.
Add buttermilk mixture.
Stir until moistened.
Turn dough out on lightly floured surface.
Knead lightly 3 or 4 times.
Roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake in oven preheated at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Dough may be stored in refrigerator in covered container for up to 3 days.

title: banana split pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Refrigerate for a couple of hours before serving.

title: fried cucumbers
directions: Slice cucumbers and roll in flour mixture evenly.
Put in the hot grease, turning often, until light brown and cucumbers are tender.

title: chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Mix ingredients except chocolate chips.
Beat thoroughly. Stir in 16 ounces chocolate chips.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes, then turn onto a plate.

title: mexican salad
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Shred or dice cheese.
Add beans, diced tomatoes and chopped onion.
Cut or tear lettuce into bite size pieces.
Mix all ingredients well.
Pour Catalina dressing, crushed Fritos and taco seasoning over all and stir.
Makes a great meal.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Puts chicken in pan, then put noodles. Cook about 7 minutes. Take out and feed it to us.

title: brownies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs one at a time, while beating.
Add slightly cooled chocolate, then the sifted flour. Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan, then sprinkle nuts over top, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, no longer.
If the top of brownies cracks as it cools, don't worry.
It is supposed to do that.
Cut in squares after it cools and enjoy.

title: cherry drink
directions: Place all fruits and juice in a blender and blend together until smooth.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 1/2 cups.

title: impossible cauliflower quiche
directions: Cook cauliflower (or broccoli) in salted water for 10 minutes. Drain and place in a greased pie pan.
Sprinkle with onion, green pepper and cheese.
Place remaining ingredients in blender or food processor for 15 to 20 seconds.
Pour over cauliflower mixture. Bake 20 to 25 minutes in a 375° oven.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: auburn tiger butter
directions: Melt white chocolate and peanut butter together over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Spray a 13 x 9-inch pan with nonstick spray.
Spread chocolate and peanut butter mixture in pan.
With a spoon, spread melted chocolate chips on top of mixture.
Use a knife to make swirl designs.
Refrigerate until hard.
Remove from refrigerator and cut into small pieces.

title: peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in refrigerator overnight.
Remove and make into 1-inch balls and roll in white sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and flatten with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Bake cake following directions on the box.
In a bowl, mix sifted powdered sugar, margarine, strawberries (drained and thawed), vanilla and pecans.
Pour over cooled cake.

title: lemon pie
directions: Place lemon juice in bowl.
Add milk and stir until well mixed.
Add Cool Whip; mix well with spoon.
Pour into crust and let sit until firm.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: rice cooker seafood jambalaya
directions: Put oleo in rice cooker and turn on until oleo melts.
Turn off again, then add all ingredients into rice cooker and stir well.
Cover; cook for 15 minutes and then stir.
Cover and cook for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli corn bake
directions: Cook broccoli in salted water for 5 minutes.
Drain well. Saute onion in margarine until tender, but not brown.
Combine broccoli, onion, corn and egg in a 1 1/2-quart greased casserole dish.
Combine crackers and margarine.
Spoon over vegetables. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until brown and set in center.

title: banana bread
directions: Beat 1st four ingredients until well mixed. Add flour, soda and salt. Mix well. Add nuts. Bake 30 to 40 minutes in 2 small greased loaf pans at 350°.

title: lemon cookies
directions: Combine cake mix, eggs, oil and lemon juice in a large bowl. Beat at low speed until well blended. Add nuts or coconut.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Bake at 375° for 6 to 7 minutes until lightly brown. Cool 1 minute on sheet.
Remove to cooling rack. Dust with 10x sugar or frost with 1 cup 10x sugar and 1 tablespoon lemon juice.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Mix the remaining ingredients except cheese.
Cook for 5 minutes on medium heat.
Add cheese.
Stir occasionally until melted.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook and debone chicken (save broth liquid). Cook box of wild rice according to box directions. Can do this the night before.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients; cover.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Peel and cut potatoes in 2-inch pieces. Combine margarine, water and sugar in black skillet. Add potatoes. Simmer at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: sweet lime pickles
directions: Soak sliced cukes 12 hours in lime water (1 cup to 2 gallons). Rinse several times removing lime.
Cover in ice water 3 hours; drain
well.
Dissolve sugar and salt in Heinz vinegar; add spice bag and boil.
Pour hot syrup over pickles; let soak overnight.

title: swiss steak
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Rub each side of meat with salt and pepper. Place meat in deep baking dish. Add enough water to cover halfway on the meat. Add the bay leaves.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend cream cheese, peanut butter, sugar, and vanilla with mixer until smooth.
Gently fold in Cool Whip.
Spoon into crust and freeze.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Return to freezer.

title: clarice's chili
directions: Add and mix all ingredients.
Simmer 1 to 2 hours.

title: lime salad
directions: Dissolve marshmallows in 2 cups boiling water; add jello. Place in refrigerator until slightly congealed.
Remove and add nuts, pineapple and whipped cream.
Pour in molds and congeal. Serve on lettuce.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake for 1 hour at 325°.
(Tastes like chess pie.)

title: banana cake
directions: Bake in 3 layers at 350° until done.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, mix Ricotta cheese, half of Mozzarella cheese, egg, spinach, carrots, salt, oregano and pepper.

title: ham and beans
directions: Cover with water and cook for 2 to 3 hours, checking water often.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Combine pudding mix and cold milk.
Beat well.
Fold in whipped topping.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Chill at least one hour.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Boil cranberries, salt and water for 10 minutes.
Add soda; strain over sugar, Jell-O and marshmallows.
Cool.
Add apples, celery and pecans.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch dish and chill.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar and mix well.
Add beaten eggs and vanilla.
Stir in soda, flour and oats.
Form in small balls. Place on cookie sheet and press with a fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cantonese casserole(international)
directions: Mix together in cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pear preserve cake
directions: Cream shortening.
Gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Combine flour, soda, salt and spices; add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix just until blended.
Stir in vanilla, preserves and pecans.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 35 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes; remove from pan and cool completely.

title: beef cheese ball
directions: Shred beef (reserve 1/2 cup).
Mix all other ingredients. Shape into 2 large or 4 small balls.
Roll in reserved beef. Serve at room temperature.
(Makes great gifts.) Freezes well.

title: hawaiian delight
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onion.
Drain.
Combine meat, rice, corn, peas, chili powder and tomato sauce.
Place in baking dish. Cover with grated cheese and bake at 350° for about 20 minutes. Green peppers can be added with onions, if desired.

title: chicken wellington
directions: Thaw pastry 20 minutes.
Sprinkle chicken with seasonings. In medium skillet, brown chicken in 3 tablespoons margarine; set aside.
Add remaining margarine to skillet.
Add onion and mushrooms; saute until tender and liquid has evaporated.
Stir in parsley.

title: ham glaze
directions: Mix together.
Place pineapple rings on top of ham and stud with cloves.
Brush glaze over ham.
Bake.
During the last 15 minutes, brush on remaining glaze.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer first four salad ingredients in order.

title: osogood pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add egg yolk.
Beat well.
Add raisins, nuts and vanilla and fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake in unbaked pie shell.

title: no bake mini cheesecakes
directions: Mix crumb mixture as directed on package.
Press onto bottom of 12 paper-lined muffin cups.
Prepare filling mix as directed on package.
Spoon over crumb mixture.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour or until ready to serve.
Garnish as desired.
Makes 12 servings.

title: frog eye salad
directions: Combine sugar, flour and 1 half teaspoon salt. Gradually stir in pineapple juice and eggs. Cook over moderate heat, stirring until thickened.
Add lemon juice. Cool mixture to room temperature.

title: baked chicken with chipped beef
directions: Layer chipped beef in bottom of baking dish sprayed with Pam. Put chicken breasts on top of beef.
Combine soup and sour cream and pour over chicken.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: In
buttered
dish,
mix first 4 ingredients.
Then mix butter, soup, milk and mayonnaise and pour over first mixture. Spread cheese over this mixture.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Combine salad dressing mix, sour cream and mayonnaise.
Set aside.
Place half of crumbled corn bread in bottom of large bowl.
Add half of beans.
Top beans with mayonnaise.
Mix.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar well, then add the eggs, beating after each.
Add vanilla together with the milk.
Add the baking powder, crushed graham crackers and pecans.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 3 large or 4 small layers.

title: cheater chili
directions: In a large kettle, cook ground beef, onion, green pepper and garlic until meat is browned.
Drain off fat.
Combine remaining ingredients and bring to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer about 20 minutes.
Taste before serving, adding more chili powder or hot sauce, if desired.

title: easy candies
directions: Melt together at low heat and then let sit 10 minutes.
Add 5 cups Rice Krispies and 1/2 cup salted peanuts.
Drop by teaspoons on wax paper.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: vanilla-maple milkshake
directions: Pour milk and syrup into a blender container; add ice cream and cover.
Blend on medium speed about 1 minute or until smooth. Pour into 2 glasses.
Sprinkle with cinnamon, if desired.
Serve immediately.
Makes 2 servings.

title: shrimp jambalaya
directions: Fry the bacon in a skillet until crisp.
Drain on paper towels.
Cool pan down.

Put it on medium heat and cook the celery, onion and paper in the bacon fat until the onion is soft. Add the garlic, tomatoes, cayenne pepper, chili powder and thyme. Lower heat and simmer for 20 minutes.
Add shrimp, parsley and salt.
Cook just until the shrimp is hot.
Mound rice on a platter.
Spoon the shrimp and tomato sauce over it.
Garnish with bits of crisp bacon.

title: strawberry pretzel dessert
directions: Make crust of pretzels, margarine and 3 tablespoons sugar. Press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Bake
at 375° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: fruit cocktail cookies
directions: Mix brown sugar, white sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add fruit cocktail (drained), walnuts, flour, salt, baking soda, baking powder, allspice and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: potato leek soup(yield: 6-8 servings)
directions: 1. Heat olive oil and butter in soup pot until hot. Add vegetables, season with salt and pepper.

title: cream cheese danties
directions: Cream together the butter, cheese, sugar and extract until fluffy. Stir in flour just enough until combined. Chill 1 to 2 hours. Shape into balls. Roll in cereal and place on ungreased cookie sheet. Top each with a cherry. Bake in a 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes. Cool on rack.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: shrimp peri-peri
directions: Chop garlic and mix with salt. Combine with oil and lemon juice. Pour over shrimp and mix well. Add Peri-Peri or pepper. Marinate at least 30 minutes.
Arrange shrimp in shallow baking dish and pour melted butter over all.
Broil 5 to 8 minutes turning once.

title: outrageous chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Beat margarine, sugars, peanut butter, vanilla and eggs in large mixing bowl until creamy and well blended.
Mix in flour and oats.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop dough by rounded tablespoonfuls, about 2-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool 1 minute.
Remove from cookie sheet to wire rack.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream together butter and margarine.
Add sugar, then eggs, one at a time.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Bake in 9 or 10 inch tube pan at 325° for about 1 hour 15 minutes (test for doneness).

title: fudge(club member: nicholas thompson)
directions: Mix all ingredients well. You may also add 1/2 cup chopped nuts. Pour into greased pan. Refrigerate. Cut into squares.

title: spinach balls
directions: Lightly saute onion in oil; set aside to cool.
Combine other ingredients, then add sauteed onion (drained).
Chill and roll into balls.
Freeze now, or bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Put butter on hands when rolling balls.
They are done when they stay together and bottoms are light brown.

title: rancho beans
directions: Brown meat and onions in 2 tablespoons shortening until meat is done.
Drain meat; add remaining ingredients.
Bake in moderate oven for 25 minutes.
Can be mixed the day before needed and refrigerated.
Freezes well also.

title: tuna pate
directions: Combine all ingredients in food processor and mix well.
Oil or grease a bowl or mold.
Press pate into it firmly.
Chill well. Turn out onto pretty plate and garnish with olives, cherry tomatoes and parsley if desired.
Can be frozen.
Defrost in refrigerator 24 hours.

title: spinach and mashed potatoes
directions: Blanch spinach and squeeze out liquid.
Mix mashed potatoes, butter, salt, black pepper and spinach.
Serve hot as a side dish.

title: irish cream
directions: Mix in blender until well mixed.
Bottle; use in 1 month. Refrigerate.

title: venison meat balls
directions: Bring to a boil in a medium saucepan.
Pour over meat balls. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Can be made with all hamburger.

title: diet punch
directions: Mix all ingredients except 7-Up; stir until dissolved. Add 7-Up just before serving.

title: turtle bars
directions: Mix cake mix, egg and melted butter.
Set aside 1 cup.
Spread rest on bottom of 11 x 14-inch pan and bake for 10 minutes at 350°. In microwave melt the caramels, stick of butter and Milnot.
(Has to be creamy and smooth.)
Pour on top of crust from oven. Sprinkle with chocolate chips, nuts and cake mix you set aside. Bake for 20 minutes.
Let cool at least 2 hours so caramel sets up.

title: tuna-macaroni casserole
directions: Combine macaroni, tuna, mayonnaise, celery and salt.
Blend soup and milk; heat.
Add cheese and heat until cheese melts.
Add macaroni mixture.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake for 20 minutes on 450° or until brown.

title: marinated sliced tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes 1/2-inch thick and place in a single layer in a large shallow dish.

title: shoo-fly cupcakes
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients.
Save 1 cup of the crumbs.
Mix next 3 ingredients.
Add the flour mixture.
Mix well, will not be smooth.
Fill cupcake liners 1/2 full.
Sprinkle with crumbs. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate chip fudge
directions: Cook sugar, butter, milk and vanilla together until boiling, then put chips, marshmallow cream and nuts.

title: crock-pot stew
directions: Place meat in crock-pot; mix flour, salt and pepper.
Coat meat in crock-pot.
Add remaining ingredients and stir to mix. Cook on low for 10 to 12 hours or on high for 4 to 6 hours. Serves 6.

title: shortbread
directions: Cream the butter and shortening with powdered sugar and brown sugar.
Work in sifted flour.
Roll dough out about 1/4 inch thick. Cut into shapes or sticks.
Sprinkle with granulated sugar.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet at 350° until light brown.

title: deer roast
directions: Dredge meat in flour then brown in a Dutch oven.
Add lots of ground pepper and salt to taste.
Mix catsup and spices.
Pour over meat.
Add water.
Cook slowly in a 325° oven.
Add onions, carrots and potatoes after 1 hour.
Continue to cook for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: twice baked potato casserole
directions: Cut baked potatoes into 1-inch cubes. Place 1/2 in greased 13 x 9 x 2 pan. Sprinkle with half of salt, pepper and bacon. Top with half sour cream and cheeses. Repeat layer. Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 20 to 30 minutes. Sprinkle with scallions.

title: old fashion peanut brittle
directions: Melt margarine in small saucepan over very low heat.
Add peanuts and salt to warm.
Place sugar in large thick skillet over medium heat.
Stir continuously until sugar caramelizes into golden brown syrup.
Stir in peanuts.
Pour onto large buttered surface at once.
With big spoon, stretch.
Makes 1 1/2 pounds brittle.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: quick fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple and fruit cocktail and save juice.
Drain oranges, but don't save juice.
In large bowl, dissolve pudding with 2 juices.
Stir until pudding is dissolved; do not beat.
It will thicken some as it sets.
Just before serving, add bananas or serve without.

title: chocolate amaretto cheese cake
directions: Sprinkle chocolate wafer crumbs in bottom of 7-inch spring-form pan.
Set aside.
Position knife blade in food processor bowl; add cream cheese and next 7 ingredients, processing until smooth.
Add eggs and process just until blended. Fold in chocolate morsels.
Slowly pour mixture over crumbs in pan.
Bake at 300° for 65 to 70 minutes or until cheese cake is set. Let cool in pan on wire rack.
Cover and chill at least 8 hours.
Remove sides of pan and transfer to serving plate. Garnish with curls.
Serves 12.

title: singles snack
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Toss with dressing and serve with crackers.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook ground beef until brown.
Drain grease.
Add taco mix and 1 cup water.
Bring to a boil.
Let simmer for 5 minutes.
Shred cheese; dice onion and shred lettuce in a bowl with tomato.
Crush chips.
Put all this into a bowl and mix.
Add ground beef last. Stir until mixed well.
Serve with hot sauce.

title: chocolate pie
directions: In a medium saucepan, blend dry ingredients.
Add 1 cup hot milk;
mix
well.
Blend
in egg yolks and add last cup of hot milk.
Cook
over
medium heat, stirring constantly until thick, about
minutes.
Add
butter and vanilla.
Pour into cool, baked pie crust.
Top with meringue and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: green tomato mincemeat
directions: Mix together.
Cook slowly for 1 hour.
Bottle and seal (water bath for 10 minutes).
Yields 12 quarts.

title: lentil and split pea ham soup
directions: Cover lentils and split peas with water; soak overnight. Drain.
Place lentils and split peas in large saucepan with 8 cups water, ham, onion, garlic, bay leaf and cayenne.
Bring to boil; reduce flame.
Simmer, partially covered, 2 hours until lentils and split peas are tender and mixture thickens.
Add carrots and celery.
Simmer, uncovered, 45 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Remove bay leaf.
Yield:
about 1 1/2 quarts.

title: old fashion christmas cookies
directions: Sift flour; measure.
Add salt, soda and baking powder, then sift again.
Add nutmeg to sifted flour.
Cream shortening; add both sugars.
Beat the eggs at one side in same bowl, then blend with shortening and sugar mixture.
Add extracts.
Add dry ingredients, alternating with buttermilk.
Chill several hours. Roll and cut out.
Bake at 325° for approximately 13 minutes or until done.

title: chicken and noodle casserole
directions: Mix all together and put in long Pyrex dish.
Top with buttered crumbs.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream the Crisco and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add buttermilk and beat well.
Add eggs. Sift the flour; measure baking powder, salt and soda.
Sift together 3 or 4 times.
Add flour all at once.
Beat well.
Add flavoring last.
Bake at 300° to 325° for 1 hour; do not open oven.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients and set aside.
Beat eggs lightly in large mixing bowl.
Add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Stir in zucchini and pineapple.
Add dry ingredients, stirring only until moistened.
Pour batter into 2 well-greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done. Cool 10 minutes; turn out on racks.

title: rye bread dip
directions: Make the dip in advance and chill well.
Before serving, hollow out a whole loaf of round, unsliced, rye bread.
Serve dip inside the hollowed out area.
Take the bread which was removed from the loaf and break it into pieces.
It is good with the dip, as well as vegetables.

title: bavarian pot roast
directions: In a large Dutch oven, heat oil over high and brown meat on all sides.
Combine all remaining ingredients, except mushrooms; pour over meat.
Cover and reduce heat to simmer.
Cook 2 1/2 to 3 hours or until meat is tender.
Transfer meat to platter; keep warm.
Add mushrooms to cooking juices; simmer 5 minutes.
With a slotted spoon, remove mushrooms and spoon over roast.
Meanwhile, reduce cooking juices to desired thickness by cooking over high heat.
Spoon a portion of the gravy over roast and pass the rest. Yields 12 to 15 servings.

title: cheese spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in casserole at 350° until bubbly and light brown on edges.
Delicious spread on crackers and so easy!
Before serving, I drain the liquid!

title: shells and spinach bake
directions: Cook shells according to package directions.
Drain.
Toss with 2 1/2 cups sauce.
Meanwhile, in medium bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
In 2 1/2-quart casserole, layer 1/2 shell mixture.
Spread cheese filling over shells.
Cover with remaining shells.
Top with remaining 1 cup sauce.
Sprinkle with additional Parmesan cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: granola cereal
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients, then honey and oil.
Put in large roaster and bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring often.
Add raisins after baking.
Use your own imagination for variation.
Shredded Wheat may be added or substituted in part.
Dried dates or dried apples, cinnamon, etc. may be added.
Adds more flavor.
If you do not have wheat germ, omit and use more oatmeal.
Makes good eating.

title: pam's broccoli corn casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender; drain.
Beat egg and add cooked broccoli and corn.
Add onion, salt and pepper to taste.
Add one handful of crackers, crushed with your hand.

title: turkey sausage
directions: Blend all ingredients together very well.
Make patties and fry.

title: tropical salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserve 2 Tbsp. juice (set aside)
Stir lemon juice and sliced banana, into pineapple juice.
In a large bowl combine cabbage, oranges, marshmallows, coconut, salt, raisins, walnuts, pineapple and banana mixture.
Add yogurt, toss to coat, cover and refrigerate before serving.
Serves 10.	Can be used as salad or dessert.

title: hot mustard sauce
directions: Heat until bubbly.
Great for dipping cocktail wieners or pour over cream cheese and liverwurst.

title: german pancakes
directions: Mix ingredients in a blender.
Pour into 2 (9-inch) buttered cake or pie pans.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.
Reduce to 350° for 5 to 10 minutes.
Top with syrup and butter or powdered sugar.
Also good with fresh fruit and whipped cream.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
mix with onions and beef.
Form in a ball and cover with chopped pecans.

title: cheese apples
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar in a bowl.
Add cheese; continue beating until well blended.
Add flour and mix well.
Put the apples in the buttered casserole dish.
Cover the apples with the cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Crush Ritz crackers and mix with sugar.
Melt margarine and pour over crackers and sugar mix.
Mix and pat into 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Mix pudding with evaporated milk (follow box directions).
Spread pudding mix over crumb crust.
Cover with Cool Whip and sprinkle crumbled Heath bars over top.
Refrigerate and serve in squares.
Delicious Christmas or St.
Patrick's Day dessert ... or any day of the week!

title: venison stew
directions: Fry fat back.
Boil venison until tender.
To fat back drippings, add venison, potatoes, onions and celery.
Add enough water to cover.
Cook until onions are done.
Add other ingredients.
Simmer at least 30 minutes, stirring constantly.

title: caramel nut cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugars. Add eggs, one at a time.
Combine flour, salt and baking powder. Add slowly alternating with milk and beating mixture as you go. Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Brown celery and onion in butter.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Bake in casserole at 350° for one hour.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: You will need an 8 1/2-quart punch bowl.

title: super nachos
directions: Fry beef and large onion until lightly browned; drain.
Season with salt and Tabasco sauce; set aside.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Put all fruit through food grinder and add sugar.
Mix well and keep refrigerated.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon in a plastic Ziploc bag.
Place each biscuit in the mix and shake it.
Place in greased Bundt pan. Pour the leftover mix over the biscuits, then pour over the melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Parboil chicken until about half tender; drain.
Reserve broth.
Cut chicken in cubes or slice thin.
Add all soups, broccoli and rice.
Place in casserole dish.
Use enough reserved broth to moisten stuffing mix.
Place on top of other ingredients; cover.
Bake in 350° preheated oven for 1 hour.

title: no fat brownie oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine dry ingredients and stir.
Combine liquids and stir. Add to dry ingredients and stir until moistened.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheets sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Store in sealed container.

title: apricot jello dessert
directions: Mix Jell-O and water; let cool.
Add pineapple, sliced bananas and marshmallows to Jell-O mixture.
Refrigerate and let set. Cook pineapple juice, sugar, egg and flour until thick.
Add cream cheese; stir until smooth.
Prepare Dream Whip according to package directions; fold into cooked mixture.
Remove Jell-O from refrigerator and spread cooked mixture over Jell-O.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Refrigerate.

title: potato pie
directions: Put cottage cheese through blender.
Add potatoes and other ingredients and mix together in mixer.
Pour into pie shell. Sprinkle with grated cheese. Bake at 425° for 50 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream both sugars, Crisco and oil.
Add eggs, vanilla, flour, soda, salt and chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pimiento cheese spread
directions: Chop peppers. Add juice and peppers to cream cheese and grated Cheddar cheese. Add mayonnaise, onion, cayenne pepper and black pepper. Mix well until blended together. Enjoy!

title: tuna macaroni bake
directions: Mix all ingredients in baking dish and bake until bubbly on top.

title: caramel coffee cakes
directions: Mix the water, brown sugar and butter; stir.
Place in microwave on High for 1 minute.
Take out and stir.
Place biscuits in the topping.
Place in microwave for 3 minutes on "Defrost" setting.
Check them by poking them; when they bounce back, they are ready.
Continue microwaving and checking until they are done.
When they are ready, turn upside down on another plate.
Serve and enjoy.

title: tomato aspic
directions: Dissolve jello and salt in boiling tomato juice.
Add cold juice, lemon juice, horseradish and onion.
Pour into 8 x 4-inch or 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Chill until firm, about 4 hours.
Cut into squares.

title: garlic-spinach chicken
directions: Drain spinach very well.
Place chicken in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Arrange 3/4 of the garlic around the chicken.
Spread spinach evenly over top.
Process soup, wine, remaining garlic and ginger until smooth.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Top with cheese and bake, uncovered, until cheese is melted.
Good with rice or noodles.

title: "best ever" pecan pie*
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat yolks until light and thick.
Add sugar to which has been added cinnamon and cloves.
Add pecans, raisins and butter.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold gently into mixture (do not beat), adding vinegar as you fold.
Pour into 8-inch unbaked pastry shell.
Bake for 10 minutes at 400°.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Bake 25 minutes.
Cool.
Serve with unsweetened whipped cream.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Heat stock, add broccoli, onions and bay leaf.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Combine flour and butter to make roux.
Cook 8 to 10 minutes, but do not brown.
Add cooked stock to roux gradually, stirring until slightly thick and smooth.
Simmer additional 1 1/2 hours.
Pass through food mill.
Add heated milk and cream; adjust seasoning.
Serves 50.

title: microwave glazed carrots
directions: Cut carrots into long, thin strips.
Set aside.
Combine brown sugar, margarine, water, salt and cinnamon in a 1-quart casserole dish.
Microwave at High until margarine is melted (1 1/2 minutes). Stir to blend.
Stir in carrots until coated.
Cover.
Microwave at High until carrots are tender (8 minutes), stirring once.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: crock-pot beef
directions: Mix and place in crock-pot. Mix well and cook on low 8 to 12 hours or until beef is tender. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: baked corn
directions: Beat eggs well, add rest of ingredients and bake for 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour and shortening into crumb mixture.
Add salt, milk and egg together.
Mix in.	Makes three single crusts.

title: judy's thick and chewy cookies
directions: Beat butter and sugars well in large bowl.
Beat in eggs, vanilla and peanut butter until well blended.
Mix baking soda with oats and stir in with other mixture until well blended.
Stir in candies and chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoons onto cookie sheet that has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned, approximately 12 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen cookies.

title: rotel sausage dip
directions: Combine the Old El Paso cheese and salsa with Rotel
(do not drain) into a saucepan or crock pot, using low heat.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix together margarine, sugar and eggs. Sift together and stir in flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt. Roll into balls size of small walnuts. Roll in mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon. Place about 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes in 400 oven until lightly browned but still soft.

title: strawberry trifle
directions: In trifle bowl (tall, clear glass bowl) break angel food cake into small pieces.
Mix glaze, strawberries and water.
Spoon over cake letting it run down some around inside of bowl.
Mix cool whip, sour cream, sugar and milk.
Spoon over strawberry mixture. Keep refrigerated.
This can be made low cal by using sugar free cake, lite cool whip and sugar-free glaze and Splenda sugar substitute.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken and remove bones.
Cut into pieces and place in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix soups and bring to a boil.
Pour over bottom chicken.
Mix together margarine, buttermilk and flour.
Pour on top.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: taco casserole
directions: Fry the meat; drain.
Add taco seasoning, tomato sauce and water.
Stir well.
Allow to boil, then reduce heat and simmer for 15 minutes.
Add the tortilla chips and cook in oven for 15 minutes at 400°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients; bake at 400° for 20 minutes, covered. Top with 1 cup of Ritz cracker crumbs.
Return to oven, uncovered, and bake 10 minutes or until brown.

title: potato doughnuts
directions: Cream sugar with the eggs and add remaining ingredients.
Roll out lightly on floured board and cut out.
Fry in oil.
Sugar a few at a time by placing them in a paper bag with the sugar.
Shake.

title: cracklin cornbread
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.
Pour into well-greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake in 325° oven for about 30 minutes, until golden brown.

title: chicken bake
directions: Add bouillon, rice, carrots and potatoes to boiling water and salt; cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Add mushroom soup (diluted).
Stir together thoroughly.
Pour into baking dish and top with chicken chunks and pepper.
Bake in 375° oven for 15 minutes, then stir and bake for 10 minutes longer or until all liquid is absorbed.
Strips of cheese may be placed on top of hot rice.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown the beef.
Put into a 2-quart baking dish.
Drain liquid from beans, then layer beans, onion rings and Tater Tots.
Pour milk over the top; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican mixture layer dip
directions: On 12-inch plate (glass pizza dish), mix and spread first layer of refried beans and Fritos bean dip.
Next layer chopped onions.
Mix together avocados, picante sauce and lemon juice to make a guacamole mixture.
Spread on top of onions. Layer sour cream, taco seasoning, cheeses, olives and tomatoes in order given.
It looks like a pizza.
Use a spoon or cake server to dip it.
Eat with tortilla chips.

title: baked garlic sausages with garlic
directions: Split sausages.
Arrange in a greased shallow baking dish just large enough to hold them in a single layer.
Saute mushrooms and onion in butter over medium heat until lightly browned.
Smoothly mix in mustard and cream.
Bring to boiling.
Cook, stirring occasionally until liquid is reduced and slightly thickened. Divide mushroom mixture evenly into split sausages.
Top with tomatoes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes until sausages and cheese are lightly browned.

title: easy chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken and let cool; then shred.	Mix all ingredients together and toss in chicken.
Chill. Serve on pumpernickel bread. Enjoy.

title: frances' tasty chops and rice
directions: Trim fat from pork chops; cut into strips.
Brown in cooking oil.
Add vegetables; cook until vegetables are thawed.
Add soup and milk.
Cook on medium heat for 10 minutes.
Add rice; turn off heat.
Let stand 7 to 8 minutes.
Serves 2.

title: squash cornbread
directions: Combine cornmeal, flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat eggs. Add milk and cooking oil.
Add this to cornmeal mixture, then add grated squash and grated onion.
Stir together.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: In a 9 x 13 inch casserole dish, layer lettuce, onion, green pepper, celery and peas.
Mix mayonnaise and sugar and spread over the top of salad completely to the edges.
Sprinkle parmesan and bacon on top.
Seal air tight and store in the refrigerator overnight.

title: roast beef
directions: Put roast in pan.
Sprinkle with vinegar.
Spread soup over roast.
Sprinkle onion soup mix, salt and pepper over top.
Cover; roast at 350° for 1 hour.
Reduce heat to 325°; roast 2 to 3 hours longer or until meat is tender.

title: sharon's poppy seed pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well and bake in a Bundt cake pan greased well with butter or Crisco and coated with sugar (not flour). Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Combine warm noodles, soup, mayonnaise, salt and pepper in oven-safe casserole.
Top with Cheddar cheese. Place under broiler until cheese melts and is slightly brown.
Serve warm with Texas Pete as a condiment, if desired.

title: good luck pickles
directions: Mix 4 cups vinegar red or white, 6 c sugar and 1/4 c salt.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Pre-heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour bundt pan.
Combine cake mix, pudding and oil in large mixing bowl.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well.
Batter will be very thick.
By HAND, mix in sour cream.
LET SET 15 MINUTES.
Add half of the chocolate chips and mix well.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cola and marshmallows.
Beat at medium speed 1 minute.
Add cola; mix well.
By hand, stir in marshmallows.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: angel food trifle(fat-free)
directions: Prepare cake mix; cut into bite size cubes.
Combine the next 4 ingredients; cook, stirring, until thick.
Remove from heat. Whisk in egg.
Cook over medium heat for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Stir in lemon rind and juice; chill.
Later, fold yogurt into cream mixture.

title: chicken in gravy
directions: Partially cook chicken in small amount of water.
Place chicken in 3-quart baking dish.
Place slice of cheese on top of each breast piece.
Mix soup and water; pour on top of breasts. Crunch up croutons and put on top.
Pour melted butter on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.
Makes 6 servings.
Good served with rice.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of celery soup

title: pudding cake
directions: Melt margarine and combine with flour and pecans; spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Combine sugar, cream cheese and Cool Whip and pour over cooled crust. Mix the puddings and milk and pour over cheese mixture.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with nuts.

title: potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Defrost potatoes.
Mix all ingredients and pour into a greased 3 x 13
Pyrex baking dish. Bake for 1 hour.

title: chicken paprika
directions: Melt butter in Dutch oven.
When it foams, add onions and saute until soft.
Add paprika, vinegar and salt; continue cooking for a minute or two.
Add chicken and broth.
Cover and simmer over low heat until chicken is tender, about 30 minutes for breasts, 45 minutes or longer for dark meat.
If liquid evaporates, add water or more broth.
Add 1 1/2 pt. sour cream, heat to bubbling stage. Mix flour thoroughly into remaining 1/2 pt. sour cream, stir into pot and continue simmering for 5 minutes.
Serve with rice or noodles.
Serves 12.

title: oven fried chicken and biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Mix flour and seasonings in Baggie.
Put shortening or margarine (or combined to equal 1/2 cup) in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan to melt.
Shake 3 or 4 pieces of chicken in the bag to coat evenly.
Place skin side down in hot shortening (I usually have skin removed on my chicken; it doesn't make any difference whether the skin is on or not).
Bake for 30 minutes and turn chicken over and bake another 15 minutes.
Then push chicken or stack it in one end of dish.
Add 1 can biscuits or home biscuits in single layer in chicken evacuated dish and continue cooking for another 15 minutes or until biscuits are light brown on top.

title: chocolate peanut clusters
directions: Melt almond bark in top of double boiler on low heat.
Stir until melted.
Take off stove and add peanuts.
Drop by tablespoonfuls on wax paper.
Let set until hard.
Store in container with lid.

title: perfect pie meringue
directions: Beat egg whites with cream of tartar until frothy.
Gradually beat in sugar and vanilla.
Continue beating until stiff and glossy.
Put on top of cream pie and bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Combine all ingredients except spaghetti, beans and cheese. Bring to a boil. Simmer gently, covered, for 1 hour.
Add spaghetti and cook for 30 minutes, stirring.
Add beans and cheese.
Makes a big pot.

title: oatmeal drop cookies(a 1945 recipe)
directions: Cream shortening and sugar thoroughly.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Sift together flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with the milk.
Stir in vanilla. Add raisins and oats.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased sheets. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix together.
Make into 1 1/4-inch balls.
Cook in oven for 20 minutes at 350°, then drain off fat.

title: sesame seed cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; blend in almond extract and salt. Add flour and mix well.
Shape tablespoon of dough in ball; roll in sesame seed.
Place on ungreased baking sheets; flatten slightly.
Indent center of each; fill with jam.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes approximately 36 cookies.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Combine into a casserole first six ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Stir together the Ritz crackers and margarine and place on top of casserole.
Bake an additional 10 minutes.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients into bowl.
Mix oil and eggs and add to dry ingredients.
Fold in berries and nuts.
Pour into 2 greased, floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cool in pans for 15 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: brunswick stew
directions: If served at 2:00 o'clock, put up the shank as for soup, at the earliest possible hour.

Then about 12:00 o'clock, take the shank out of the soup and shred and cut all of the meat as fine as you can, carefully taking out bone and gristle, then return the meat to the soup pot and add all of the vegetables and the bread. Season with salt and pepper to taste and when ready to serve, drop into the tureen 2 or 3 tablespoons butter.

title: potato soup with cheese
directions: Bring water and salt to boil; add potatoes.
Cook until tender. Saute chiles, tomato and onion in butter.
Add to potatoes.
Just before serving, stir in cheese and bacon.

title: banana split brownie pizza
directions: Combine brownie mix, applesauce, water and egg; mix well. Place parchment paper on 15-inch baking pan or use 9 x 13-inch dish.
Pour brownie mixture on pan and spread out to 14-inch circle if using round pan.
Bake until brownies are done.
Cool completely. Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar until smooth. Spread mixture evenly over brownies.
Top with strawberries, bananas, chopped nuts and chocolate chips.
Chill.
Cut into pizza slices or into bars.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello and cranberry sauce.
Let chill until partially jelled.
Add pineapple, celery and nuts.
Pour into a large mold or individual ones and chill to firm.

title: dumplings for game meat stews
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt together well.
In separate bowl blend together eggs, milk, oil, parsley and sage.
Mix all ingredients together by adding liquids to flour mixture until well blended.
Drop by tablespoons over top of simmering stew. Continue to simmer covered 20 minutes.
Remove cover and continue simmering an additional 5 to 10 minutes, until dumplings are cooked through.

title: sesame-ginger chicken
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a small bowl. Stir well and set aside.
Place chicken between 2 sheets of heavy-duty plastic wrap and flatten to 1/4-inch thickness using a meat mallet or rolling pin.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 3/4 cup oleo; mix with cracker crumbs.
Press into a 10 x 13-inch pan.
Mix sugar, 1 1/2 cups oleo and eggs; beat 15 minutes on medium-high.
Pour over crust.
Slice bananas lengthwise; place on top.
Spread pineapple over bananas; spread Cool Whip on top. Drizzle chocolate over top, then top with cherries and nuts. Refrigerate an hour before serving.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain. Stir in rest of ingredients. Sprinkle some cheese on top and bake 15 minutes at 300°.
Serve with nachos.

title: orange julius
directions: Combine everything in a blender and blend/whip until your desired consistency.
Enjoy.

title: barbecued hamburgers
directions: Brown meat and onion, pour off fat and add rest of the ingredients.
Simmer about 30 minutes.
Serve on a small hamburger bun.
Yield: 6 servings.
Carbohydrate 5 g, protein 15 g, fat 11 g, calories 179.
One serving = 2 meat medium fat exchange, 2 fruit exchange, 1 hamburger bun = 2 bread starch exchange.

title: baked crab and shrimp dish
directions: Combine all ingredients, except crumbs.
Sprinkle crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: to die for chocolate cake
directions: Follow directions on box; bake cake and let cool.
Poke holes in cake with wooden spoon (alternating 3 hole and 4 hole rows). Pour sweetened condensed milk over cake, soaking in holes.
Pour 3/4 jar of caramel topping over top.
Spread Cool Whip on top. Crunch candy bars and spread over top.
Cover with foil. Refrigerate 6 to 8 hours.

title: buttermilk biscuit mix
directions: In a bowl, combine the first 7 ingredients; cut in the shortening until crumbly.
Store in an airtight container in a cool dry place for up to 6 months.
Yield:
about 13 1/2 cups.

title: chocolate mint patties
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together with a spoon and, if it seems too dry, use hands to finish mixing.
Shape into patties, place them on a piece of wax paper and let stand 3 to 4 hours.

title: chex muddy buddies
directions: Measure cereal into large bowl and set aside.
Combine chocolate chips, peanut butter and margarine in 1-quart microwave-safe bowl, microwave on High 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until smooth, stirring after 1 minute.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour chocolate over cereal, stirring until all pieces are coated.
Pour cereal into a Glad Lock bag with powdered sugar.
Seal and shake until all pieces are coated.
Spread on wax paper to cool.
Store in a Glad Lock bag or airtight container.

title: cheesy ham and broccoli casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook broccoli according to directions; drain.
Spread in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Layer ham and cheese over broccoli.
Beat remaining ingredients with hand beater until smooth.
Slowly pour over cheese.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Cut chicken in serving pieces; brown in hot fat.
Brown onions in fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Pour over chicken.
Bake in 300° to 325° oven for 1 hour.
Sauce may be used for other meats also.
Serves 6.

title: lemon cool whip cake
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients.
(It will be crumbly; press in with fingers.)
Bake for 10 minutes at 375°.
Cream the cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Fold in the Cool Whip and spread over.
Cook the lemon pie filling; let cool and spread on top of cream cheese layer.
Put Cool Whip on top.
Use a 10 x 4 x 2-inch or 9 1/2 x 13 1/2 x 2-inch pan.

title: bacardi rum cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube or Bundt pan.
Sprinkle nuts over bottom of pan.
Mix all cake ingredients together.
Pour batter over nuts. Bake 1 hour.
Cool.
Place cake on serving plate.
Prick holes with toothpick.
Spoon glaze evenly over tops and sides.
Allow cake to absorb glaze.
Repeat until all glaze is used.

title: black cherry forest cake "plus"
directions: Blend first 5 ingredients on low speed of electric mixer for 1 minute, then beat on medium-high speed for 2 minutes, scraping bowl frequently.
Pour into a greased and floured 14 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until done.
Cool completely.
Leave cake in pan.

title: easy chocolate mint cookies
directions: Place chocolate in a tin with a cotton ball (with a few drops of oil) for 2 days. Taste chocolate to see if minty enough; if not, a couple more drops and let set 2 more days. Place chocolate in a microwave bowl and melt. Be sure to stir constantly until chocolate is melted. Dip Ritz crackers into melted chocolate. When both sides are coated, place on cookie sheets lined with wax paper. It won't take long for the cookies to get hard. Store in an airtight container.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Pour batter into an 8 x 12-inch pan.
Spread fruit and sprinkle 1 cup sugar and 1 cup hot water over all.
The dough comes to the top when it's done.
Bake at 375° about 30 minutes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl, cream together butter and sugar.
Add the eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
In a separate bowl, combine the flour and baking powder.
Add to butter mixture alternately with the milk.
Stir until just moist.
Fold blueberries and walnuts into batter.
Fill greased muffin tins about 2/3 full.
Bake about 20 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: nonfat yogurt
directions: Heat water and milk to 115°.
Stir in yogurt.
Preheat thermos with 115° water.
Pour water out and fill with yogurt.
Let set 4 hours or until starts to thicken.
Remove from thermos.
Put in cups and store in refrigerator.
Makes approximately 4 cups.

title: sugar free cake
directions: Cook together raisins and water until there is no water left. Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350°.

title: potato donuts
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs, sugar and shortening. Combine dry ingredients. Gradually add to egg mixture alternately with mashed potatoes.
Dough should be smooth.
Chill at least 2 hours. Divide dough in half.
Roll out to 1/2-inch thickness. Cut with doughnut cutter.
Heat oil to 375° in deep fat fryer. Drop in doughnuts. Turn as they float to top and fry to a golden brown. May roll in sugar and cinnamon or powdered sugar.

title: easy stuffed eggs
directions: Carefully remove cooked yolks and mash in bowl.
Add all ingredients, mix well and carefully replace mixture into egg whites.

title: spinach rolls
directions: Defrost and drain spinach.
Pat dry.
Mix ingredients together except tortillas.
Spread evenly on tortillas, roll up.
Cover and let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Cut into 1-inch slices to serve.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: In medium mixing bowl, blend ground beef, egg, cornstarch, onion, salt and pepper.
Shape 1 tablespoon mixture around each pineapple chunk.
Reserve remaining pineapple.
In a glass pie plate, arrange meatballs evenly around edge.
Cook 5 to 7 minutes, stirring to rearrange meatballs halfway through cooking time.

title: dump cake
directions: "Dump" into 9 x 13-inch pan the above in the order listed. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: kisses(servings: 60)
directions: Cream butter and sugar, beating well.
Add vanilla and flour; mix well.
Chill dough for 1 hour.

title: peach cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: curried cauliflower and pasta
directions: In saucepan, cook fresh cauliflower, covered, in boiling water just until crisp-tender.
(Or cook the frozen cauliflower according to package directions.)
Drain.
In another saucepan combine soup, milk, onion, parsley, curry and paprika.
Bring mixture to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Stir in cream cheese; cook and stir until cheese melts.
Remove from heat; stir in cauliflower.
Serve over the hot cooked pasta.
Sprinkle with almonds and additional parsley, if desired.
Makes 6 side dish servings.

title: succotash
directions: In a medium saucepan over medium heat, melt butter.
Add corn, lima beans, salt and pepper. Stir to combine. Add cream and simmer gently, uncovered, for about 5 minutes. Stir in parsley and serve. Makes 6 servings.

title: brunch quizza(a quiche pizza combination)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Crumble sausage in medium skillet; cook until brown, stirring occasionally.
Drain well.
Line bottom of buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish with crescent rolls, firmly pressing perforations to seal.
Sprinkle with sausage and Mozzarella cheese.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Chop onion in skillet with butter.
After onion is tender, add package of broccoli and cook until thawed.
Add soup and Cheez Whiz.
Pour into casserole dish over rice and mix well.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Remove and top with fried onions.
Bake for 5 more minutes.

title: potatoes ala ruth
directions: Cover sheet cake pan with foil (enough to wrap potatoes when you
cook
them).
Slice
potatoes
thin
and
layer with sliced onion,
seasoning
and margarine.
top with margarine. Bake at 450` for 45 minutes to 1 hour, covered with foil.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spray 9 x 13 inch pan with cooking spray.
Spread pecans and coconut on bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix according to package. Pour on top of pecans with coconut.
Mix margarine, cream cheese, vanilla and powdered sugar.
Drop by spoonful on top of unbaked cake batter.
Bake 45 minutes to one hour until done in oven of 350°.
Cake will crack.

title: eggnog french toast
directions: Beat eggs lightly.
Add eggnog, rum extract, melted butter. Turn into shallow bowl or pie plate.
Dip bread slices in eggnog mixture, turn until well coated.
Arrange on buttered baking sheet or broiler pan.
Brown under broiler, about 5 minutes, turning once.
Serve hot.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sweet and sour chicken wings
directions: Cut off tips of wings.
Discard.
Place in pan.
Mix dressing with all other ingredients.
Mix well and pour over wings.
Bake at 350°, turning every 30 minutes to brown evenly.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Can be frozen and reheated.
Does equally well with chicken breasts.

title: beef crescent pie
directions: Brown hamburger and drain off fat.
Add onions if desired. Add tomato sauce and green beans.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Set oven to 350°.
Use a 13 x 9-inch pan and press out biscuit dough on the bottom of the buttered pan.
Add 1/2 cup of grated cheese on top of dough.
Add meat mixture on top.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake for about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: potato puffs
directions: Cook potatoes in barely enough water to cover.
When done, put through a potato ricer.
Put water and shortening on stove.
Bring to rapid boil and add flour all at once, stirring rapidly until mixture leaves sides of pan and forms a mass or ball.
Cool.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add salt, pepper, nutmeg and potatoes.
Drop by tablespoon in hot Crisco and cook until light brown.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Add Manwich mix.
Add rice and stuff green peppers with rice-beef mixture.
Top with cheese of choice.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: jelly roll
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease bottom and sides of jelly roll pan. Line bottom with greased brown paper or foil.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat eggs in small mixer bowl until very thick and lemon colored.
Pour beaten eggs into large bowl.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Blend in on low speed water and vanilla.
Mix in dry ingredients until batter is smooth.
Pour into pan.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Turn onto cloth sprinkled with 10x sugar.
Roll up quickly.
Cool, unroll, spread with jelly, then roll up again.

title: giant nacho
directions: Layer, in a 9 x 13-inch pan, refried beans, hamburger, mild picante sauce, black olives, green onions and grated Cheddar and Monterey Jack cheeses.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.
Top with guacamola or sour cream.
Serve with plain Doritos chips or tostado chips.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a rapid boil.
Sift together sugar and flour in a large bowl.
Pour boiling mixture over sugar/flour mixture.
Mix together buttermilk, eggs, soda and vanilla and add to mixture.
Pour batter into a floured and greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for about 35 minutes, until a toothpick comes out clean.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pastry as directed.
Form in one large ball.
Roll pastry to 18 x 12-inch rectangle.
Cut into 6-inch squares.
Place apples on pastry squares.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except eggs.
Add one egg at a time and beat, then add food coloring.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cat cookies
directions: Place cookie dough in freezer for at least 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Slice cookie dough into 1/4-inch slices.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet 3 inches apart.

title: easy rhubarb shortcake
directions: Mix
sugar and cream together;
add soda; stir in flour and rhubarb.
Spread
in
a
greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake
at
350° for about 25 minutes.
Serve warm with cream, if you'd like.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine oil and sugar; mix well.
Sift together remaining
dry ingredients.
Sift half of dry ingredients into sugar and oil mixture and blend.
Sift in remaining dry ingredients, alternating with
eggs
one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Add carrots;
mix well.
Then mix in pecans.
Pour into tube
pan or oblong pan.
Bake in slow oven at 355° about 1 hour.

title: crabmeat mardi gras
directions: Boil egg noodles until they are al dente.
Coat them with 1 pat of margarine so they don't stick together.
Set them aside. Melt down 1/2 stick of margarine; toss in crabmeat and stir-fry about 4 minutes.
Then spoon in cream of mushroom soup, stirring constantly until soup is smooth and crabmeat is mixed thoroughly.

title: harry's hot vegetable soup
directions: Put vegetables in 5-quart pot or crock-pot.
Add tomatoes, salt and crushed red peppers.
Bring to boil on medium to high heat for about 1 hour and 45 minutes.
If using a crock-pot, put on high heat for 3 or 4 hours.
Stir often.

title: scripture cake
directions: To find the ingredients, look in your Bible for the chapter and verse indicated.

title: crock-pot chicken wings
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Cut off and discard wing tips. Cut each wing at joint to make two sections.
Sprinkle wings with salt and pepper and place on broiler pan.
Broil 4 to 5-inches away from the heat for 20 minutes, turning once during the middle of broiling.
Transfer wings to the crock-pot slow cooker.

title: country style pot roast with gravy
directions: Brown roast in hot oil.
Add onion soup mix and 2 cups water. Bring to a boil.
Cook 2 hours.
Add veggies, cover and cook 30 minutes.
Combine flour and 1/2 cup water.
Add to drippings and stir constantly.

title: quick cinnamon rolls
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam, turn sideways.
Dip biscuits in butter, then cover with cinnamon-sugar mixture.
In a pan this size, we put 5 rows of 6.
Overlap biscuits by standing them partly on end.
Drizzle fruit juice over all and bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Immediately invert onto serving plate.

title: vegetable dill dip
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Store in refrigerator for approximately 1 hour before serving.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Set aside 1 cup dry cake mix for topping.
Mix remaining dry cake mix with melted margarine and 1 egg.
Press in bottom of well-greased 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: hot sausage pasta
directions: Heat olive oil and red pepper flakes in a large skillet.
Add sausage and brown for 10 minutes.
Drain well, then return to skillet.
Brown onion and garlic with sausage for 7 minutes.
Drain and dice tomatoes; add to skillet and cook another 10 minutes.
Add heavy cream.
Simmer until mixed well and serve over bow ties.

title: sourdough starter
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup very warm water. Stir well. Add 2 cups lukewarm water, sugar and salt. Stir in flour and mix well. Put mixture into a jar. Cover with cloth and leave at room temperature 2 or 3 days, until mixture ferments. When it foams and bubbles, it's ready for use. Can be used at once or stored in the fridge. If stored in fridge, remove 24 hours before using.

title: cornflake cookies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients over low heat.
Let boil for 3 minutes.
Stir in cornflakes.
Spoon onto greased waxed paper. Makes 20.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix margarine, oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Sift all dry ingredients.
Drop from teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: french toast batter
directions: Whip eggs until smooth.
Add cream; stir slowly and add cinnamon, sugar and vanilla.
Dip French bread slices.
Fry at 350° until brown on both sides.

title: lemon curd
directions: Cream the sugar and butter together, then beat and add beaten egg yolks, lemon juice and rind.
Cook slowly in double boiler until mixture gets thick.
Delicious used as a spread on bread or a filling for tarts or sponge cake.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix together all except cheese.
Grease pan and heat very hot. Put in 1/2 the mixture.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of cheese.
Add rest of mixture.
Cover with cheese.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown ground beef with taco seasoning.
Drain.
Place ground beef in greased 10-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Mix Bisquick with milk and eggs, beat well.
Pour this mixture over meat mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve with lettuce, tomato, onion and sour cream. For added crunch add taco chips.

title: brunch egg strata
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Spread cubed bread crumbs on bottom.
Sprinkle bacon and broccoli on bread.
Top with cheese. Beat together eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over all.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: fiesta cake
directions: Mix and sift flour, sugar, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Stir in pecans.
Beat eggs slightly.
Combine with oil, vanilla, bananas and pineapple.
Add to dry ingredients and mix thoroughly, but do not beat.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and let stand 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool.

title: tater-tot casserole
directions: Crumble raw hamburger on bottom of casserole dish.
Salt and pepper to taste and cover with dried onion soup mix.
Spread frozen Tater-tots over this.
Cover with soup which has been diluted with milk.
Bake in 350 degree oven for 45 minutes.

title: zesty sauced haddock
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 10 x 6-inch baking dish. Cut haddock into 3 servings; sprinkle each on both sides with salt; place in single layer in baking dish.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, about 25 minutes. Cut into squares.
Serve warm.

title: e-z pineapple cookie bars
directions: Spread pineapple (not drained) in bottom of 9 x 13 pan.
On top, sprinkle evenly the coconut.
Add cake mix and spread evenly also.
Pat down.
Add butter (that has been shredded) on top and spread evenly.
