Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Cool thoroughly and cut into bars.

title: flan
directions: Pour sugar into a 10-inch heavy or cast-iron skillet; place over medium heat, stirring constantly with a wooden spoon until sugar melts and becomes light golden brown.
Pour syrup into a 9-inch round cake pan.
Set aside.

title: 24 hour slaw
directions: When mixture starts to boil remove from heat. Mix with cabbage, onions and green pepper. Mix well and refrigerate 4 hours.

title: cornmeal muffins
directions: In large bowl, combine the cornmeal, flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
In another bowl, mix together the buttermilk, melted butter and egg.
Pour liquid ingredients over dry ingredients; carefully stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Pour into 8 large greased cups or 12 small muffin pans.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes, or until golden.
Remove from pans.
Serve hot.

title: mayonnaise rolls
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes until brown.
Makes about 9 rolls.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Mix soups and the can of water.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add rice and stir to distribute.
Dip each piece of chicken in melted butter.
Place chicken on rice.
Pour remaining butter over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: hot cajun pickles
directions: Drain pickles in colander for at least 45 minutes.
Press out juice.
In large bowl mix sugar, garlic flakes and Tabasco sauce. In wide mouth gallon jar, tightly pack alternate layers of pickles and sugar mixture.
Fasten lid securely and set aside on counter. Every 24 hours for 5 days, turn jar upside down.
Divide pickles into sterilized pint jars and seal.
Chill before serving.

title: peach bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg, beating lightly.
Add milk alternately with the flour, baking powder, salt and spices that have been mixed together.
Beat well after each addition.
Stir in pecans.
Flour peaches with 1/4 cup flour, tossing to coat.
Carefully stir into the dough.
Pour batter into 2 loaf pans that have been buttered and floured.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until they test done.

title: orange fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together with spoon. Put in casserole dish and refrigerate.

title: spinach dip #2
directions: Thaw and squeeze liquid out of spinach until dry. Stir all ingredients together and blend well. Cover and refrigerate 2 hrs. Serve with bread or crackers.

title: butterfly salad
directions: Heat pineapple, pour in jello-set to cool. Put in cottage cheese, pecans and cherries whip cream and get stiff.
Fold in put in 6 cup mold. Refrigerate.

title: shrimp in cheese sauce
directions: Saute celery, bell pepper and green onions in oleo.
Melt Velveeta over low heat.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Stir in sauteed vegetables, shrimp and mushrooms.
Serve over rice.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Sift flour, baking powder, sugar and salt. Combine egg, milk and oil; pour into flour mixture and stir enough to moisten flour.
Fold in blueberries.
Fill muffin cups with batter.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes about 12 muffins.

title: quick party dip
directions: Heat together in pan.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: ginger and onion chicken
directions: Combine salt, ajinomoto and pepper.
Season chicken.
Dust with flour.
Heat oil.
Fry four or five pieces of chicken at a time until brown.
Remove chicken to a casserole.
Set aside. Saute ginger and spring onion.
Stir in soy sauce, sugar and 2 teaspoons cornstarch dispersed in water.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over chicken.
Add 1 cup water.
Cover tightly and simmer for 15 minutes or until chicken is done.
Serve with hot rice.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Crumble a layer of cookies on bottom of large, plastic container.
Mix cream cheese and sugar together; beat well. Spread over cookie crumbs.

title: chocolate eclair dessert
directions: Layer whole graham crackers on bottom of rectangle pan.
Mix Cool Whip and vanilla pudding together, then smooth over graham crackers.
Place another layer of graham crackers on pudding. Spread chocolate frosting on top, then chill in refrigerator (this allows graham crackers to soften).
Cut and serve.

title: pecan bars
directions: Combine flour and 1/3 cup brown sugar.
Cut in 3/4 cup of butter with pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal. Press mixture evenly into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 17 minutes.

title: oven baked sausage casserole
directions: In a skillet, crumble and cook until browned.
Drain.
Place in a greased 1 1/2 quart casserole.
In same skillet, saute the vegetables.
Drain and layer over sausage.
Top with cheese.
Beat together eggs, milk, garlic, salt and white pepper until frothy. Pour over cheese.
Bake at 350 for 35 minutes or until set.

title: banana bread
directions: Grease pans.
Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add bananas and eggs.
Add nuts.
Combine dry ingredients, sift and add to mixture.
Pour into pans and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: ohio state buckeyes
directions: Mix together peanut butter, butter and confectioners sugar.
Form into small balls. Using a toothpick, dip balls into chocolate until almost covered, leaving some of the peanut butter mixture exposed on top.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Parboil zucchini and onions in salt water for 5 minutes. Combine zucchini and onions with soup, sour cream and carrots. Then combine stuffing and butter together.
Cover bottom of 12 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish with one half of stuffing, then add zucchini mix and top with remaining stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: nell's pork chops
directions: Season, flour and brown pork chops in oil on each side.
Place in foil-lined pan, add Coca-Cola and seal foil tightly.
Bake at 250° for 3 to 4 hours.

title: meatballs deluxe
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients; form into meatballs.
Cover with the tomato juice, green pepper, onion, carrot and celery.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peas and potatoes
directions: Pull strings from peas.
Break in half.
Cook over medium heat until almost done, about 3/4 of an hour.
Scrub new potatoes with a brush or rough dish cloth.
Rinse and put on top of peas.
Cook until tender, about 20 minutes longer.

title: strawberry delight cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box in a 12 x 9-inch pan. While cake is still warm, top with thawed strawberries, pushing them down into the cake.
Let cool in the refrigerator, then add Cool Whip on top of strawberries, covering them completely. Sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: chili burger supper
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package direction.
Drain well. Brown ground beef in skillet.
Mix all ingredients except cheese in a casserole.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle top with cheese; place under broiler until cheese melts.

title: crabmeat spread
directions: Blend softened cream cheese with seasoned salt, onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Spread in a shallow serving dish.
Cover with chili sauce, then crabmeat.
Put fresh parsley on top.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 12 hours.
Serve with crackers.

title: corn bread
directions: Combine cornmeal, egg, buttermilk and mayonnaise to create batter. Put bacon grease into cold iron skillet and place in oven while oven is preheating to 450°. Remove skillet and pour half the hot bacon grease into the corn bread batter and stir. Pour batter into hot skillet and bake for 20 minutes.

title: zucchini scramble
directions: Peel one large zucchini; remove seeds and grate.
Add one grated carrots.
Mix equal parts of sugar, vinegar and milk according to amount of vegetable mixture.
Add 1/2 teaspoon celery seed according to amount of sauce.
This makes a delicious creamy sauce.

title: butterscotch cream cheese bars
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels and margarine in a saucepan.
Add nuts and cracker crumbs.
Put 1/2 mixture in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
In a large mixing bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Add milk, egg and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour over crumbs.
Top with remaining crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool; then refrigerate.

title: tomato dip
directions: Combine all; let marinate overnight.
Serve with corn chips.

title: taco salad
directions: Make sure ground beef is cold, then mix all other ingredients at once.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Spread dried beef all over bottom of 9 x 13 pan.
Cut chicken into pieces and place on top of dried beef.
Mix in a bowl, cream of chicken soup and cream of mushroom soup and sour cream.
Pour mixture into pan.
Bake in oven for approximately 1 to 1 1/2 hours until chicken is done at 400°.
When done, spoon rice into mixture and let sit for 15 minutes.

title: quick as a wink hot dish
directions: Place the sliced raw potatoes in bottom of casserole (as many as your family eats).
Crumble the raw hamburger over them.
Add the soup (undiluted); cover with foil.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Take foil off the last half hour.

title: sour cream muffins
directions: Add flour and sour cream to melted oleo.
Mix.
Pour in greased muffin tins.
Bake at 375° until golden brown, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Very easy and delicious!

title: texas hash
directions: Brown ground beef, onions and green pepper.
Pour off fat, then add salt, pepper, chili powder, rice, tomatoes, okra and water. Cook, covered, over low heat for approximately 30 to 45 minutes, until rice is done and liquid is absorbed.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Take out of water and debone. Cook rice in chicken broth.
Add chicken and the can of cream of chicken and cream of mushroom soup, a stick of butter.
Cover and let sit for about 20 minutes.

title: crab dip
directions: Blend together cream cheese, milk, crab meat, onion and horseradish.
Add salt and pepper.
Put in shallow baking dish and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: frozen salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and Miracle Whip.
Add pineapple and cherries.
Whip cream and add to first mixture.
Fold in marshmallows and freeze.

title: pasties
directions: Place pie crust in pie pan.
Mix meat, potatoes, onion, pepper and parsley.
Place mixture on one side of pie crust, then place pat of butter and 1 tablespoon water.
Fold pie crust over and pinch sides together.
Put 3 vent holes with knife on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
(Amount of crust depends on amount of pasties. You will have 2 pasties per pie pan.)

title: five flavor cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs which have been beaten until lemon colored.
Combine flour and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture.
Alternate with milk.
Stir in flavorings.
Spoon mixture into prepared 10-inch tube pan and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Let cool about 15 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients; add chocolate chips.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour.
Serves 12 to 20.

title: turkey loaf
directions: Combine celery, onions, mushrooms, shallots, parsley and poultry seasoning.
Saute in bouillon for 5 minutes.
Combine with the remaining ingredients and shape into a loaf.
Place in a 1 1/2-quart loaf pan coated with nonstick cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours or until done.

title: old fashioned potato salad
directions: Place potatoes in a Dutch oven.
Cover with water and bring to a boil.
Cook 8 minutes or until tender.
Drain.
Place in a large bowl.
Add onion and next 4 ingredients.
Toss gently.

title: sweet potato pone
directions: Peel and grate raw sweet potatoes.
Mix remaining ingredients. Pour into greased baking dish.
Dot with butter.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: toffee bars
directions: Thoroughly cream the butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour and mix well. Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Press mixture into 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Cut while warm into bars. Cool before removing from pan.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: oven roasted sweet potato fries
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Line cookie sheet with foil.
Brush foil with 1 teaspoon oil.
Cut potatoes lengthwise into 1/2 thick wedges.
Transfer to bowl.
Add remaining oil, salt and pepper; toss.
Spread potatoes in single layer on cookie sheet.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until crisp.

title: rhubarb and pineapple jam
directions: String and break up beans; pack in quart jars.
Add one tsp of salt per jar.
Cook for 3 to 3 1/2 hours or pressure cook 20 minutes at 15 pound pressure in pressure cooker.

title: turkey a l'orange
directions: Place tenders on broiler pan.
Broil 5-inches from heat just until cooked through, about 8 to 10 minutes, turning once.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Take rolls out of the package and lay into the cookie sheet. Press the seams together.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until light brown.
Cool.
Mix remaining ingredients and beat until smooth.
Spread on cooled crust.
Cut up and put on any vegetables you want.

title: mexican pinto bean soup
directions: Brown hamburger; drain fat.
Chop onions and green pepper. Add all ingredients together; bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Pretty spicy.
Goes great at a cookout.
Makes 8 cups.

title: sad cake
directions: Melt brown sugar, margarine and white sugar.
Stir ingredients just until mixed.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: french steak
directions: Mix ground chuck, eggs, cracker crumbs, 1 onion, Worcestershire sauce and salt together and roll in flour.
Make patties.
Put into ungreased skillet.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Mix ground beef, onion, rice and eggs; roll into balls.
In a large pot, mix the tomato soup and sauce with 3 cups of water. Put some of the hamburger balls in the 3 green peppers.
Put peppers and hamburger balls in the tomato soup and sauce.
Stir and cook over medium heat for 1 hour.
Stir occasionally.
Turn heat on low and cook until done, about another 1 hour.

title: st. augustine orange and pineapple pie
directions: Beat egg yolks in saucepan; mix sugar, cornstarch and flour. Add to egg yolks and beat until smooth.
Place over medium heat and add orange juice, lemon juice and pineapple.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
I cook mine in microwave in 4-cup Pyrex measuring cup, about 9 minutes, 2 minutes at a time, on High.
Cool and spoon into pie crust.
Put in refrigerator until filling is cold, then put meringue, 3 egg whites and 6 tablespoons sugar on top and bake until golden brown.

title: chicken or turkey, ham bake
directions: Saute onions and mushrooms. Blend in flour, salt, pepper, milk and sherry. Cook until thick. Add turkey, ham and water chestnuts. Pour into casserole dish and top with cheese.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 400°.
Serves 4.
Good to use up leftovers.

title: ham loaf
directions: Add eggs, milk and bread crumbs to purchased ham loaf. Mix all together and brown. Remove loaf and add brown sugar, water, vinegar and mustard. Boil for 5 minutes. Put loaf in a casserole dish and pour syrup over the top. Bake as you would a meat loaf.

title: congo squares
directions: Mix eggs and butter.
Add sugar and flour, then pecans.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: barbecued beans
directions: Mix together well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, but use only 1/2 of oleo.
Pour into greased 2-quart dish or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with 1/2 oleo and 2 cups crushed corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: applesauce drop doughnuts
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and cinnamon together. Beat eggs and milk.
Add applesauce and oil.
Add to dry ingredients; mix well.
Drop batter by teaspoon into 375° fat. Fry until golden brown on both sides.
These will turn over by themselves.
If not, turn them over.

title: quick hot muffins
directions: Add ingredients one at a time; mix until moist.
Grease a muffin pan.
Drop into muffin pan.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: pickled beets
directions: Mix well and chill before serving.

title: lucy's oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together butter, sugar and brown sugar in a large mixing bowl.
In a separate bowl, sift together flour, salt, baking powder and soda.
Add flour mixture, one cup at a time, into the creamed mixture and blend well.
Next, beat and add eggs and vanilla to the dough and blend well.
Next, add pecans and blend well.
Then add oatmeal and coconut, one cup at a time, blending well after each cup.
Drop dough by teaspoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: In a large pot, put chicken, onion, celery and carrot.
Cover with water and bring to boil.
Simmer until chicken is cooked. Take chicken out and cut into small pieces.
Set aside.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Yields one 9-inch pie.

title: italian orange roughy(low-fat)
directions: Marinate fish in a glass dish in lemon juice about 45 minutes, turning at least once.
Drain lemon juice off fish.
Place fish in glass baking dish.
Mix tomatoes, seasoning, garlic and Butter Buds.
Pour over fish.
Sprinkle dill on top.
Bake, covered, about 20 minutes at 350°.
Remove cover and bake another 10 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Mix together and freeze.
Do not add ginger ale until ready to serve.

title: jackie's cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together with mixer. Shape into a ball. Roll ball in chopped pecans.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° until thick.

title: turkey jarlsberg
directions: Mix ingredients together.
May use prepared creamy dressing or 1/2 cup mayonnaise, plus 3 tablespoons sour cream.

title: sausage rolls
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Roll dough out very thin. Spread sausage evenly on dough.
Roll up as for jelly roll.
Cut in slices.
Bake in 425° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: yum yum salad
directions: Mix Jell-O, hot water and cold water.
Add pineapple, bananas and marshmallows.
Let chill.

title: vegetarian pot of chili
directions: Put all ingredients in a pot.
Simmer for 15 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour into buttered casserole and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crustless vegetable quiche(serves 4)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute celery and onion in a nonstick pan, sprayed with "Pam."
Spray a 9-inch pie pan or quiche pan with Pam.
Arrange celery, onion and vegetables in pie pan.
In a medium bowl, beat the eggs, yogurt, milk and 3 ounces of the Swiss cheese and the salt and pepper.
Pour into pie plate.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake for 35 minutes until a knife, inserted in center, comes out clean.
Approximately 270 calories per serving.

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine milk, sugar, biscuit mix, eggs, butter and vanilla in electric blender container. Cover and blend at low speed for 3 minutes. Pour into a greased 9-inch pie pan. Let stand about 5 minutes, then sprinkle with coconut. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Serve warm or cool. Store any leftovers in refrigerator.

title: blackberry jam cake
directions: Cream together oleo and brown sugar.
Beat in eggs and buttermilk.
Sift together the listed ingredients.
Beat with creamed mixture.
Fold in nuts if desired and blackberry jam. Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan or 2 round pans.

title: creamy tacos
directions: Brown hamburger; add Ro-Tel, cheese, cream and beans.
Cook on low for 30 minutes.
Serve over cheese flavored Doritos and top with lettuce, tomatoes and onion.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Heat broiler.
Mix dressing, juice and seasoning mix.
Place chicken on rack of broiler pan.
Brush with 1/2 of the dressing mixture.
Broil 5 to 7 inches from heat for 8 to 10 minutes. Turn.
Brush with remaining dressing mixture.
Continue to broil 8 to 10 minutes or until tender.

title: apricot balls
directions: Roll mixture into one-inch balls, then roll in 10x sugar. Cover and refrigerate.

title: rena's mincemeat bread
directions: Mix white sugar, spices, soda and salt.
Add eggs, water and oil.
Mix together brown sugar and pumpkin.
Add to other ingredients.
Blend at low speed until mixed then on medium for 3 minutes.
Add mincemeat and nuts.
Spray inside of wide mouth pint jars with Pam and fill 1/2 full.
Do not put on lids.
Place jars in 325° oven for 45 minutes.
When done, seal immediately.
Makes 10 jars of bread.
This may also be baked in loaf pans for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: western snapper
directions: Cut fish into serving size pieces.
On a plate, combine oregano, chili powder, cayenne, flour, corn meal and salt.
On another plate, combine melted butter and lemon juice.
Dip fish into butter mixture first, then press into corn meal mixture. Place on a lightly buttered, shallow dish.
Pour any remaining butter over fillets.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes until fish flakes when pressed with finger.
Makes 4 servings.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a large mixing bowl cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Gradually add milk and vanilla wafers to creamed mixture.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: mincemeat(to can)
directions: Boil any roast beef, or neck meat will do, until tender.
Then grind.
Put all in large container.
Mix.
Put into jars and cold pack 30 minutes.

title: english oatmeal tea bars
directions: In saucepan, combine corn syrup, butter, brown sugar and vanilla over low heat until melted.
Stir in oats (and nuts, optional).
Mix well.
Press mixture into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan and bake in a preheated 300° oven for 10 minutes.
Stir mixture well, then press firmly back into pan.
Bake 10 minutes longer.
Do not overbake.
Cookies should be chewy.
Cut into 1 1/2 x 2-inch bars while still warm.
Cool completely in pan. These are also good frosted with melted semi-sweet chocolate.

title: sausage balls
directions: Grate cheese real small.
Mix sausage with cheese and the Bisquick.
Shape in very small balls and until lightly browned.

title: apricot bars
directions: Cream Crisco, sugar, milk, vanilla and salt until fluffy.
Add flour and oats and mix well.
Set aside 1 cup mixture for topping. Pack remaining in ungreased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Spread cooked and sweetened apricots or prunes in pan and sprinkle with the cup of reserved topping.
Bake in a 325° oven for 25 minutes and enjoy.

title: taco salad deluxe
directions: Mix all ingredients when ready to eat.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Pour soup into saucepan; add mushrooms and simmer until heated through.
Add cheeses, stirring until melted.
Place asparagus in casserole dish; cover with soup mixture.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350 until bubbly.

title: russian tea cookies
directions: Thoroughly mix butter, sugar and vanilla with electric mixer. Gradually add sifted flour and salt.
Mix in nuts.
Chill dough several hours or overnight.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls and place about 2 inches apart on ungreased baking pan.
Bake until set but not too brown at 400°
for 10 to 12 minutes.
While warm, roll cookies in confectioners sugar; allow to cool and after cooled, roll again in confectioners sugar.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: reduced-calorie lemon-garlic chicken
directions: In a nonstick skillet, saute first 2 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients; cook, covered, for 15 minutes or until done.

title: banana pancakes
directions: Blend together the flour, milk and salt.
Leave to stand for 15 minutes before using.
Mash the bananas, then add the egg and the sugar.
Blend until you have a smooth paste.
Mix together the banana mixture and batter; beat thoroughly, until all ingredients are blended.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli; drain and arrange in large greased baking dish. Place sliced, cooked chicken on top.
Combine mayo, soups, lemon juice, curry and mushrooms.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese, Cool Whip, drained pineapple and pudding. Refrigerate.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Place hash browns in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix all ingredients, except cornflakes, in saucepan to melt.
Then pour over potatoes.
Top with 2 cups crushed cornflakes.
Melt another 1/2 stick margarine and pour over crushed cornflakes.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix together macaroni, cheese, pickles and boiled eggs.
Add salad dressing, salt, pepper, garlic powder, basil and dill.

title: fresh apple crunch cake
directions: Sift together
flour,
salt, nutmeg, cinnamon and soda. Mix oil, eggs and sugar together; beat well.
Add dry ingredients to oil
mixture
and mix well.
Add apples, nuts, vanilla and brandy. Mix
again.
Batter
will
be
very
stiff,
like cookie dough. Spread
into
lightly
greased
13 x 5 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Meanwhile in large bowl, beat eggs, corn syrup, butter and vanilla until well blended.
Stir in pecans.
Immediately pour over hot crust; spread evenly.
Bake 25 minutes or until filling is firm around edges and slightly firm in center.
Cut into squares.
Makes 48 bars.

title: crispy crusted baked chicken
directions: Wash chicken, pat dry and set aside.
Beat egg and milk in bowl.
In another bowl, mix potato flakes, garlic salt and Parmesan cheese.
Roll chicken in egg mix, then potato flake mixture.
Melt butter in shallow baking pan.
Roll coated chicken in the butter and place them skin side up in the pan.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: pumpkin chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and beat well.
Add dry ingredients, chocolate chips and walnuts.
Mix thoroughly.
Drop by rounded tablespoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pear honey
directions: Peel, core and chop pears with food chopper.
Add crushed pineapple and sugar.
Gradually bring to a boil and cook until thick (about 25 to 30 minutes).
Stir frequently to prevent burning.
Place in jars and seal.
Delicious on toast or between homemade biscuits.

title: cheese blintz bubble ring
directions: Place cheese and 1/2 to 1 teaspoon cinnamon-sugar mixture on each biscuit.
Pull dough up around cheese ball and pinch to seal. Pour melted butter in Bundt pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 of the nuts and 1/2 remaining sugar on butter.
Place 1/2 rolls on mixture, seam-side up.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes until lightly browned.
Cool 5 minutes in pan.
Invert on serving platter.

title: taco salad
directions: This can also be made with 1 pound ground beef, cooked and browned.

title: sweet and sour carrots
directions: Cook the carrots in a small amount of lightly salted water for 15 to 20 minutes or until fork tender.
Add peppers and continue cooking for 3 minutes, covered. Add enough water to the pineapple juice to make 1/3 cup.
In a medium saucepan combine the pineapple juice, sugar, cornstarch, salt, vinegar and soy sauce. Heat just until bubbly, stirring constantly.
Add carrots, peppers, and pineapple.
Serve warm.

title: egg nog
directions: Beat eggs well, using a large mixing bowl; add cream and milk or half and half.
Then slowly add ice cream until well mixed. Pour into punch bowl and add nutmeg, if you wish.

title: peppy's potato salad
directions: In bowl, combine sugar and turmeric; add eggs and vinegar. In large skillet, melt butter.
Let cool to room temperature.
Add egg mixture and cook on low heat until thick, stirring constantly. Add mayonnaise, mustard and salad dressing.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix with dressing.
Chill and serve.

title: french bread french toast with peach puree
directions: In a food processor, coarsely chop the peaches.
Add the jam; process briefly to blend.
Set aside.
Slice the bread on the diagonal into 1/2-inch slices.
In a shallow dish, beat the eggs, milk and vanilla together.
Soak the bread, a few slices at a time, in the egg mixture.
Be sure the bread is thoroughly soaked. In a large skillet (preferably nonstick), warm 1 teaspoon of butter in 1 tablespoon of the oil over medium high heat until the butter is melted.
Add 4 slices of bread; cook until golden on both sides.
Repeat for the remaining bread, using the remaining butter and oil, plus more if needed.
Dust the toast with confectioners sugar; serve with the peach sauce.
If desired, the peach sauce can be briefly warmed before serving.

title: broccoli corn medley
directions: Cook over medium heat with 1/2 cup water to desired tenderness.
A bit more salt or sugar may be added to taste.

title: melina's southwest skillet supperserves 4
directions: Saute onion and garlic in margarine.
Add remaining ingredients and cook over medium-high heat, stirring frequently until vegetables are crisp-tender and most liquid has evaporated, about 3-4 minutes.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Pour sugar, vinegar, salad oil and salt (mixed) over drained peas, beans, celery, pimentos, onion and pepper.
Cover; refrigerate overnight.
Keeps indefinitely.

title: * yum yum *
directions: Saute ground beef in 1/3 cube oleo; add mushroom soup and salt.
Saute celery and onions in 1/3 cup oleo.
Combine the 2 mixtures and put in casserole.
Cover with Chinese noodles.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: grandma boney's bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and onions in paper thin rounds. Place in stone crock. Mix salt and ice. Pack around cucumbers; cover crock with weighted lid. Allow to stand 3 hours, then drain. Combine sugar, spices and vinegar. Pour over vegetables in large enamel or aluminum kettle. Bring to boil over low heat. Pour in hot sterilized jars. Seal and process in water bath canner for 10 minutes.

title: pecan tarts
directions: In a mixing bowl,
beat cream cheese and butter.
Blend in the flour and salt. Chill
for one hour.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Press into bottom and sides of mini-muffin cups.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Can be put in blender or mashed with fork.
Chopped tomatoes, chilies and hot sauce may be added to taste.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: kugli(lithuanian potato)
directions: Fry bacon, drain and set aside.
Beat eggs.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Add bacon.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan (well-greased).
Put bacon slices on top.
Bake 1 1/2 hours or until brown and set at 350°.

title: scalloped winter vegetables
directions: Cook potatoes, rutabaga and carrots in chicken stock to which has been added the minced garlic, thyme and pepper.
When barely tender, remove from heat.
Melt butter in skillet; stir in flour and cook briefly.
Drain the stock from cooked vegetables, and gradually add stock to butter flour mixture.
Stir and cook until thickened.
Combine with the precooked vegetables and pour into a baking dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: barbecue clams
directions: Shuck clams; loosen from shells.
Leave clams on larger half-shells.
Place in 1 1/2 to 2 inch deep baking pan.
Place about 1/4 teaspoon ketchup on each clam.
Add 1/2 inch slice cheese; top with 1/2 inch slice bacon.
Broil for about 5 minutes or until bacon is crisp.

title: italian sauce
directions: Pour meatball drippings into saucepan; should be 1 1/4 cups. If not, add oil.
Brown minced garlic clove in drippings.
Add tomato puree and equal amount of water.
When sauce comes to a boil, add sugar and seasonings.
Cover pot, reduce heat and simmer 2 or 3 hours until thick.
Stir frequently.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Drain pineapple and combine with other ingredients.
Pour the Dressing over salad and chill 24 hours.

title: chocolate cookie with surprise center
directions: Blend dry ingredients.
Cream white sugar, brown sugar and butter; add vanilla.
Add eggs.
Add dry ingredients to wet ingredients.
Wrap dough around Rolo candy.
Roll in chopped nuts and sugar.
Bake 1-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 7 to 10 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Add milk and mix.
Add vanilla flavoring.
Melt butter in pan.
Pour batter on butter. Add peaches.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar over it.
Bake at 350° until done.
(Batter will bake up through peaches to top while cooking.)

title: "hot to trot" dip
directions: Brown ground beef and drain. In a saucepan, heat cheese and salsa until cheese is melted. Add Tabasco. Combine meat and cheese mixture. Serve hot with tortilla chips.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine sugar, cornmeal, flour and salt.
In large bowl, beat eggs until light, then beat in sugar mixture.
Add the buttermilk, butter, lemon peel and juice, then vanilla.
Stir until combined.
Pour into pie shell and bake 35 to 40 minutes until golden brown and set but not puffed.
Let cool to room temperature.
You may serve with a dollop of whipped cream.

title: beefy nachos
directions: In large skillet over medium-high heat, brown beef and onion. Drain.
Stir in steak sauce.
Arrange tortilla chips on large heatproof platter.
Spoon beef mixture over chips; sprinkle with cheese.
Broil 6-inches from heat source for 3 to 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Top with sour cream, chiles, tomatoes and ripe olives, if desired.
Serve immediately.
Makes 6 servings.

title: lemon-baked chicken
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Remove skin from chicken breasts; split or cut in large strips.
Place chicken in ungreased baking pan, 9 x 9 x 2-inch.
Spread 1 teaspoon soft butter or margarine on each chicken piece.
Sprinkle pieces with 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon paprika.
Drizzle with lemon juice.
Bake, uncovered, 35 to 45 minutes or until tender.

title: pumpkin dip
directions: Beat all ingredients until smooth.
Store in refrigerator and serve with Ginger Snap Cookies (recipe found in cookie section of this book).

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Bring to a boil in a saucepan, the milk and butter.
Remove from heat.
Blend in chocolate, vanilla and confectioners sugar until of spreading consistency.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except almonds.
Place in a lightly greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with almonds.

title: old fashioned boiled ham
directions: Place ham in large kettle so you can cover with cold water. Add the bay leaf and cloves.
Cover and boil gently for around 4 hours until tender, about 25 minutes per pound.
Let ham remain in water about 2 or 3 hours.
Ham is ready to eat.

title: pumpkin apple muffins
directions: In large bowl combine first 5 ingredients - set aside.
In medium bowl, combine eggs, oil and pumpkin; mix well and add to dry ingredients.
Stir until moistened.
Add apples. Spoon into greased or paper-lined muffin pan. Bake at 350° for 35-40 minutes.
Makes 18 muffins.

title: coffee delight
directions: Crush crackers into crumbs.
Mix crumbs and butter.
Press into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°; cool.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat hard one minute.
Add vanilla to buttermilk.
Add alternately with dry ingredients to shortening mixture (beginning and ending with flour).
Add vinegar, then food coloring. Mix well for 2 or 3 minutes.
Bake in two 9-inch greased and floured cake pans at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine the beans, bacon and onion.
Combine the brown sugar, dry mustard and vinegar.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Mix all ingredients together. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: swiss steak
directions: In large pan, saute cut onions and bell pepper in oil.
Flour steaks; cut into small strips and brown with onions and bell pepper.
Add tomatoes and juice.
Cook for 1 hour on medium-high heat.
Keep a lid on the pan to keep in moisture.

title: ham-cheese balls
directions: Soften cheese at room temperature.
Combine all ingredients except nuts.
Refrigerate until set.
Roll into ball and cover with nuts.

title: bubba's pot roast
directions: Trim excess fat from meat and cut in medium-sized pieces. Sprinkle with paprika, salt and pepper.
Brown in hot oil in Dutch oven.
Add water and bay leaf and cover and simmer 2 hours or until meat is tender.
Place mushrooms, onions and carrots around and over meat.
Pour in tomato sauce.
Cover and simmer 60 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Serve with cooked noodles. Serves 6 to 8.
Enjoy!

title: potato pancakes
directions: Combine and stir in mixing bowl the potatoes, bread crumbs, egg yolks and salt.
Fold in egg whites.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into hot fat or on hot griddle.
Brown and turn.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: oyster stew
directions: Melt butter; add drained oysters and cook 3 minutes or until edges curl.
Add milk, salt, pepper and paprika.
Bring almost to boiling point and serve at once with oyster crackers.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Saute meat and onion; cook until brown.
Drain.
Mix meat into spaghetti sauce.
Add garlic and oregano.
Add milk, both cheeses and mushroom pieces.
Mix well and pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Makes 6 or 8 servings.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown
meat,
chopped
onion
and bell peppers.
Drain. Add tomatoes,
catsup,
Heinz 57 sauce and parsley flakes and sprinkle with Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer this for about 15 minutes. Add
mushroom
soup
and cooked macaroni.
Pour into casserole dish.
Put
grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Put slice of cheese on top of 1/2 chicken breast per person. Mix chicken soup, dry wine and stuffing mix.
Bake until chicken is tender.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook or steam broccoli.
Cook chicken.
Lay broccoli in bottom of pan, cube chicken and place on top of broccoli.
Mix everything but cheese, crumbs and butter. Put on top of chicken.
Then add cheese and crumbs, put butter on top.
Cook, covered, at 350° for 1 hour or until bubbles.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: persimmon pie
directions: Beat all ingredients together with rotary beater.
Pour into pastry-lined pie pan (9-inches).
Bake at 425° for 45 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted 1-inch from side of filling comes out clean.
Center may still look soft, but will set later.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli.
Place in greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Put chicken on top.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder. Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour to 45 minutes.

title: garlic pickles
directions: Pour off vinegar from pickles and save.
Slice pickles and put in jar.
Mix sugar and garlic with vinegar and shake.
Let stand in refrigerator 1 week before serving.

title: new orleans crawfish etouffee
directions: Melt butter in large skillet.
Saute vegetables for 1/2 hour. Add crawfish tails and seasonings.
Add flour, stirring for about 3 minutes.
Add chicken bouillon water and 1/4 cup each green onions and parsley.
Simmer for 15 minutes.

title: dole pineapple spinach salad
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve 1/2 cup juice for dressing.
Mix pineapple, bacon, spinach, celery and onion.
Combine reserved juice with remaining ingredients; mix well.
Add to salad and toss.
Makes 4 servings.

title: lean scalloped potatoes(microwave)
directions: Combine cheese, yogurt, milk, green onions and parsley.
Mix well.
Arrange half of potatoes in 2-quart microwave-safe dish. Spread half of cheese mixture over potatoes.
Repeat with remaining potatoes and cheese mixture.
Cover and microwave at High for 15 to 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Stir once after 8 minutes.

title: homemade chicken rice soup
directions: In a large pot, boil and debone chicken.
Add cream of chicken soup and onion (cut up).
Also add rice; cook until rice is done. Serve.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Add eggs and melted butter.
Blend well. Add vanilla.
Spread chocolate chips in unbaked pie shell.
Cover chips with pecans.
Pour in egg mixture.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: fran's cheese balls
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix all ingredients together and make into a ball.
If desired, roll in crushed nuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: candy canes
directions: Mix together milk, salt and sugar.
Soften yeast in a little warm water and add to mixture.
Stir in eggs, Crisco or margarine and flour.
Add flour in two additions, using the amount necessary to make it easy to handle.
Knead dough until mixed.
Dump out onto floured surface and wash bowl, then grease bowl.
Put dough back in and turn dough over right away.
Cover and let rise until double, then punch down gently and let rise again.

title: dutch potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in water for 20 to 25 minutes or until just tender. Drain well, peel and cube.

title: jellied gazpacho
directions: Add gelatin to 1/4 cup tomato juice.
Let stand for 5 minutes. Meanwhile, combine 1 3/4 cup tomato juice and the bouillon cube in saucepan. Bring to boil, stirring to dissolve cube in saucepan. Add gelatin; stir to dissolve.
Then add all remaining ingredients.
Pour into an 8 or 9-inch pan and chill until set. Spoon into chilled bowls.

title: honey bunches
directions: Mix oats, coconut, nuts and flour; set aside.
Mix brown sugar, butter and honey together.
Bring to a boil, pour over dry ingredients.
Blend well.
Bake at 350° in greased muffin cups for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: mashed potatoes dish
directions: Combine mashed potatoes and cream cheese; beat well.
Stir in 1 beaten egg, 2 tablespoons chopped green onion and parsley; blend well.
Transfer to greased baking dish. Dot with butter. Sprinkle top with paprika.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Do not beat. Add 1 cup pecans if desired. Spoon into 2 loaf pans. Bake 325 degrees for 45 to 60 minutes. If you grate and freeze zucchini in the summer, you will need to freeze 3 cups for this recipe.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Optional:
Nuts or raisins may be added to batter if desired.

title: sole fish
directions: Wash fish, dry thoroughly. Cut foil 14 inch square. Place one fish fillet in center of each. Arrange shrimp and mushrooms over fillet. Sprinkle with salt, pepper, paprika, and lemon juice. Top each with 1/4 cup white sauce. Sprinkle with parsley. Fold to seal. Bake at 400° for 35 minutes. Serve in foil. Makes 8 servings.

title: oyster stew
directions: In large saucepan cook carrots and celery in 1/4 cup butter till tender.
Blend flour, salt, Worcestershire sauce, hot pepper sauce, and 2 Tablespoons water till smooth.
Add to vegetables. Add oysters and the liquid.
Return to boiling; simmer over very low heat 3 to 4 minutes, stirring gently.
Add hot milk.
Remove from heat.
Cover; let stand 15 minutes.
Place remaining butter in tureen.
Reheat stew to serving temperature.
Pour into tureen. Dash with paprika, if desired.

title: berry dessert
directions: Cream the cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Add Cool Whip. Spread on crust, then drain frozen berries.
Use that liquid and rest of water to equal 3 cups and mix with Danish dessert topping. Add berries.
Cool (Junket) well.
When cool, pour over cheese layer, then add another layer of Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: breakfast quiche
directions: Line unpricked pastry shell with a double thickness of heavy-duty foil.
Bake at 450° for 5 minutes; remove foil.
Bake 5 minutes longer.
Remove from the oven and let cool.
Reduce heat to 425°.
Sprinkle bacon, cheeses and onion over the crust.
In a bowl, beat eggs, cream, salt, sugar and cayenne.
Pour into the crust.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300°.
Bake 30 minutes longer or until a knife inserted near the center comes out clean. Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: working woman soup
directions: Brown ground beef with the onion in a skillet.
Drain in large pot.
Add all ingredients.
Bring to a boil, then cover and simmer for 20 minutes or until done.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine dressing mix and butter; press 1/2 of mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour on top of dressing mixture.
Top with remaining dressing mix.
Bake 1 hour at 300° or half hour at 375°.

title: lynn's cholesterol free muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then add wet.
Mix then place in muffin tins sprayed with nonstick spray coating.
Instead of using flour to coat tins, use rolled oats.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: microwave rice pudding
directions: Put hot water, rice and salt in 2-quart casserole; cover with waxed paper.
Microwave 5 to 6 minutes until rice is tender. Standing time:
5 minutes, covered.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat slowly; spoon off excess fat.
Add next 6 ingredients; simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes, stirring several times.

title: basic vinegar dressing
directions: Combine ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to a boil to dissolve sugar.
Cool.
Store in jar in refrigerator.

title: sweet potato candy
directions: Mix all ingredients, except the peanut butter, into a dough. (Add a little extra powdered sugar to stiffen the dough if needed.) Roll out the dough 1/4-inch thick onto a floured surface. Spread the peanut butter evenly over the rolled out dough. Start at 1 end and roll it over like a jelly roll. Cut into slices approximately 1/2-inch wide. Let set until slices are firm.

title: broccoli and chicken duo
directions: Boil chicken breasts
with
carrots
and onion in small amount of water.
Set
aside
and	steam
chopped broccoli for about 3 minutes.
Heat
the cream of chicken soup, half can of water
and soy sauce.	Mix together the chopped chicken (bite-size
pieces), carrots,
onions
and
the	chopped
broccoli. Arrange
in	baking dish and pour the hot soup over all.
Heat for 5 to 8 minutes in oven.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: barbecued pork chops
directions: Season pork chops with salt and pepper; dust with flour.
Sear on both sides until browned.
Reduce heat and cook for 30 minutes or until tender.
Combine 1 teaspoon salt and remaining ingredients; heat to boiling.
Pour over chops.

title: meat loaf patties
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape in 1-inch burgers and put into oblong long pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: hot crabmeat dip
directions: Heat ingredients until blended.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese; bake at 350° for about 40 to 45 minutes.
Prepare ahead of time; let cool.
The cooler it gets, the better.

title: broker's tip dip(he was a famous derby winner)
directions: Combine all ingredients, heat over low heat.
Remove to chafing dish.
Serve with tortilla chips or potato chips.

title: hot rize biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Cut shortening into flour until particles are like fine crumbs.
Add milk and stir with a fork only until dough leaves the side of the bowl.
Turn dough out onto lightly floured board or pastry cloth; knead just until smooth.
Roll dough out about 1/2-inch thick and cut with floured cutter.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 12 to 14 (2-inch) biscuits.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Pour into 2 ungreased 9-inch pans and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Use your favorite cream cheese icing.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in bowl.
Mix well and cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water; stir in milk mixture. Gradually stir in flour to make a stiff dough.
Beat well after each addition.
Cover bowl with damp towel.
Let rise; knead dough on floured board.
Divide dough in half; shape into 2 loaves, adding if sticky.
Place loaves in 2 pans, greased lightly.
Brush tops with melted butter.
Cover and let rise until double in size.
Bake at 375° until done, 35 to 40 minutes.

title: banana cake
directions: Pour over cake while in pan.
Mix 1/2 banana and enough powdered sugar to make glaze.

title: hot fudge sauce 2(revised - easy - microwaved)
directions: Microwave enough to heat.
Blend with a spoon until creamy.

title: hawaiian chicken kebabs
directions: Cut chicken, pineapple, peppers and onions into approximately 24 pieces, each about 1 inch thick.
Combine chicken, pineapple juice, garlic, soy sauce and oil in a large nonmetallic bowl. Marinate in refrigerator for at least 1 hour and up to 1 day. Coat vegetables with cooking spray.

Thread a piece of each item on 8 skewers, repeating twice in same order. Brush with marinade. Grill over medium-hot coals until chicken is completely cooked, about 8-10 minutes, turning kebabs every 2 minutes so they're cooked evenly on all sided.
Yields 2 kebabs and 1/2 c. rice per serving.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Cook peaches in water until tender.
Mix 2 tablespoons of flour, sugar and pinch of salt.
Add to peaches.
Add melted butter.

title: best rhubarb pie
directions: * Let set overnight in refrigerator.

title: monkey bread
directions: Scald
milk.
Pour
over
sugar
and butter.
Let stand until lukewarm.
Then
stir
in
yeast,
salt and beaten eggs. Add 5 or 6
cups
of
flour.
Knead and let rise for 3 hours. Roll out
and cut into round shape.
While rolling out, put 1 cube of butter in pan and melt.
Place circles in pans and let rise again approximately
1 hour.
Use 2 Bundt pans.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Yields 2 circle loaves.

title: cherry bread pudding
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add egg, beating until mixed.
Add cherries and nuts.
Mix soda with flour and combine with first mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, depending on pan size.

title: love recipe
directions: Melt the hugs and kisses.

Mix together thoughtfulness, helpfulness, obedience and happiness. Slowly stir in the hugs and kisses. When the mixture is smooth, add the kindness and consideration. The sweetness and humor can be added at all times.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix together in a large pan the tuna, peas, celery, cheese, corn and water.
Bring to a boil over medium heat and let simmer, stirring until cheese melts.
Add a dash of salt and a dash of pepper; stir.
Add the noodles and stir occasionally until noodles are soft.
Add more water, if needed.

title: strawberry glazed fruit salad
directions: In large bowl, gently toss strawberries, pineapple and bananas. Fold in the glaze.
Chill for 1 hour.
(Serves 6-8.)

title: egg salad(deviled egg sandwiches are great with chips!)
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients except bread.
You may need more or less of mayonnaise, depending on taste.
Spread on slice of bread and top with another slice of bread for a sandwich. Serves 6.

title: cold eye of round
directions: In a small mixing bowl, blend all ingredients, except roast. Place beef in a separate bowl.
Pour marinade over.
Cover well. Refrigerate overnight or let stand at room temperature for 8 hours.
When ready to cook, remove meat from marinade.
Place in roasting pan.
Heat oven to 450°.
Cook beef 10 minutes on 1 side. Salt and pepper, turn and cook 10 minutes.
Remove from pan for rare; for medium cook 15 minutes on each side; for well done, 20 minutes.
Wrap, refrigerate and serve chilled plain or with your favorite sauce.
Makes 10 servings.

title: cherry squares
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Beat in eggs.
Stir in flour and add nuts.
Spread 3/4 of mixture in greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Cover with cherries.
Drop remaining batter by spoonfuls on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Slice potatoes thinly in bottom of a casserole dish.
Brown hamburger and put on top of potatoes.
Spread soup on top; clean can with 1/2 cup milk.
Pour over casserole.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° or until potatoes are done.

title: pickled squash
directions: Sprinkle canning salt over dry squash; let stand 1 hour.
Rinse well.
Bring sugar, vinegar and spices to a boil; add squash, peppers and onions.
Bring to a boil again.
Remove from heat.
Put in sterilized jars; turn upside down until cool.
Ready to eat when cool.

title: geno's brunswick stew
directions: Bake Boston butt slow on low heat until done. Boil chicken in about 2 1/2 cups water. Save broth. Bone. Grind all meat and vegetables together with meat grinder (food processor can be used). Combine all other ingredients, except seasoning and bring to a boil. (Put ground beef in raw.) Cook on low heat until ground beef is done, stirring constantly. Cook in heavy stockpot to avoid sticking. Add seasoning.

title: steak casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut fat from steak and cut into 1 or 2-inch pieces.
Season and dredge in flour and brown in hot fat quickly.
Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Add tomatoes, onion, green pepper, rice, tomato juice, salt and pepper.
Arrange with the onion slices on top.
Cover with foil and bake for 1 1/2 hours.

title: "better than sex cake"
directions: First Layer:
Combine flour, butter and 1 cup nuts in 9 x 13 pan.
(Pat in pan.)
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: cheese soup
directions: Place carrots, celery, onion and bouillon cubes in water and boil until tender.
Add Velveeta cheese.
Make a paste of margarine and flour; add to cheese soup after taking off heat.

title: salami pinwheels
directions: Peel casing off salami slices.
Spread softened cream cheese carefully onto each salami and slice with spatula.
Roll each slice up.
Fasten with toothpicks.
Refrigerate until cream cheese hardens.
Carefully remove toothpicks and slice into 3/4-inch slices and arrange with cut edges up.

title: mom's roquefort dressing
directions: Add Roquefort cheese to cream cheese.
Add salt, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix and add mayonnaise and light cream. Refrigerate.

title: crunchy sweet pickles
directions: Drain pickles, reserving 3 tablespoons juice.
Cut pickles into chunks (each pickle into 3 or 4 pieces).
Mix the other ingredients and shake well to dissolve sugar and pour over pickles.
Refrigerate several days before using.

title: pearl's turkey dressing
directions: Mix bread crumbs and cornbread with turkey stock until moist. Saute celery and onion before adding.
Mix all together.
Be sure to use enough stock so it will not be stiff.

title: tri-bean bake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In 10-inch nonstick skillet, combine onion, celery and oil.
Cook over medium heat for 5 to 8 minutes or until vegetables are tender; stir occasionally.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Crush the stuffing. Beat the eggs. Dip chicken breast into beaten eggs, then into stuffing mix. Brown chicken in skillet with butter. Lay browned chicken in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Add the broth and mushrooms. Cover with slices of cheese. Bake 1 hour at 350°. Bake 35 minutes longer if not done.

title: baked chicken nuggets
directions: Pre-heat oven to 400 degrees.
Cut chicken into bite-sized pieces.
Place cornflakes into plastic bag and crush by using a rolling pin.
Add remaining ingredients to crushed cornflakes. Close bag tightly and shake until blended.
Add a few chicken pieces at a time to crumb mixture and shake to coat evenly. Lightly grease a cookie sheet.
Place chicken pieces on cookie sheet, not touching.
Bake until golden brown.
Cook about 12 to 14 minutes.

title: souperior meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl combine all ingredients.
In large shallow baking pan, shape into loaf.
Bake 1 hour or until done.
Tested recipe from the Lipton kitchens. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: old time banana pudding
directions: Stir sugar, flour and egg until blended.
Add milk until dissolved.
Place on medium burner; stir often, approximately 5 minutes, until mixture thickens.
Take off burner.
Add butter and vanilla extract.
Stir and pour over vanilla wafers and banana. Serves 4.

title: fran's cheese cake
directions: Blend together cream cheese and Ricotta until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time, sugar, melted butter, flour and cornstarch. Add vanilla and lemon juice.
Last, blend in sour cream.
Pour batter into spring-form pan.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.
Do not open oven door!
After 1 hour, check cake (it should be slightly browned on top).
Shut oven off.
Leave cake in oven about 1 1/2 hours with door slightly open.
Can be served with fruit topping.

title: chicken pie
directions: In 3-quart saucepan over medium heat in hot butter, cook onions and celery until tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in soup, milk and Worcestershire sauce until well blended.
Add chicken, vegetables and potatoes.
Heat through, stirring occasionally. Spoon into baking dish, set aside.
Preheat oven to 400°.
On a floured surface, roll pastry 1-inch large all around the baking dish.
With knife, cut pastry into 3/4-inch strips.
Crisscross over the soup mixture to form lattice top.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: marie's apricot dessert
directions: Set aside 1/2 cup crushed vanilla wafers.
Mix vanilla wafers, powdered sugar, eggs and pecans.
May need to add 3 teaspoons milk to hold together.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Cool.
Cook apricots according to package directions; mash.
Add 1 cup sugar and cubed butter.
Spread on top of crust.
Cover with Cool Whip and crumbs.

title: papas gisadas
directions: Heat oil in frying pan and saute potatoes.
Add onion to potatoes.
Add water, tomato sauce and all remaining ingredients. Simmer, adding more water if needed.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Cut carrots into 2-inch pieces.
Heat carrots and remaining ingredients except parsley to boiling. Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until carrots are tender (approximately 25 minutes). Serves 4 to 6.

title: congealed orange salad
directions: Mix first two ingredients until gelatin is completely dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients and chill for 4 hours.

title: no-cook marshmallow frosting
directions: Beat egg whites and salt until soft peaks form.
Add sugar, 1 teaspoon at a time, beating until smooth and glossy.
Continue beating and add syrup, a little at a time, until frosting peaks. Fold in vanilla.
Makes enough for 2 (9-inch) layers.

title: barbecued meat balls
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Form into small meat balls and brown on all sides in small amount of oil.
Continue cooking for 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and drain.

title: sweet potato delight
directions: Cook about 40 minutes at 360° or until golden brown.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion together until tender.
Drain well.
Add cracker crumbs, butter and one cup of cheese.
Beat eggs with milk and add to the squash and onion mixture.
Pour into buttered casserole and top with remaining 1/2 cup of cheese.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: creamy caramel frosting
directions: Melt butter.
Remove from heat.
Add brown sugar and cream, stirring until smooth.
Return to heat.
Bring to boil and boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Cool until bottom of pan is lukewarm.
Beat in powdered sugar until smooth.
Add vanilla.

title: sweet and sour pork(microwave)
directions: In 3-quart casserole, combine oil and carrots.
Cook 5 minutes. Stir in pork, onion, red and green pepper.
Cover and cook 3 minutes.
Drain pineapple (save juice; 1/2 cup).
In a clean bowl add 1/2 cup juice to cornstarch; stir until dissolved.
Stir in all remaining ingredients to make sauce.
Add sauce to the pork mixture.
Stir to mix.
Cover and cook on medium 10 to 17 minutes. Stir twice until sauce is thickened and pork is done.
Serve over rice.

title: date bars
directions: Beat eggs with sugar until thick.
Sift dry ingredients and add to first mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Add nuts, dates and vanilla.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes. Cut in squares.
Roll in confectioners sugar.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
This can be baked in a Bundt pan or angel food cake pan.
To make fruit cake, add any fruit you desire.
Bake in a very slow oven for about 2 hours, but test for doneness occasionally.
This is a good cake for the Christmas holidays.

title: lemon freeze
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, put graham crackers and butter; mix well.
Pat out to make a crust.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Cook chicken and debone.
Mix all ingredients, except chicken and chips.
Place a layer of chicken, a layer of the mixture and then a layer of chips.
Repeat the layering and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: pizza fondue
directions: In a large skillet brown onion and ground beef in butter. Stir frequently.
Mix cornstarch, fennel seed, oregano and garlic powder together and stir into the meat.
Add pizza sauce with rapid stirring and reduce the heat.
Add grated cheese in 1/3 portions and stir well until cheese melts.
Serve with cubes of French bread or you can slice the bread and eat it like an open-faced sandwich.

title: french dip sandwiches
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place meat in a roasting pan and cover with Worcestershire sauce and garlic salt.
Generously sprinkle with parsley flakes, oregano, pepper, basil and Tabasco sauce. Bake, covered, 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300°; pour broth around meat and continue to cook in a covered roasting pan, 2 to 4 hours. Check periodically to see if more liquid is needed; add water, if necessary.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine eggs (beaten) with sugar and flour.
Add milk, corn and melted butter in baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 50 minutes or until firm.
Makes 10 servings.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in greased 10-inch tube pan. Bake 1 1/2 hours.
Glaze while cake is still hot.

title: corn casserole
directions: In a casserole dish, combine all the ingredients. Mix well. Bake in preheated oven at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Mix all together jello, water, sugar, salt and lemon juice. Chill until mixture thickens, but not completely jelled.
Combine sweetened condensed milk and Pet milk; whip until fluffy.
Mix with jello mixture.
Pour over graham cracker crust.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares.
Serves 24.

title: easy blueberry syrup
directions: In a saucepan, boil sugar, water and cornstarch.
Cook and stir until mixture is clean.
Add remaining ingredients; bring to boil.
Simmer until it begins to thicken.

title: marshmallow frosting
directions: In a mixer bowl, beat sugar, egg white, cream of tartar and hot water.
Just before peak stage, add vanilla.
Beat to stiff peak stage.
Frosts 9 x 13-inch.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Mix together crushed graham crackers and 1/2 stick oleo; chill.
Beat for 10 minutes the powdered sugar, 1 stick oleo, eggs and vanilla.
Put on top of crackers and chill for 2 hours.

title: fish bake
directions: Place fish in a 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish. Cover with soup. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes. Combine remaining ingredients. Put on fish and bake another 10 minutes.

title: nursery fizz
directions: Fill a large goblet with ice and pour in equal parts of orange juice and ginger ale.
Decorate with a slice of orange speared with a cherry and 2 straws.

title: green rice
directions: Combine rice, boiling water, salt and set aside.
Mix in large bowl onion, oil, Pet milk, soup, parsley, eggs and garlic salt. Mix with rice and put in casserole.
Grate cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Mix all well.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with foil. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Cook until cheese melts.

title: hot cinnamon candy
directions: Cook at medium to high heat until hard cracked stage (300°) approximately 35 minutes.
Take off heat.
Add red food coloring. Add one bottle of cinnamon flavoring (.25 ounce).
If wanted hotter flavor, add more cinnamon.
Pour on greased or buttered cookie sheet until hard.
Crack and eat!
To harden faster, refrigerate.

title: corn flakes
directions: Melt butter and marshmallows together; add food coloring to suit you.
Put in corn flakes and stir.
Put on wax paper. Decorate with cinnamon.

title: zucchini pickles(like bread and butter pickles)
directions: Slice zucchini in thin slices.
Add chopped onion and salt. Add water to 1-inch over top of vegetables.
Let stand 2 hours.

title: 2 minute fudge
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk, butter and salt together; bring to a boil on high.
Cook 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour in buttered pan.
Cool and cut.

title: pineapple cheesecake
directions: Crush biscuits.
Mix with sugar, cinnamon and butter.
Press into bottom and sides of spring-form pan.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Put coconut and pecans in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cake mix as directed on package and pour over coconut and pecan mixture.
Mix cream cheese, butter and powdered sugar and spoon on top of cake.
Bake 55 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Beat egg; add all ingredients and mix well.
Place in greased casserole; top with crushed crackers. Bake at 350° for 15 to 30 minutes until bubbly and crackers are browned.

title: beer cake
directions: Cream brown sugar and shortening until smooth. Add eggs, blending well. Combine dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture, alternately with beer, beating well after each addition. Stir in pecans and dates. Spoon batter into a well-greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Cool. Frost with Caramel Frosting.

title: fiesta chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper.
Grill, bone side up, over medium heat on outdoor grill for 20 minutes.
Combine salsa and lime juice; turn chicken and grill for 15 to 25 minutes more, brushing with 1/2 cup salsa mixture.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in jar until ready to use.
Have water boiling (hot water brings the flavor out better). I use 2 teaspoons to a teacup of water.
Use more or less to taste.

title: never fail fudge
directions: Combine butter, sugar and milk.
Boil 5 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients except nuts.
Beat until well mixed.
Add nuts.
Put into buttered pan.
Cool until firm.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Mix everything except mushrooms in pan.
Boil mixture.
Pour over mushrooms and let cool.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Serve with toothpicks and pieces of crackers to catch marinade.

title: french sponge cookies
directions: Beat egg yolks in small bowl until very thick and lemon colored.
Add flavoring during the beating.
In another bowl, beat whites until stiff and shiny.
Add sugar 1 tablespoon at a time. Beat constantly.
Beat until whites are stiff and glossy.
Gently and slowly fold in egg yolks, then dry ingredients.
Drop onto ungreased baking sheet by level tablespoonful for each cookie. Space 2 inches apart.
Bake 10 minutes until golden brown at 350° .
Let stand, uncovered, to dry and crisp.
Makes 40 cookies.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello with boiling water.
Add strawberries, pineapple, bananas and nuts.
Pour half of jello mixture into pan and set.
Add 1/2 pint sour cream, then add rest of jello fruit mixture.

title: quick beef with broccoli stir-fry
directions: Trim fat from steak.
Slice steak diagonally across grain into thin strips.
Combine tomatoes and water.
Let stand 5 minutes. Drain and slice thinly.
Break broccoli flowerets.
Slice green onions.
Mince garlic.
Cook rice according to package directions. Combine cornstarch, juice or wine and soy sauce; stir well.
Coat a wok with vegetable cooking spray; place over medium-high heat until hot.
Add steak; stir-fry 2 minutes.
Remove steak from wok; set aside.
Add oil to wok; heat to hot.
Add broccoli; stir-fry 3 minutes.
Add tomatoes, green onions and garlic; stir-fry 1 more minute.
Add cornstarch mixture and beef to wok; stir-fry 1 minute or until sauce is thickened and bubbly.
Serve over rice.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: banana pudding
directions: Puddings are not instant.
Combine 2 cups of liquid from cans. Combine with pudding.
Mix and cook until thick.
Let cool.
Fold in fruit and refrigerate.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni, drain and cool.
Add chopped onion and celery. Cut eggs and add, then add dressing.
Refrigerate a few hours and serve.

title: party salad
directions: Pour dressing over combined vegetables.
Cover and marinate in dressing in refrigerator several hours or overnight.
Drain, reserving marinade.
Combine vegetables and greens; toss lightly. Serve with reserved marinade.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: key lime pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well until mixture thickens.
Reserve egg whites for meringue.

title: cobbler
directions: Spread butter in 9 x 13 pan.
In a bowl, mix together the milk, sugar and flour.
Pour mixture into pan and spread fruit and it's sauce on top evenly.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Filling:
Scald the milk in top of double boiler.
Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt; mix in scalded milk.
Beat egg yolks with a fork.
Add some of the hot mixture a small amount at a time with egg yolks, then add to milk mixture.

title: raisin-custard pie
directions: Cook in double boiler until thick.
Put in baked pie shell.

title: pancakes
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Add milk and shortening.
Add flour, salt and baking powder.
Mix well with mixer.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Fry in nonstick frying pan, turning to brown both sides.
You can also make waffles with this mix.

title: apple bread
directions: Mix in order given. Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: mocha caramels
directions: Mix all ingredients, except vanilla, in a large, heavy saucepan.
Heat to boiling over medium heat, stirring constantly. Cook until temperature reaches 248° (firm ball stage on thermometer), about 1 hour.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla. Pour into buttered 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Let stand until cool.
Cut into 1-inch squares and wrap each caramel in waxed paper.
Refrigerate up to 3 weeks.

title: texas tuna on baked potatoes
directions: Cook onion and celery in 1 tablespoon oil until tender, but not brown. Add remaining ingredients, except the tuna, and simmer, uncovered, about 10 minutes. Fold in tuna and heat.
Serve on top of baked potatoes that have been split open and scored.
Sprinkle grated Cheddar
and Monterey Jack cheese on top and put under broiler in oven until cheeses are melted.
(Can put a little bottled barbecue sauce on top of that.)
Serves 4.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar and eggs.
Add dry ingredients, water and
vanilla.
Mix
well.
Add
chocolate chips or coconut. Drop by
spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375°.

title: salsa
directions: Chunky Salsa: Finely chop onion, garlic, cilantro and jalapeno peppers (removing seeds before chopping makes a milder salsa). Mix together and add tomatoes, lime juice, salt and pepper. Mix well.

title: baked rice
directions: Combine all ingredients; stir well.
Pour into a Pam sprayed 1 1/2-quart casserole dish and bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: million dollar pie
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine Cool Whip, condensed milk and lemon juice; stir with a spoon until mixture is smooth.
Drain pineapple juice.
Add crushed pineapple.
Cut frozen strawberries into bite size pieces and add to mixture, along with pecans.
Stir until well mixed.
Pour juice from strawberries into mixture for pink color.
(Optional:
Add pineapple juice to mixture.
The more juice added, the sweeter the mixture will be.)
Pour mixture into 2 pie crusts; chill pies for at least 3 hours in the refrigerator. Cut and serve.

title: arlene's marinated carrots
directions: Cut carrots in thin lengthwise strips.
If very long, cut in half.
Cook in a little water until just tender.
Combine all and pour over carrots.
Marinate 24 hours.
Can be made several days ahead and refrigerated.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix up stuffing according to package and set aside (uncooked).

title: no-fat nutri-muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Chop apricots.
Mix dry ingredients, Grape-Nuts, apricots and raisins together in a large mixing bowl. Blend thoroughly to prevent large lumps.

title: no sugar apple pie filling
directions: Peel, core and thinly slice apples.
In bowl, combine sugar, flour, spices and salt.
Mix with sliced apples.
Pour into 9-inch pastry lined pan.
Dot with butter.
Add top crust, cutting slits to vent.
Bake in 400° oven for 50 minutes or until crust is nice and brown and apples are well done.

title: iced tea punch
directions: Steep 8 tea bags in 4 cups boiling water for 10 minutes.
Pour into a gallon jug.
Add a 6 ounce can of orange juice concentrate and a 6 ounce can of lemonade concentrate.
Fill jug with cold water.
Sweeten to taste.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: strawberry nut salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Fold in strawberries, drained pineapple, bananas and nuts.
Turn half of mixture into dish and refrigerate until firm.
Spread with sour cream.
Spoon on rest of jello mixture and refrigerate.

title: apple yam bake
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon with apples and nuts.
Alternate layers of apple mixture and yams in baking dish.
Cover top with butter, cut in pieces.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Top with marshmallows and broil until lightly brown.

title: divinity candy
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, salt and water.
Cook until mixture spins a thread.
Pour over beaten egg whites and beat well until candy holds its shape when dropped from a spoon.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: pizza bread
directions: On oiled surface, roll or press dough until thin.
You can use cooked sausage, pepperoni or your favorite pizza toppings.
Add Mozzarella, about 1 cup per loaf.
Pull sides together and pinch to close.
On oiled cookie sheet, place seam side down.
Let rise about 15 to 20 minutes.
Bake in a 400° oven about 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove and brush with garlic butter.
Let set 5 minutes.
Slice and serve with your favorite sauce.

title: broiled fresh salmon steaks
directions: Wash and wipe dry 1 steak per person.
Place on greased broiler.
Pour melted butter with lemon juice added over slices and let set.
Salt and pepper each and sprinkle with paprika.

title: cranberry macaroon pie
directions: Grease pie pan well; sprinkle with cranberries, then sprinkle cranberries with sugar and nuts.
Beat eggs well.
Add sugar gradually; mix well.
Add flour and melted butter; beat well. Pour over top of cranberries.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes to give macaroon flavor.

title: patio beans
directions: Put 4 to 5 slices bacon in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add half the beans. Add the onions, green peppers and tomatoes.
Put in rest of beans.
Mix together catsup, brown sugar and salt. Pour over beans.
Put remaining bacon on top. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: poppy seed and lime dressing
directions: Heat vinegar and lime juice to boiling.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add to hot mixture.
Stir to dissolve sugar.
Add oil and onion juice.
Beat with rotary beater until thoroughly mixed and slightly thickened.
Chill.
Serve on canned or fresh fruit. Makes 1 3/4 cups.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix tuna, soup, onion and chips, saving 1/2 cup of chips for the top.
Fold in peas, pour into a lightly greased casserole dish. Top with remaining chips.
Bake 15 to 30 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: rhubarb whip
directions: Cook rhubarb, sugar and water 8 to 10 minutes.
Add jello and dissolve.
Stir in 1/2 cup cold water.
Chill until partially set. Whip until fluffy.
Fold in whipped cream or small Cool Whip. Chill.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Add water as directed on frozen concentrate and mix all juices together.
Serve in punch bowl over ice cubes.
May garnish with lemon and/or orange slices.
May also freeze ice cubes of punch mixture.

title: cheese potatoes for the grill
directions: Slice potatoes but leave together.
Place on a piece of heavy-duty foil.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper, and garlic. Sprinkle with onion.
Dot with butter.
Wrap up tight.
Place on grill at medium-high heat.
Cook for about 40 minutes.
When done, open and place cheese cubes inside.
Reclose and melt cheese. Remove from heat.
Individual potatoes may be done.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Drain large can of asparagus, reserving liquid.
Place on bottom of greased baking dish.
Slice hard-boiled eggs over top. Spread a can of cream of mushroom soup over top.
(Cheddar cheese soup may be used instead.)
Top with crushed Ritz crackers.
Pour asparagus juice over all.
Bake until it bubbles.
Serves 4.

title: creole rice and tuna casserole
directions: Cook the rice and set it aside to cool.
Cook the eggs in the oil like you would for an omelet.
Remove it from the skillet and cut into small pieces.
Cook the onion, green pepper and celery in the skillet with the bacon drippings until just tender.
Add the rice, eggs and soy sauce and stir gently to mix.
Next, add the tuna which you have drained and flaked.
Place in casserole.
Bake at 425° until thoroughly heated.

title: quesillo(flan)
directions: Melt the sugar in a small casserole and pour in a round cake baking dish until all dish is covered.
Mix ingredients in Osterizer.
Pour in cake dish and bake in oven for 45 minutes at 350°.
Wait until it cools and turn on plate.

title: broccoli cauliflower salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Add onion and raisins.
Refrigerate overnight or several hours.
Add vegetables before serving.

title: rocky road fudge
directions: In saucepan, melt chips with the sweetened condensed milk and margarine.
In a large bowl, combine the peanuts and the marshmallows.
Pour chocolate mixture into the peanut mixture and mix well.
Spread into a waxed paper lined 13 x 9-inch pan. Chill 2 hours.
Cut into squares.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients in double boiler until thickened. Add eggs yolks (slightly beaten).
Cook until thickened.
Cool and add butter and vanilla. Add coconut.

title: maude's famous noodles
directions: Cook noodles until done.
Drain.
Fry onions and pepper until done in butter.
Combine all ingredients in large saucepan, using one of the meats.
Cook on low heat until cheese melts.

title: layered spinach salad
directions: Rinse and shred spinach leaves.
Put half in the bottom of serving bowl.
Layer eggs, bacon, onion and peas.
Mix mayonnaise, salad dressing, vinegar and black pepper to make dressing.
Spread dressing over peas.
Sprinkle Swiss cheese over dressing and cover with remaining spinach.
Chill overnight and serve without mixing.

title: tomato cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat 2 minutes.
Pour in greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25-30 minutes. Frost with maple or caramel icing.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken; remove meat from	bones.	Reserve
broth. Chop meat into bite size pieces.
In large bowl, add both cans of cream of mushroom soup and both cans
of	cream
of chicken soup, 2 soup cans of reserved chicken
broth,
onion,
cheese, hot
peppers and chopped chicken.
Mix
ingredients	together. In large casserole dish, layer tortillas and then add layer of meat
mixture. Repeat layers.
Top
casserole
with
Fritos. Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: peanut clusters
directions: In the microwave, using a two-quart casserole, melt chips on High for 2 1/2 minutes.
Stir in peanuts and complete cooking for another minute or until chips are melted.
Drop by teaspoonful on wax paper.
Chill 1 hour in refrigerator until firm.

title: rosemary-mustard chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients except chicken in a large glass or plastic dish.
