Add chicken; turn to coat with marinade.
Cover and refrigerate at least 3 hours.

title: apple-pecan crisp
directions: Butter casserole.
Add apples.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and add water.
Blend together sugar, flour and butter until crumbly.
Add nuts.
Spread over apple mixture.
Bake 35 minutes at 400°.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Preheat Oven to 325 degrees.

title: easy beef stew
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Check occasionally. Stir, cover and bake until well done.

title: gingerbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift dry ingredients into a large mixing bowl.
Add shortening, eggs and molasses.
Mix together. Then gradually add hot water.
Mix well.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
May be served warm or cold.

title: mother's tomatoes and onions
directions: Combine oil, vinegar, salt and spices in a jar and shake well. Pour over tomato and onion slices that have been placed in a shallow glass dish.
Sprinkle with pepper.
Serve cold or at room temperature.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in margarine until tender; in blender on mix speed, beat the eggs, evaporated milk and whole milk together.
Add flour and cheeses and blend a few seconds. Add Worcestershire sauce, onion and green pepper.
Add salt and nutmeg.
Mix in ham pieces and mix well.
Pour mixture into prepared, unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes or until knife blade inserted in center comes out clean.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream sugar, shortening, peanut butter, salt, vanilla and eggs.
Add sifted flour and baking soda.
Roll in balls and flatten with a fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: venison barbecue
directions: Add barbecue sauce to all ingredients to taste.
Pour over venison meat.
Bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring to a boil and boil 8 minutes the first 3 ingredients. Add the marshmallow cream, peanut butter and vanilla. Beat with mixer until begins to get thick. Pour at once into a buttered pan.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Cut up artichokes.
Mix in large bowl all ingredients.
Spray casserole dish with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until brown and bubbly.
Sprinkle with slivered almonds, if desired. Serve with chips or small bread rounds.

title: tropical delight drink
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Add pudding mix, pineapple with juice and milk.
Beat on low until blended.
Stir in 2 cups Cool Whip and spoon into glasses. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Garnish with Cool Whip and coconut.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix ingredients in order listed.
Pour into 2 small wax paper lined loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done. Yields 20 slices.

title: crispy herb chicken
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Line with foil or grease baking pan. Combine potato flakes, Parmesan cheese, parsley flakes, onion powder, garlic salt and pepper; stir until well mixed.
Dip chicken into margarine; roll into potato flake mixture to coat. Place in greased pan.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes or until done and golden brown.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.
(My husband, T. G., loves this recipe!)

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Wash tomatoes; slice.
Mix flour, sugar, salt and pepper in bowl.
Dredge tomato slices in this mixture.
Heat butter or corn oil in large frying pan.
Put tomato slices in pan and brown on both sides.
Place on hot platter and serve.

title: chicken pie
directions: Break chicken in pieces and place in 9 x 13-inch greased pan or dish.
Spread chopped onion, then sliced eggs over chicken. Mix soups, Veg-All and chicken broth; pour mixture over all.
Mix flour, milk and mayonnaise; pour evenly over top.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until golden brown. Freezes nicely.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter; combine flour, sugar and enough milk to make batter the consistency of pancake batter. Pour over butter. Add filling and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until brown.

title: dilled okra
directions: Place garlic and pepper in bottom of hot sterilized jars. Remove stem from okra pods.
Pack okra firmly in jars. Add dill seed. Bring vinegar, water and salt to a boil.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Pour over okra.
Seal jars.

title: cheese chowder
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender.
Blend in flour.
Add remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Reduce heat.
Add cheese; stir to melt.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: perfect microwave rice(microwave)
directions: Place all ingredients in a large glass measuring or any microwave safe bowl.
(Note:
The rice expands during cooking, so be sure to choose a container that is large enough.)
Microwave on high, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Microwave on medium-low, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Do not stir the rice at any time during the cooking process.
Season with salt and fluff with a fork just before serving.

title: date n nut bread
directions: Combine dates, water, and soda in small bowl.
Set aside while mixing other ingredients (5 minutes).
Combine all other ingredients mixing well, add date mixture.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix, chill and serve cold.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Yields 8 servings.
Seasonings may vary according to individual tastes.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Core and parboil cabbage until limp and easy to roll.
Place in colander and separate leaves.
Slice largest leaves in halves on the ribs.
If ribs are large, cut them off.

title: mint chip pie
directions: Mix pudding, milk, extract and coloring.
Fold in whipped topping and chips.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with whipped topping and a few chocolate chips for garnish.

title: pecan sandies
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll into small balls; place on cookie sheet lined with parchment paper. Cook at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes. Cool. (These freeze good.)

title: macdonald's fudge recipe
directions: Forty-five minutes before cooking fudge, dissolve sugar in tall can Pet milk; add butter.
Bring to boiling point and boil for exactly 8 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from fire and stir in chocolate chips and Marshmallow Creme.
Add vanilla and black walnuts or pecans.
Pour into buttered 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan. Makes 5 pounds.

title: seafood pizza
directions: Blend cream cheese, Worcestershire, mayonnaise and onion. Spread on a plate and cover mixture with chili sauce.
Sprinkle with crab or shrimp.
Garnish with chopped parsley and sliced olives.
Serve with crackers.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in 1 egg at
a time.
Add	in
flour and 7-Up alternately, then add in flavorings.
Put
in tube pan (grease and flour pan).
Preheat oven
to
Cook
for	1
1/4	hours at 325°.	Stick with toothpick; if it comes out clean, cake is done.

title: banana milk shake
directions: Blend first four ingredients until smooth.
Sweeten to taste with sugar or sweetener.
Yields 1 cup.
Calories per serving:
90 with Equal sweetener, 105 with sugar.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix the ingredients.
Store in refrigerator.
Use 2 teaspoons to a cup of hot water.

title: katasha's chicken dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Pour into baking dish, greased.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: traditional apple butter
directions: Core and chop apples.
Combine apples and cider in a slow cooker.
Cover; cook on low for 10 to 12 hours or until apples are mushy.
Puree in food mill or sieve.
Return puree mixture to cooker.
Add sugar, cinnamon and cloves.
Cover and cook on low for 1 hour.
Will keep several weeks in the fridge or pour into hot jars and seal.
Can also be frozen in freezer containers. Makes 8 cups.

title: three-bean chili chowder
directions: Garnish with shredded Cheddar, Monterey Jack cheese, green onions (sliced) or sour cream.

title: sesame chicken salad
directions: Preheat broiler.
Rub chicken breast halves with salt and pepper and 1 tablespoon sesame oil. Place in broiler pan without rack.
Place in broiler at closest position to heat.
Broil 4 minutes on each side or until juices run clear when pierced.
Cool chicken until easy to handle.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef; add salt, pepper, garlic salt, onion powder and oil.
Pour into stockpot.
Add kidney beans and tomato sauce.
Simmer 45 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Serve hot with shredded cheese on top and crackers on the side.

title: tijuana torte
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add tomatoes, sauce, chilies and seasoning.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Place 1/2 cup mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place layer of tortillas on top. Add more mixture, then layer cheese.
Repeat layers.

title: easy lemon pie
directions: Mix lemonade and Eagle Brand milk together lightly. Fold Cool Whip into mixture.
Put mixture in
pie crusts and chill.
May be kept in freezer.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix flour, salt and brown sugar together.
Slightly beat egg yolks.
Mix milk and egg yolks together and add dry ingredients. Mix well.
Cook over medium heat until thick, stirring constantly. Remove from heat; cool and add butter and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell and spread meringue made of egg whites.

title: ship wreck
directions: Fry beef and onion in frying pan; add thyme and bay leaves. While that is cooking, clean vegetables.
Arrange in small roasting pan in layers: layer of celery, then carrots, then kidney beans and then a layer of sliced potatoes.
Put beef mixture on top of potatoes.
Next, spread an undiluted can of tomato soup over beef.
Fill soup can 1/2 full of water and add.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until carrots and potatoes are done.

title: mrs. moon's pineapple sherbet
directions: Combine all the ingredients and freeze until slushy.
Beat on high speed with an electric mixer, then refreeze before serving. Yields 8 servings.

title: creme de menthe
directions: Mix together as given.
Chill before serving.
Does not spoil within a reasonable time.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, two at a time, until all six are added.
Add flavorings.
Add whipping cream and flour, beginning with cream.
Bake in a tube cake pan for 1 1/2 hours at 350°, or until tested done with cake tester.

title: p-nut butter truffle cookies
directions: Mix peanut butter, brown sugar and egg.
Add chocolate chips and mix well.
Drop by tablespoons on baking sheet and bake 9 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool baking sheet on wire rack for 5 minutes and then remove cookies.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Melt margarine in hot potatoes.
Beat eggs and sugar until fluffy.
Add condensed milk and vanilla.
Add to potato mixture. Mix well. Bake in unbaked pie shell approximately 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Makes 2 pies.

title: angel food cake
directions: Make layers of cake, pudding, peaches, banana and pie filling. Top with Cool Whip.
Very good dessert.

title: flatbrod
directions: Mix and let cool.
Roll out and bake on griddle, just to brown.
Put on cookie sheet in a 250° oven until crisp.
Break into pieces and butter.

title: coconut millionaire cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box, then add 2 cups coconut, cook as directed.
When finished baking, while cake is hot, poke holes all over and pour can of cream of coconut and undrained pineapple on top.
Let cake cool and cover with Cool Whip and remaining coconut.

title: corned beef and cabbage
directions: Melt butter; blend in flour and stir until smooth.
Remove from heat; gradually add milk.
Return to heat; simmer until smooth and thickened, stirring constantly.
Cook cabbage and onion in boiling, salted water for 8 minutes; drain thoroughly.
Combine cabbage mixture and corned beef pieces and layer with sauce in greased 3-quart casserole.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: lemon crunch
directions: First Layer:
Crumble margarine, nuts and flour.
Bake 15 minutes at 370° in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let cool.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Chop broccoli and cauliflower.
Mix with uncooked peas and onions.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Mix them well and pour over the broccoli/cauliflower mixture.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours before serving.

title: clam dip
directions: Melt margarine.
Add onion, clams and crackers and put into 9-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle top with lemon juice.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, covered, then for 10 minutes uncovered.

title: cheddar spread
directions: Add milk and mustard to cheese; beat with electric mixer until almost smooth.
Serve with unpared apple wedges.
Makes about 1 cup.
Two tablespoons equal 1 meat exchange.
Five apple wedges are 1/2 fruit exchange.

title: gingered carrots
directions: In medium saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Cook, covered, stirring occasionally for 20 to 30 minutes or until carrots are tender.

title: cinnamon candy
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in a large saucepan.
Stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves.
Boil, without stirring, until temperature reaches 310° or until drops of syrup form hard, brittle threads in cold water.
Remove from heat after boiling has ceased.
Stir in cinnamon flavoring and coloring.

title: graham cracker treats
directions: Lay graham crackers in jelly roll pan edge-to-edge so that they completely cover the bottom of the pan. Gently boil butter/margarine and sugar for 5 minutes. Pour the hot mixture evenly over the graham crackers in the jelly roll pan. Chopped nuts or mini-chocolate chips may be sprinkled over the crackers at this stage, if desired. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes (until the butter mixture bubbles up a little). Break or cut into individual cracker segments. Cool completely. Store in airtight container.

title: chow mein casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except noodles, in a greased casserole. Bake for 1/2 hour at 350 degrees, uncovered.
Reduce heat to 300 degrees and cover with chow mein noodles.
Bake 1/2 hour longer.

title: green tomato pickles
directions: Dissolve lime in water; let lime settle that does not dissolve and pour off.
Add sliced tomatoes and leave for 24 hours.
Rinse tomatoes and soak in cold water for 4 hours, changing water every hour.
Drain well.
Mix other ingredients and bring to boil.
Pour over tomatoes and leave overnight.
Place on stove and boil for 1 hour.
Place in jars.
Makes about 12 pints.

title: summer country salad with basil
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water for 15 to 20 minutes, or until done.
Drain; place in bowl.
While potatoes are cooking, combine vinegar, mustard and the chopped basil in a food processor. Process for 15 seconds.
With motor running, add the oil slowly through the feed tube.
Pour mixture over potatoes.
Add salt and pepper and toss well.

title: sweet and sour black-eyed peas
directions: Combine black-eyed peas, molasses, vinegar, mustard and garlic powder.
Pour mixture into a shallow 2-quart casserole.
Top with pineapple slices.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: cheese and shrimp dip
directions: Mix and cover.
Let stand at room temperature before serving.

title: seasoned pretzels
directions: Mix together in microwave dish and microwave for 2 minutes. Lay on paper towel to get rid of excess oil.

title: krunchy kiss kookies
directions: Combine corn syrup and brown sugar in saucepan. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat. Blend in peanut butter and vanilla. Add rice cereal and cornflakes.
Stir until well coated. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet. Loosely shape into balls.
Gently press milk chocolate kiss in center, forming mixture into cookie shape. Store at room temperature in covered container.

title: more
directions: Melt fat and cook onions, pepper and garlic, but do not brown. Add ground
meat
and
cook until it is no longer red. Add tomatoes, chili powder and water; cover and cook over slow heat for 30 minutes.
Add mushrooms, cooked peas, salt, pepper and m.s.g.
Add
more seasoning to taste, if necessary.
Last, add cooked
spaghetti
to
sauce
and
blend well.
Fill large baking dish half
full,
cover
with half the cheese, then add the rest of
the
spaghetti
mixture and cover with remaining cheese.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes in a preheated 350° oven.

title: chicken with rice
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Wash chicken pieces and pat dry.
Place chicken, skin side up, in 4 baking pans, 13 x 9-inch.
Brush chicken with oil; season with salt, garlic salt, pepper and paprika.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt oleo in saucepan.
Add cocoa, sugar, flour and eggs.
Beat well until batter is thick and waxy.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into slightly greased pan or Pyrex pie pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Do not overcook.
The flour makes the crust.
Serve with vanilla ice cream or whipped cream.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil butter, milk and cocoa for 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add sugar, peanut butter, salt, vanilla and oatmeal.
Mix well and spoon onto aluminum foil.
Let cool for about 10 minutes.

title: bread clay
directions: Remove the crusts from the bread (crust crumbs will show up as dark spots later) and tear the slices into small pieces.
Pour the glue over the bread and mix by hand.
At first the mixture will be extremely sticky, so make sure to remove all hand jewelry.
Knead the dough vigorously for about 5 minutes or until smooth and velvety.
If dough is still sticky, clean hands and apply hand lotion or fabric softener on hands and continue kneading.
If properly kneaded, the mixture should now form beautifully into a smooth ball.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator.
If making an impression, first dust the mold with cornstarch, press the bread clay into place, then shake or lift out the dough and allow to dry on a flat surface.

title: aunt mary and uncle don's punch
directions: Simmer all ingredients together; do not boil.
Keep simmering as it is being used.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Saute celery, green pepper, onion and garlic until tender, but not brown.
Blend soup and milk and add to mixture.
Add cheese, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce, stirring until cheese melts. Add chicken and heat thoroughly.
Combine with cooked spaghetti. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and parsley.
Serves 6 persons.

title: tomato cracker salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Very good with fish.

title: lissa's favorite spaghetti
directions: Lightly brown ground meat and drain.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix and simmer 2 hours over low heat.
This can also be simmered in crock-pot.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli roll-ups
directions: Melt butter in saucepan over medium heat.
Gradually add flour, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat; cook and stir 2 to 3 minutes. Remove from heat.
Gradually add cream, stirring constantly.
Add cheese and cook and stir until thickened.
Season to taste with nutmeg, salt and pepper; set aside.
If frozen, thaw broccoli completely.
Drain and pat dry.
Top ham slice with turkey slice. Place 2 broccoli spears along one edge with florets facing opposite directions.
Roll meats around broccoli.
Place broccoli rolls, seams down, in nonmetal or ovenproof dish.
Pour on sauce.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Serve on toast.
Microwave on High 2 minutes.
Rotate and cook 4 minutes.

title: sharon's broccoli casserole
directions: Bake until rice is done, about 45 minutes to 1 hour, at 325°.

title: marmalade cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients. Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. (Place far apart or they bake into one big cookie.)

title: maple syrup
directions: Boil water; pour over sugar and stir to melt sugar.
Add maple flavoring.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until thick and lemon colored.
Gradually add sugar, oil and vanilla to eggs.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Add flour mixture and zucchini alternately to the egg mixture.
Fold in chopped nuts.
Pour into 2 oiled and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes, then cool on rack.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Follow the directions on the box of cake mix, except reduce water to a half cup.
Add the can of pumpkin and the pumpkin pie spice.
Spread into greased 13 x 9-inch pan; bake as directed on the box of cake mix.
Let cool; add cinnamon to frosting and frost.
Decorate with candy pumpkins.

title: barbecue muffins
directions: Separate dough into 10 biscuits; flatten into 5-inch circles. Press each into the bottom and up side of greased muffin cup.
Set aside.
In a skillet, brown ground beef; drain.

title: applesauce
directions: Wash, peel, core and quarter apples.
Put them in saucepan; half cover with cold water.
Bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and let simmer until tender.
Stir in sugar and salt.
Cook 5 minutes more.
Mash apples with a spoon or force through a sieve. Chill.
If desired, a little lemon juice, cinnamon or nutmeg may be added after cooking.
Serves 6.

title: jello dessert
directions: Take juice from fruit and heat in saucepan. Dissolve into jello. Add same amount of cool water and stir. Stir in cool whip, fruit and cottage cheese. Chill till set.

title: chewy raisin walnut shortbread bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease an 8-inch square pan. Combine flour and 1/2 cup sugar using pastry blender or fork; cut in butter until mixture resembles fine meal.
Press into pan. Bake for 20 minutes or until edges are light gold.
Combine eggs, brown sugar and vanilla.
Beat well.
Stir in baking soda, walnuts, raisins and coconut.
Spoon over hot crust.
Spread to cover evenly.
Return to oven; bake 20 to 25 minutes or until top is set.
Cool completely.
Cut into 20 bars.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Place 3 cups of chopped lettuce in bottom of large bowl. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Layer egg slices over lettuce in bowl and sprinkle more salt and pepper. Continue to layer vegetables in this order: peas, remaining chopped lettuce, crumbled bacon and shredded cheese, along with light sprinkling of salt and pepper throughout layering. Combine mayonnaise and sugar and spread over top to cover entire salad to edge of bowl. Cover and chill 24 hours or at least overnight. Garnish with green onion and a little of paprika. Toss before serving. Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Combine sugar, sour cream and mix well.
Add coconut and flavoring.
Stir until all is mixed well.
Set aside.
Mix and bake cake mix as directed on box.
Poke holes in cake and frost cake while still warm.

title: peach pudding dessert
directions: Place peaches in an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Mix the next 4 ingredients; pour over peaches.
Pour melted margarine over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: sky high biscuits
directions: Combine flour, whole wheat flour, baking powder, salt and cream of tartar.
Cut in oleo.
Add egg mixture.
Knead lightly on floured board.
Roll or pat out.
Bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Grease a 10 x 1 1/2-inch pan. Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Add salt and pepper.
Spread in plate. Beat milk, Bisquick and eggs until smooth.
Pour into plate and bake 25 minutes at 400°.
Top with tomatoes and cheese.
Bake 5 to 8 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: chicken souffle(serves 8)
directions: Dice 4 slices bread - place in 9 x 13 baking dish.
Mix large pieces of chicken with mayonnaise, green pepper, celery and onions.
Spread over diced bread.
Trim crust off remaining slices of bread and place over the chicken mixture.
Beat eggs until frothy, add milk, pour over bread.
Place in refrigerator over night.
When ready to serve, bake at 325 for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven, pour soup on top and add grated cheese on top of soup. Shake generous amount of paprika on top.
Bake at 325 for 1 hour.

title: breakfast sausage casserole
directions: Lightly grease 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Tear bread into bite-sized pieces.
Place in bottom of dish.
Brown sausage; add onion and pepper.
Cook until tender and meat is done.
Drain and set aside.
Mix eggs, milk and seasonings.
Beat well.
Sprinkle sausage mixture over bread pieces.
Top with cheese; pour egg/milk mixture over all.
Cover and refrigerate at least 8 to 10 hours. Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes, uncovered, or until puffy or eggs are set.

title: steak with tomatoes
directions: Broil steak 10 minutes.
Turn.
Add tomato halves topped with mixture of bread crumbs, oregano, salt and pepper.
Broil 12 minutes.

title: chocolate oat cookies
directions: Mix the first four ingredients and boil hard for one minute. Remove from heat and add peanut butter, vanilla and rolled oats. Drop on wax paper and let cool.
Chopped nuts may be added.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Put into well-greased tube pan.
Melt butter and pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Could also add nuts if desired.

title: escalloped pineapple
directions: Mix pineapple and bread gently. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over bread cubes.
Pour into ungreased casserole and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Heat broiler.
Mix dressing, juice and seasoning mix.
Place chicken on rack of broiler pan.
Brush with half of the dressing mixture.
Broil 5 to 7-inches from heat 8 to 10 minutes.
Turn and brush with remaining dressing mixture.
Continue broiling 8 to 10 minutes or until tender. Serve with twisted breadsticks and black beans with chopped red pepper, if desired.
Makes 8 servings (or 4 servings with enough left to make Easy Chicken Enchiladas).

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Salt and brown pork chops that have been dipped in milk and rolled in flour.
They don't need to cook, just brown.
Slice potatoes; cut onion in small chips.

title: hot wings
directions: Fry or bake wings.
Dip wings in a thin batter.
After wings are done, place them in pan and spread hot sauce mixture over them.
Put in oven for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pia tropicale
directions: Whirl all ingredients in a blender until thick and smooth.

title: angel food pie filling
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Add sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add pineapple and water.
Cook in double boiler until thickened.
Fold in beaten egg whites while mixture is still hot.
Cool.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Cover with whipped cream; sprinkle with coconut or nuts.

title: oven french toast
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, melt margarine, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Place bread (double layer) on top of first 3 ingredients.
Beat together eggs; add milk and beat again.
Pour over bread.
Cover and place in refrigerator overnight.
Uncover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cut and invert on plates to serve.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour over chicken and simmer in oven for 1 hour or until chicken is done.
(This is good for other barbecued meats also.)

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well adding chips last.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Nuts may be added, if desired.
Bake at 375°.

title: apples with spiced ice cream
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a small bowl combine syrup and 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon.
Set aside.
Core apples, leaving bottoms intact.
Set apples upright in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Spoon half of syrup mixture (about 1 teaspoon) into each apple.
Pour water into baking pan at a depth of about 1-inch and bake until apples are tender, 20 to 30 minutes.
Using slotted spoon, transfer apples to serving plate.
Let cool for 10 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix chicken, chicken broth, soup, melted butter and Veg-All together.
Put into large casserole.
Mix the Bisquick and milk. Pour on top and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: kansas dirt cake
directions: You will need 1 flower pot and gummy worms.

title: family beans
directions: Cook beans until tender.
Dice onions; mince garlic.
Mix all ingredients and bake at 300° for 1 to 2 hours.

title: sweet nothings
directions: Melt the butterscotch chips, oleo and peanut butter in 2-quart microwave bowl until smooth.
Place the cereal and nuts in a large container or cookie sheet.
Pour chip mixture over cereal and nuts; toss well.
After cereal is coated, place 2 to 3 cups powdered sugar in large container or brown grocery poke (sack). Add coated cereal mixture to sugar and shake until all cereal is coated.
Place in a sealed container and serve as desired.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook rice, set
aside.
Cook rest of ingredients except butter and egg whites
(cook
until
thick).
After filling is cooked, add rice and butter.
Put
in baking dish and top with meringue made from
the
egg
whites and 10 tablespoons sugar. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes until meringue is browned.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Reserve 1 cup of corn chips.
Combine remaining chips with 1 2/3 cups cheese, chili, enchilada sauce, tomato sauce and onion mix.
Pour into 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Bake uncovered at 375° for 30 minutes or until hot.
Spread top of mixture with 1 cup sour cream.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup shredded cheese.
Circle reserved corn chips around edge.
Bake 5 minutes longer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken in boiling salted water until tender, about 45 to 60 minutes.
Cool and cut up in small pieces and add all ingredients except bacon.
Sprinkle bacon on top.
Chill.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: congealed salad
directions: Heat crushed pineapple until it boils; turn burner off.
Add the lime jello.
Cool and put in fridge until it starts to thicken.
Add the grated cheese, Cool Whip and pecans.

title: shaker rose water
directions: Add about 1/2 teaspoon rose water to a cup of applesauce or sprinkle rose water over fresh fruit salad.

title: chocolate balls
directions: Melt margarine and stir in all ingredients except peanut butter.
Add it last.
Mix well and roll into small balls and refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours.

title: coconut pie (crustless)
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add eggs one at a time, then add milk and flour.
Mix and then add coconut.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese-chive biscuits
directions: Mix flour and shortening until it resembles coarse crumbs.
Add milk, grated cheese and chives and work in extra flour until dough pulls from sides of bowl.
Roll out to 1/2-inch thick and cut with floured cutter.
Brush tops with melted butter.
Bake until golden brown at 425°, about 12 minutes.
Watch!

title: strawberry dumplings
directions: Bring strawberries, 10 oz. water and 1/2 cup sugar to boil. Lower heat and add dumplings, and cook until done.

title: molasses crinkles
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, egg, and molasses thoroughly.
Blend all dry ingredients; mix together.
Chill.
Heat oven to 375°. Roll dough in 1 1/4 balls.
Dip tops in sugar.
Place balls, sugar side up, 3 inches apart on greased baking sheet.
Sprinkle each with 2 or 3 drops of water.
Bake 10-12 minutes, or just until set but not hard.
(Do not over bake.)
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: cinnamon apple butter
directions: Put in crock-pot.
Cook on low until thick.
Put in jars and seal with lids.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Place all ingredients over pork chops in baking pan.
Bake 2 hours at 375°.
Stir vegetables after 1 hour.
Last 1/2 hour bring pork chops to top for browning.
Serve with mashed potatoes or rice, crusty Italian bread or rolls.
Enjoy!

title: heart smart artichokes
directions: Squeeze lemon juice into large pot of cold water.
Add lemon wedges, artichokes, onion, bay leaves and salt and pepper.
Allow to come to a boil, then cook at a simmer until artichokes are tender.
This is low-fat, low calorie and very flavorful.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix well amd form into balls, marble sized for cocktails or larger for dinner.
Fry in light oil, time depends on the size of the meatballs.
They should be brown on the outside and just cooked through on the inside.
Drain on paper towels.

title: breakfast biscuit mix
directions: Cut shortening into dry ingredients with pastry cutter or electric mixer on low speed.
Store in Tupperware 8 weeks or more.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix together shortening,
1 1/2 cups sugar and eggs.
Sift together and stir in flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Roll into balls.
Roll in sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: frozen waldorf salad
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, pineapple juice and salt and cook over low heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Cool and add celery, crushed pineapple, diced apples and walnuts.
Gently fold in whipped cream.
Spoon in an 8-inch square pan and freeze.

title: chicken chop suey
directions: Brown chicken in butter; add onion, stir occasionally. Dissolve cubes in hot water, add to chicken together with molasses and choy sauce.
Cover and cook on low about 20 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Add vegetables, bring up to simmer and cook 6 minutes longer.
Blend cornstarch dissolved in water into chop suey.
Cook until gravy is thickened.
Sprinkle almonds over chicken chop suey before serving.
Serve with cooked rice.

title: oriental beef and peppers
directions: Cut steak cross-grain into very thin slices.
Heat 10-inch browning dish in microwave on High for 3 minutes.
Add 3 tablespoons oil, bell peppers and onion; mix well.
Microwave, covered with glass lid, on High for 3 minutes, stirring once. Remove vegetables from browning dish; set aside.
Add 2 tablespoons oil and steak to browning dish; stir to coat well.
Arrange in even layer in browning dish.
Microwave 1 1/2 minutes.
Add mixture of soy sauce, water, cornstarch, ginger and pepper sauce; mix well. Add vegetables.
Microwave, covered, on High for 2 minutes, stirring once.
Serve over fluffy rice.
Yields 4 servings.

title: jiffy cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions.
Put it into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Cool.
Put instant pudding, cream cheese and 1 1/2 cups milk into bowl and beat well.
Put pudding mixture on cool cake; add drained pineapple over top, then add Cool Whip over the top of that.
Top with coconut, if desired.

title: chocolate scotcharo
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to a boil.
Remove from heat.

title: hot asparagus
directions: Trim crusts from bread and flatten slices slightly with a rolling pin.
Blend cheeses and egg to workable consistency and spread on each slice of bread.
Roll one asparagus spear in each slice of bread.
Use toothpicks to fasten edges.
Dip in butter to coat thoroughly.
Place on cookie sheet and freeze.
Cut each rolled slice into three pieces and store frozen.
When ready to serve, bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned, using a jelly roll pan.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Cook the rhubarb with the sugar for 7 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in the gelatin. Stir until dissolved.
Pour in glasses and seal.

title: hickory nut cake(recipe of miss ellen pugh, a past president)
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Alternate adding flour, which has been sifted twice with baking powder, with milk, then nuts and fold in beaten egg whites last.
Bake in well-greased tube pan. Bake in not too hot oven.
Try with straw after about 45 minutes. (I usually use just half the recipe.)

title: no bake banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding mix with milk; add sour cream and 1/2 Cool Whip. Layer dish with wafers and bananas and mix until all are used up. Put other half of Cool Whip on top and refrigerate.

title: saucy salmon cakes
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Grease muffin tins.
Spoon mixture in and bake.
Use undiluted cream of chicken soup or cheese sauce.

title: christmas strawberry cake
directions: Soften jello in half cup water.
Combine other ingredients and blend all together in an electric mixer for at least 4 minutes.
Bake in 3 (9-inch) pans for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli soup(4 servings)
directions: Place vegetables and broth in saucepan.
Bring to boil, reduce heat, cover and cook until vegetables are tender, about 8 minutes. Mix next 5 ingredients.
Add to cooked vegetables.
Cook, stirring constantly until soup is slightly thick and mixture begins to boil. Remove from heat.
Add cheese and stir until melted; 115 calories per cup.

title: red devil's food cake
directions: Stir shortening to soften.
Gradually add 1 cup of the sugar, creaming together until light.
Add salt and vanilla.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Combine cream cheese and Cheddar cheese, blending well. Stir in
remaining
ingredients, except pecans.
Shape into a ball
and roll in pecans.
Chill.
Serve at room temperature. Yield: about 3 cups.

title: mashed potato doughnuts
directions: Cream together oleo and sugar.
Add eggs, milk and mashed potatoes.
Beat and add sifted together flour, baking powder, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Dough will be sticky.
Roll or pat out on floured board and cut with doughnut cutter.
Fry in hot lard.

title: color red cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray 3 (9-inch) cake pans.
Bake 20 minutes or until done.
Cool. Frost, then refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.
Mix all ingredients together, except white vinegar.
Leave it until last, then mix it in.

title: orange-pineapple sherbet(club member: clint hudson)
directions: Mix all ingredients and freeze in ice tray.

title: pecan kisses
directions: Beat egg white until stiff (but not dry).
Add sugar, one tablespoon at a time.
Continue to beat.
Add pecans.
Drop by 1/2 teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for 30 minutes. Can be placed close together; they do not spread.

title: seven minute cabbage
directions: Heat the milk to boiling.
Add butter and cabbage.
Cook seven minutes.
Thicken with flour, mixed with a little cold water.

title: easy pickled beets
directions: Leave root and 1 inch of stem on beets; scrub with a brush. Place beets in a saucepan; add water to cover.
Bring to a boil, cover and cook 35 to 40 minutes or until tender.
Drain, reserving 2 1/2 cups liquid.
Pour cold water over beets.
Let set for about 5 minutes and drain.
Trim off roots and stems, then skin; set aside.

title: cream cheese salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple.
Add water, if necessary, to make cup.
Add 1/2 cup sugar to juice; dissolve by heating.
Do not boil.
Warm just enough to dissolve.

title: savory fresh pole beans
directions: Remove tips from beans and cut in half.
Heat oil in saucepan. Peel garlic and cook in hot oil until golden.
Remove garlic and discard.
Add onion.
Cook slowly for 3 minutes.
Add beans, salt, basil, sugar and water.
Cover and cook slowly for 15 minutes or until beans are crisp-tender.
Serve hot.
Yields 6 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put into a greased baking dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: good sauce for hot dogs
directions: Saute 1 stalk celery and 1 small onion until tender.
Add rest of ingredients.
Add water if too thick.
Simmer with 6 to 10 hog dogs for 45 minutes.

title: green rice
directions: After rice and broccoli are cooked to your taste, combine remaining ingredients and add broccoli and rice mixture.
Put in 2-quart casserole sprayed with Pam.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over top.
Bake at 400° until bubbly or about 20 minutes.

title: spiced pecan pie
directions: Combine eggs, syrup, sugar, vanilla and salt; mix well.
Blend spices with melted butter; add to egg mixture.
Mix well.
Combine pecans with flour; stir into egg mixture.
Turn into pastry shells.
Bake in a 400° oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and continue to bake for 40 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Makes 3 (9-inch) pies.

title: easy poppy seed coffee cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Pour into a well-greased Bundt pan.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes. This is good by itself or served with cream cheese.

title: cabbage and beef soup
directions: In a Dutch oven, brown beef.
Add all remaining ingredients, except parsley.
Bring to a boil and simmer, covered, for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Add parsley when almost done cooking.

title: impossible pie
directions: Put all ingredients in a blender for 1 minute.
Bake at 350° in greased and floured pie pan for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: company potatoes
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Add soup, potatoes and sour cream. Spoon into a greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Combine cheese and corn flakes; spread over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: banana crunch pops
directions: You will need 15 wooden sticks.
Place yogurt in a shallow dish.
Insert a wooden stick into each banana piece.
Roll banana pieces in the yogurt, covering the entire piece of banana.
Place the cereal in a small, shallow dish.
Roll the banana pieces in the cereal.
After coating with cereal, place banana pieces on a waxed paper-lined baking sheet.
Place in the freezer.
When frozen, wrap each in freezer wrap and label.
Store in freezer. Let stand at room temperature for 10 minutes before serving. Makes 15 pops.

title: winter vegetable soup
directions: In a soup kettle, cook onions in butter until they are tender and golden.
Stir in ground beef and garlic and cook the mixture (separating beef with a fork) until it is browned.
Add beef stock, tomatoes, potatoes, celery, green beans and carrots.
Then add rest of ingredients.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown onion and hamburger; add salt and pepper.
Then add can of drained green beans and tomato soup (do not dilute soup).
Put in casserole dish.
Boil potatoes; when done, mash and add 1/2 cup warm milk, 1 beaten egg, salt and pepper.
Spoon over meat.
Bake covered for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
While
cake bakes, simmer sugar and pineapple. Remove cake from
oven;
punch
holes
in
cake
with fork and cover with pineapple
and
cool.
Mix
pudding
as directed on box; add coconut
and
spread over pineapple.
Cover with Cool Whip;
sprinkle with nuts.

title: nighty nites
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Gradually add 2/3 cups sugar, then stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on foil lined cookie sheet about 1 inch apart.
Put in preheated 300° oven and immediately turn heat off.
Do not open until completely cool.

title: pineapple punch
directions: Mix all together.
Fill with crushed ice.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Remove bones and skin from breasts; cut breasts into halves. Place chicken between 2 pieces plastic wrap.
Pound with mallet until 1/4 inch thick.
Place 1 slice each ham and cheese on each piece chicken.
Roll up carefully, beginning at narrow end; secure with wooden picks.
Mix flour, salt, & pepper; coat rolls with flour mixture.
Dip into egg, roll in bread crumbs.
tags: thin slices fully cooked smoked ham

title: potato cheese casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in flat casserole (not a deep casserole).
Store in refrigerator at least 4 hours or overnight. Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pepper sauce
directions: You will also need sterilized jars, lids and rings.

title: caramel pie
directions: Put 3/4 cup granulated sugar in iron skillet on low heat. Cook until sugar is melted and browned.
Add sugar and flour together, then add enough milk to wet the sugar mixture.
Add well beaten egg yolks, then the remaining milk.
Add salt and browned sugar.
Cook in saucepan until mixture is thick.
Add vanilla and butter, then pour into pre-cooked pie shell.

title: fast noodles
directions: In a large mixing bowl mix all the ingredients except noodles.
Cook noodles according to directions on the package. Drain them and mix noodles and tuna mixture together.
Put in a lightly greased baking dish, top with crushed potato chips, and bake in oven at 350°F for about 45 minutes.

title: can't fail pie crust
directions: Work
together	flour,	salt,
baking powder and Crisco just as	you
make any other crust.
Add the cold water.
Roll out on floured
surface
and
place in pie pan and bake until brown.

title: egg dish for a large group
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Put bread cubes in pan.
Melt butter and cheese in double boiler.
Pour over bread cubes.
Add extra ingredients at this point.
Beat eggs and milk.
Pour over bread. Let stand in refrigerator at least 20 to 24 hours.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour, uncovered.
May be served hot or cold and can also be reheated.

title: chicken pot pie with frozen vegetables
directions: Cook chicken in a minimum of water.
When cooked, take out of water to cool.
Cook vegetables and reserve about 3/4 cup liquid to add to soup.
Be sure to keep soup thick and not watery.
Mix boned chicken, vegetables and soup to which the liquid has been added.
Put mixture in pie crust, topping with second pie crust. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until crust is brown.

title: granny's pound cake
directions: Cream butter or margarine, Crisco and sugar thoroughly with electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Add flour and milk alternately; add vanilla and nuts.
Stir with spoon to mix.
Pour into a well greased and floured tube pan. Place in a cold oven.
Turn oven on to
Bake for 1 hour 15 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Remove cake from tube pan when cooled.

title: carrot and cheese dish
directions: Combine carrots with drained onions; add salt. Add cubed cheese and dot with margarine. Spread crushed Pringles on top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O according to directions using 1/4 cup less water. Add undrained pineapple and grated carrot. Chill and serve.

title: hawaiian meatballs
directions: Mix together first 7 ingredients and shape into balls.
Brown in 1 tablespoon shortening and cook thoroughly.
Remove from frypan and drain fat.
Mix together soup, vinegar and soy sauce. Add cornstarch and sugar.
Pour into frypan.
Heat, stirring constantly, until bubbly for 1 minute.
Add meatballs, pineapple and pepper.
Heat through.
Serve with rice or Rice-A-Roni.

title: chihuahua(lamesa favorite)
directions: Fry meat and 1/2 of onion until done; drain excess grease off. Add chili powder, garlic salt and pepper.
Add the water.
Boil until little juice is left.
Fry corn tortillas in hot oil until crispy; drain on paper towels.
Spread cheese on one side of tortilla.
Layer meat, onion and cabbage on top of cheese.
Put more cheese on one side of another tortilla to make top of sandwich.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix fruits and add 1 large instant vanilla pudding.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: grandma's chicken soup
directions: Put cut up chicken in a heavy pot or stock pot.
Cover with water.
Add celery, onion, peppercorns and parsley.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and skim foam on top.
Simmer halfway covered for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool slightly.
Remove chicken and strain broth. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Remove chicken from bone and chop. Add 2 cups of chopped chicken to strained broth (reserving rest of another use).
Stir in vermicelli noodles, simmer 15 minutes. Beat eggs with juice of 1 lemon.
Add a little of hot soup mixture (so mix won't curdle).
Pour egg mix into stock pot.
Mix well, heat and serve.

title: stretch-a-tuna salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Stir lightly.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: koliscky cookie
directions: Mix together.
Divide in half and chill.
Roll out to 1/4-inch and cut with cutter.
Place 1/2 teaspoon jelly in center of each cookie.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Blend
together
eggs, oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla with portable mixer.
Add remaining ingredients and beat well. Bake in loaf pans, at
350° for 1 hour or until done.
May add nuts or raisins.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Bake in greased iron skillet at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Combine softened butter with grated cheese; work together. Mix salt, paprika and flour, then work into cheese mixture.
Allow to chill.
Put olive or date in the middle of a small piece of flattened dough.
Dough should be pressed around olive or date until the center is completely covered.
Place on greased cookie sheet; allow to freeze (6 hours).
Pack in airtight container; save for later use.
Cook at 400° for 15 minutes on bottom rack (close together).
Makes 25 to 30.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes in half of broth.
Boil until potatoes are soft. Mash to desired consistency while in broth.
Add remaining broth, cooked bacon with drippings and spinach.

title: honey-dijon chicken
directions: Brown chicken in skillet about 10 to 15 minutes in oil.
Add butter and leeks; saute with chicken until leeks are tender.
Take out chicken; set aside.
Add wine, salt, pepper and mustard.
Stir and cook on medium heat for about 1 to 2 minutes.
Add whipping cream; stir constantly for about 1 to 2 minutes (sauce should be smooth).
Pour sauce over chicken; sprinkle chopped tomato on top.

title: party ham roll-ups
directions: Soften cream cheese and spread on slices of ham.
Lay green onion blade on edge and roll up (the onion blade will be in the center).
Leave in refrigerator or until thoroughly cooled, then slice 1/4 or larger slice and place cut side upon plate.
Very pretty to use at Christmastime.

title: mushroom rolls
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter until soft.
Blend in flour, salt and m.s.g.
Stir in cream.
Cook until thick.
Add chives and lemon juice.
Cool.

title: lee's chili
directions: Saute onions until translucent; brown ground beef.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 4 hours.

title: turkey rice casserole
directions: Roast turkey.
Cool, bone and cut into small bite size pieces. To turkey broth add garlic salt, seasoned pepper, thyme, onion, spinach, turkey meat and rice.
Add enough water to a little more than cover rice.
Cook until rice is just done (10 to 20 minutes). Add soup, mix well.
Put grated cheese on top.

title: dixie pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in oil.
Sprinkle with salt and sage.
Place in a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with apple rings and brown sugar.

title: scalloped cabbage
directions: Boil cabbage in water with salt and pepper.
Drain off water; pour into greased baking dish a layer of cabbage, then a layer of cheese and cream of mushroom soup.
Continue adding layers until ingredients are used.
Cover top with cracker crumbs which may be mixed with a little melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until top is brown.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Christianity is bread for daily use, not cake for special occasions.

title: beef-mac bake
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese according to directions.
Brown ground beef; drain.
In a baking dish, pour prepared macaroni and cheese in the bottom.
Make sure the bottom is covered.
Pour ground beef on top.
Add spaghetti sauce on top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix together and serve with Ritz crackers and cocktail sauce.

title: fudge chew
directions: Using first four ingredients, bring to boil and boil slowly for 4 minutes.
Add peanut butter, oatmeal and vanilla.
Stir together and pour into 2 buttered 12 x 18-inch pans.
When cool, cut into squares.

title: homemade french dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl and beat with mixer until sugar is dissolved.
Store in refrigerator.
Use on salad.

title: crostini(appetizers)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Slice bread into 1/2-inch thick slices. Arrange on a baking sheet; bake until edges are golden, 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool and store at room temperature in plastic bags until time to serve.
Can be made up to a week in advance.
Makes 24.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Stir boiling water into oats and let stand 20 minutes before making batter.

title: orange crunchies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
Put into bowl soft shortening.
Add sugar gradually, mixing well until light and fluffy.
Add egg and beat hard.
Stir in about half of flour mixture.
Stir in milk.
Add the remaining flour and mix well.
Fold in corn flakes, nuts and orange rind.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased baking sheet about 2 inches apart.
Bake on oven rack slightly above center at 325° for 15 minutes or until light brown.
Watch closely while baking.
Remove from oven baking sheet at once.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: new england boiled kielbasa dinner
directions: Combine sausage
and
vegetables
in
large Dutch oven. Add water, bay leaf, garlic and caraway seed; bring to a boil. Cover; reduce heat and simmer 45 minutes, until vegetables are tender. Remove bay leaf
and
garlic.
Arrange
sausage
and vegetables on platter.
Sprinkle
with
parsley.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: diabetic fruit salad
directions: Mix 1 1/2 cups pineapple juice with pudding mix and pour over fruit mixture.
One-half cup equals 1 serving.

title: banana muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
Beat sugar and oil together in mixing bowl. Beat in eggs, one at a time, blending well after each.
Stir in mashed bananas.
Add dry ingredients all at once, stirring just enough to moisten.
Spoon batter into muffin pan cups that have been sprayed with cooking spray, filling 2/3 full.
Bake for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix well and bake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: butter pecan dream
directions: Mix this and pat into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes; let cool.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Drain salmon; reserve 2 tablespoons of liquid.
Flake salmon. Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Shape into a loaf in a greased baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings. Or, shape into patties and fry.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: Make noodles 8 to 10 minutes.
Make spinach (defrost ahead of time).
Saute carrots and mushrooms in oil until soft, crisp and tender.
Stir in tomato sauce, paste, olives and oregano.

title: gram's cottage pudding(to serve over plain yellow cake)
directions: Mix cocoa, flour, sugar and salt in top of double boiler. Heat milk in another pan.
Add a little hot milk to dry ingredients to make paste.
Slowly add rest of milk.
Place over boiling water in double boiler.
Stir until thick.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.
Serve over yellow cake.

title: cream scones
directions: Beat together buttermilk, egg and sugars.
Sift 3 cups flour with baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add 2/3 flour mixture to buttermilk and stir well.
Gradually add butter; incorporate thoroughly into mixture.
Stir in rest of flour mixture and currants; may need to add more flour.
Turn dough onto lightly floured board; knead several minutes.
Divide into 3 parts, each a circle 4 to 5-inches across.
Cut into quarters and arrange on buttered cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 12 scones.

title: cheese cookies
directions: Melt
butter
and pour over cheese mixture.
Add a dash or two of
Tabasco
sauce.
Mix and form into balls.
Cook at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Stir cranberries with a fork as they mix with boiling water easier.
Add juice to water to make 1 1/2 cups and add remaining ingredients.

title: sponge cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: my moms meat loaf
directions: Soak bread crumbs in milk.
Mix in ground beef, onion, salt, egg and 1/2 cup barbecue sauce.
Shape into loaf and place in baking dish sprayed with cooking spray (for best results, use 13x9-inch glass cookware).
Mix remaining barbecue sauce with water and pour 1/2 of sauce/water mixture over loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Baste with remaining sauce/water mixture.

title: zucchini-cheddar bread
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease and flour round pan (9 x 1 1/2-inches).
Cook and stir onions in oleo until tender.
Cool slightly.
Mix onions, Bisquick, parsley, basil, thyme, milk and eggs.
Beat 1 minute.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spread in pan.
Bake about 40 minutes.
Cool slightly before removing from pan.

title: 10 minute microwave peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar and karo.
Cook on HI for 2 1/2 minutes,... stir and cook 2 1/2 minutes,...stir.
Add 1 3/4 cups peanuts. Cook on HI 2 1/2 minutes,...stir and cook 2 1/2 minutes or until light brown (a light caramel color).
Remove from the microwave and add butter, baking soda, and vanilla.
Stir rapidly.
Spread thinly on buttered cookie sheet to cool.

title: charlotte's easy lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add spaghetti sauce and water. Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
In 9 x 13-inch pan, layer 1/3 of sauce; next 1/2 lasagna noodles (uncooked), 1/3 of cheeses (that have been shredded and mixed together).
Repeat layers, ending with sauce, then cheese on top.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Remove foil and let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Precook bacon slices; drain on paper towel.
Crumble into pastry shell with cheese.
Beat eggs and light cream slightly. Add salt and chives.
Pour over bacon and cheese in shell.
Bake 15 minutes at 425°.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake 30 minutes. Knife will come out clean when tested as you would test custard. Let stand 10 minutes.
Cut in wedges and serve.

title: milnot cheese cake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add lemon juice and cool. Cream together cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Add cooled gelatin mixture, mix well.
Fold whipped Milnot into gelatin.
Crush graham crackers fine and add margarine.
Firmly pack 2/3 of mixture in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan, add filling and sprinkle crumbs on top.
Chill several hours.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Sift flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt into a mixing bowl. Cream sugar and Crisco together.
Add beaten eggs and vanilla to Crisco mixture.
Gradually add the flour mixture. Beat well. Chill bowl of cookie dough for easy handling.
Roll dough out to 1/8-inch thick.
Place cookies on greased cookie sheet. Sprinkle cookies with sugar and cinnamon mix.
Bake in 375° oven for 10 minutes.

title: whole wheat banana bread
directions: Cream Crisco, sugar and eggs.
Stir in bananas; add to dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: carrot cookies
directions: Cream first 5 ingredients together.
Sift dry ingredients together and stir into creamed mixture.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix all
together,
fry fritters in small amount of hot oil. Use 1 tablespoon batter for each fritter.
Brown on both sides, drain on paper towel.

title: sweet cooking chocolate
directions: Mix cocoa and sugar with Crisco.
This equals one 4 ounce bar sweet cooking chocolate.

title: pineapple ritz casserole
directions: Mix pineapple and cheese together.
Next, mix sugar, flour and pineapple juice together and combine with pineapple and cheese. Melt margarine and mix with crushed Ritz crackers.
Sprinkle over cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, about 25 minutes.

title: minty cocoa mousse
directions: In a saucepan, combine cocoa and milk until smooth. Add mints and butter; cook and

stir over low heat until smooth. Cool for 15 minutes. Stir in 1 cup whipped topping and vanilla. Fold in the remaining whipped topping. Spoon into dessert dishes. Refrigerate until serving. Garnish with mint and whipped topping, if desired. Yield: 4 servings.

title: candy nut roll
directions: Cook together sugar, dates and milk until mixture forms a soft ball when dropped in cold water (236°).
Remove from heat; set pan in bowl of cold water and cool to lukewarm.
Add chopped nuts and butter.
Beat until thick and entirely cold.
Turn onto board dusted thickly with powdered sugar and knead until it will mold well.
Roll into a long cylinder, about 1-inch in diameter and let stand 24 hours.
When wanted, cut into slices.

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Layer graham cracker crumbs over, then chocolate chips, coconut, nuts and Eagle Brand milk.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: chicken salad with almonds
directions: Toss chicken and celery together.
Mix onion, lemon juice, mayonnaise and cream.
Add to chicken and toss until chicken and celery are coated.
Season with salt and pepper and stir in almonds.
Chill.
Serves 5.

title: honey bars
directions: Mix and press into cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: mammah mccomas' pie dough
directions: Sift together the flour, sugar and salt.
Mix together the egg, water and vinegar.
Mix with flour mixture.
Cut into this mixture the Crisco.
Refrigerate until cold.
May be stored in tightly closed container for a couple of weeks.

title: paper cup salad
directions: Combine sour cream, lemon juice, salt, drained pineapple and banana pieces.
Lightly fold in nuts and cherries.
Spoon into fluted paper cups that have been placed into muffin tins; freeze. Remove from freezer about 15 minutes before serving.
Peel off paper cups and place on lettuce.
May freeze for 1 month.
Keep in freezer in plastic bag.

title: baked corn
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar, milk, salt and flour.
Add mixture to corn.
Bake at 350° approximately 45 minutes, until set.

title: aunt mary's tuna melts
directions: Prepare tuna as your favorite tuna salad mixture.
Spread tuna mix over open sandwich rolls.
Place tomato slice over tuna mixture.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: Mix vanilla wafers, nuts, raisins and fruit.
Add milk and mix well. Press into mold.
Let set at least 1 week before cutting.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Put all ingredients in blender.
Beat until smooth.

title: mark's coconut battered chicken
directions: Break and whip eggs.
Add milk and continue whipping.
Add flour and salt; whip until a smooth batter is formed.
Add coconut and sugar.
Mix in well.
Let batter set for at least 1 hour before using.
(Keep cool.)
Pound out chicken with meat mallet so it is uniform in thickness.
Dip chicken into batter and fry in oil at 350°.
Brown one side, then turn and brown other side.

title: herb roasted chicken
directions: On waxed paper, combine flour, sage and thyme.
Coat chicken lightly with flour mixture.
In skillet over medium high heat in hot margarine, cook chicken 10 minutes or until browned on both sides, put chicken to one side.
Stir in soup and water, stirring to loosen brown bits.
Reduce heat to low, cover, simmer 5 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender.
Garnish with fresh thyme if desired.

title: irish bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt and set aside.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten egg and buttermilk and blend well.
Add liquid mixture to dry ingredients.
Mix the rest by hand only until ingredients are moistened.
Fold in raisins.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart glass casserole.
Brush top with melted butter and sprinkle with a little sugar.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Reduce to 325° and bake about 30 minutes longer. Test middle of loaf before removing from oven.
Cool completely.

title: colby-swiss cheese soup
directions: Cut stalks into small bite size pieces.
In large saucepan, combine the water and granules.
Heat to boiling.
Add carrots and broccoli.
Cover and cook about 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Drain, reserving liquid.
If necessary, add enough water to the liquid to equal 1/2 cup.
Set liquid and vegetables aside.

title: tacos
directions: In a heavy skillet, cook onions and garlic in 3 tablespoons of oil until soft.
Add beef.
Cook, stirring until lightly browned and crumbly.
Drain off excess fat.
Add seasonings.
Moisten with a little tomato sauce.
Heat until flavors are blended.
Keep hot. Cook tortillas.
Fill tortillas with meat, onions, tomatoes, lettuce and cheese.
Top with taco sauce and sour cream.

title: bacon cheddar appetizers
directions: Preheat broiler. Mix all ingredients except crackers until well blended. Place crackers on baking sheet. Top each cracker with about 1 teaspoon of the cheese mixture. Broil about 2 minutes or until cheese is melted. Yield: 16 servings.

title: sandwich surprise
directions: Mix bacon, pecans and bell peppers together.
Add enough mayonnaise to bind the mixture together and make it spreadable on bread.
Portions can vary according to the individual.
Yields 10 to 12 sandwiches.

title: kisses
directions: Mix butter, milk and sugar.
Then add soda and enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Drop on cookie sheets.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and bake in a
hot oven.

title: real coffee - louisiana style
directions: You will need an old-fashioned drip coffee pot, not electric.

title: emporium walnut pie
directions: Boil sugar, water and salt together until syrup reaches 235° on candy thermometer.
Add butter and boil until bubbles are yellow. Cool to room temperature.
Add vanilla and eggs; beat good.
Place walnuts in the bottom of a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Pour mixture over walnuts and bake at 325° for 55 minutes.
This is a great pie for a hostess gift.
Keeps well and is practically indistructable.

title: curried cauliflower cheese pie
directions: Mix together the potatoes and butter.
Cool slightly.
Stir in chives and flour.
Press into a 9-inch pie plate to make a crust. Bake for 5 minutes in a preheated 350° oven.
Remove and cool. Trim and wash cauliflower; steam above water until tender, not mushy.
Beat eggs with 1 1/2 cups of the cheese, then stir in curry powder, cauliflower and salt.
Pour into the cooled crust; top with remaining cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes, or until set.

title: basic graham cracker crust
directions: Crush the graham crackers by placing squares on wax paper and rolling over them with a rolling pin.
Place all the ingredients and mix with a fork until moistened. Press into a pie pan that has been sprayed with a nonfat cooking spray.
Makes 1 (8 or 9-inch) crust.
Has 44 calories, 1 g fat, 0 mg cholesterol.

title: skillet lasagna
directions: Brown meat; drain grease.
Sprinkle half the sauce mix over meat.
Spoon on cottage cheese.
Put cooked noodles on top, one layer across skillet.
Sprinkle with remaining sauce mix, basil and parsley.
Mix tomatoes, tomato sauce and 1 cup water.
Pour over ingredients in skillet.
Cover and cook 40 to 45 minutes. Add cheese and cook until melted.

title: christmas coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together flour, soda and salt; set aside.
Combine all remaining ingredients and mix well.
Stir in flour mixture.
Spread in a buttered 8-inch square baking pan. Bake 40 to 45 minutes until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Let set 10 minutes; cut into squares.
Sift over powdered sugar and serve.

title: rocky road fudge variation
directions: Microwave chocolate and milk in 1 1/2-quart microwavable bowl on High 2 minutes, stirring after 1 minute.
Stir until chocolate is completely melted and smooth.
Stir in vanilla, salt, walnuts and miniature marshmallows.
Spread in greased 8 x 4-inch or 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Refrigerate until firm, about 2 hours.
Cut into small squares.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: peanut balls
directions: Mix all together. Dip in chocolate.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Melt chocolate bar in top of double boiler over warm water. Mix chocolate into 2/3 of the topping.
Pour into crust.
Use remaining topping for top of pie.
Chill.

title: spanish chicken
directions: Spread tamales on bottom of rectangle baking dish.
Layer remaining ingredients in order given.
Bake in 325° oven for about 25 minutes.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: Melt stick of butter.
Add soups and sour cream. Remove from heat.
Add hash browns.
Put in
a 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: congo bars
directions: Cream sugar and eggs.
Add oil.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir in the chocolate chips and nuts.
Spread in a large cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: dad's cookies
directions: Mix together and roll into balls.
Place on cookie sheet and press with fork.
Bake in 375° oven for 12 minutes.

title: granny simonson's potato soup
directions: Simmer for 1 hour until all vegetables have cooked well done. Add water while cooking for the broth.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients and form ball. Chill before serving.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.

title: chicken spaghetti casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together with approximately 1 c. of cheese. Top with 1 1/2 c. of cheese.
Bake at 350 degrees until bubbly.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 9-inch glass dish.
Mix flour, sugar and milk together and pour over melted margarine (do not mix).
Pour peaches in middle of batter (do not mix).
Bake at 400° for about 20 to 25 minutes.
Delicious!
May substitute any canned sweetened fruit or if using pie filling, use only half the sugar.
Serve with whipped topping or ice cream.

title: seven layer casserole
directions: Arrange the ingredients in layers in order given.
Cook, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover.
Bake for 15 minutes more.

title: cranberry apple cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Mix apples, 1 1/4 cups sugar, cranberries, tapioca, cinnamon and water in large saucepan. Let stand 5 minutes. Stirring constantly, cook on medium heat until mixture comes to full boil. Pour into 2-quart baking dish. Dot with 2 tablespoons butter. Mix flour, 2 tablespoons sugar, baking powder and salt in large bowl. Cut in 1/4 cup butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Stir in milk until soft dough forms. Drop dough by tablespoonfuls onto hot apple mixture. Bake 30 minutes or until topping is golden brown. Serve warm with whipped topping, if desired. Makes 8 servings.

title: pink salad
directions: Dump everything in a large bowl.
Mix well with electric mixer.
Pour into 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan or bowl.
Freeze and cut in squares or eat unfrozen.

title: strawberry muffins
directions: In mixing bowl, stir flour, sugar, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Make a well in center.
Combine eggs, oil and buttermilk; pour all at once into well.
Stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not over mix; fold in jam.
Bake in well-greased muffin tins at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: pear relish
directions: Grind pears, peppers and onions; drain well.
Bring to boil the salt, turmeric, mustard seed, celery seed, dry mustard, vinegar and sugar.
Add pears, peppers and onions.
Boil 25 to 30 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: You will need a punch bowl.

title: sweet and tasty baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients in casserole dish (except bacon).
Cook bacon 1/2 way to help get rid of some of the grease.
Then put bacon on top of beans.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: raw vegetable dip
directions: Mix well.
Serve with raw vegetables, crackers, chips, etc.

title: chicken rolls
directions: Mix together chicken, onions, mushrooms and cream cheese. Stuff rolls. Dip rolls in melted butter.
Roll in dry bread dressing mix, then bake as instructed on roll container.

title: coconut kisses
directions: Beat egg whites and sugar.
Fold in corn flakes, nutmeats and coconut.
Add vanilla.
Drop from teaspoon onto well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) 15 to 20 minutes. Place pans on damp towel; remove cookies immediately with spatula. If cookies stick to pan, return to oven to soften.
Granulated sugar may be substituted for brown sugar.

title: eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding, confectioners sugar and milk.
Add Cool Whip and whip for 2 minutes. Cover bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with layer of graham crackers.
Pour half of the pudding mix over the crackers. Add second layer of graham crackers.
Pour remaining pudding mix on top.
Add third layer of graham crackers.
Frost the third layer.
Refrigerate overnight, then ready to eat.

title: double chocolate brownies
directions: In small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.
In small saucepan, combine butter, sugar and water; bring just to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add 6 ounces chocolate chips and vanilla.
Stir until melted and mixture is smooth.
Transfer to a large bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Gradually blend in flour mixture.
Stir in remaining 6 ounces chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour into greased 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake at 325° 40 to 45 minutes.

title: impossible broccoli 'n cheddar pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate (10 x 1 1/2-inch).
Rinse broccoli under running cold water to thaw, drain thoroughly.
Mix broccoli, 2 cups cheese and onion in plate.
Beat milk, eggs, baking mix, salt and pepper until smooth, 15 seconds in blender on high.
Pour into plate.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, 25 to 35 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake until cheese is melted, 1 to 2 minutes longer.
Cool 5 minutes. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: toffee butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg, vanilla and flour.
Spread in a small jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Place Hershey bars on top.
Let melt and spread.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Cut when cool, but not cold.

title: chourico stew
directions: Remove skin from meat; break meat apart with fingers into bite sizes.
Set aside.
Peel and cube potatoes, bite size; set aside. Peel and chop onion and garlic.
In stew pot, saute onion and garlic in the olive oil and water.
When onion is transparent, add chourico and linguica.
Add water to cover meat.
Cook 20 minutes. Add water as needed.
Add seasonings to taste.
Add potatoes. When potatoes are cooked, add the peas (liquid from peas also). Remove from heat.
Serve with bread.

title: allie's chocolate peanut buddy bars
directions: Beat peanut butter and butter until smooth.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla and beat.
Blend in flour and salt.
Stir in 1 cup chocolate chips.
Spread in ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Immediately sprinkle remaining chips.
After 5 minutes, spread.

title: beer steak
directions: Brown steak in large nonstick frying pan; add beer, vinegar and seasoning and cook over slow heat until liquid becomes thick sauce and meat is cooked through.

title: rice and mushroom casserole
directions: Saute onions, celery, pepper and mushrooms until lightly browned.
Brown rice separately.
Add chicken soup to rice and dilute it as directed on soup can and cook until rice is done. Combine all ingredients in covered casserole and bake in low oven (about 200°) for 2 hours.

title: zada's meatballs
directions: Form into balls.
Fry on all sides until brown.
Place in baking dish.
Cover with cream of mushroom soup, diluted with water.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate cream cheese frosting
directions: Melt chocolate in saucepan over low heat stirring constantly. Cool.
Cream butter and cream cheese and add 1 c. powdered sugar, chocolate, whipping cream and vanilla, beating well at low speed. Add remaining sugar and beat until thick.

title: pickled beets
directions: Remove beet tops; leave 1 inch stem and roots.
Wash beets. Cook in boiling water until tender.
Drain; retain 1 cup liquid. Peel, cutting off top and roots.
Slice or dice beets.
In saucepan, combine 1 cup liquid, vinegar, sugar, salt and spices. Tie spices of cloves and cinnamon in a cheesecloth bag.
Heat ingredients to boiling.
Add beets and onions; simmer for 5 minutes.
Remove from burner and can.
Process 5 minutes in canner.

title: cottage cheese snacks
directions: Cream oleo.
Add cottage cheese and flour.
Mix until holds together like pastry.
Make into 1 to 2-inch balls.
Roll out in powdered sugar.
Spread any kind of preserves or jelly on pastry. Roll up; dip in egg whites, then nuts.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: fresh broccoli and pasta combo
directions: In skillet, saute onion and garlic in butter with bouillon until tender.
Remove from heat; stir in flour.
Gradually blend in water and lemon juice.
Cook over medium heat until thickened. Blend in sour cream. Stir in broccoli and macaroni and lemon peel; heat until steaming.
Makes 4 servings (5 1/2 cups).

title: gelatin jigglers for snacks
directions: Do not add cold water.

title: black-eyed pea corn bread
directions: Brown sausage and onion.
Mix Korn-Kit, oil, eggs, buttermilk, corn, chilies, peas and cheese.
Add meat.
Pour into greased 11 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Serve with salad.

title: beefy mexican lasagna
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Add canned tomatoes and taco seasoning. Simmer for 5 minutes.
Stir in 1/2 can fried onions.
In bowl, combine cottage cheese and 1 cup Cheddar cheese.
Place 3 tortillas on bottom of 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Overlap 6 tortillas on sides of baking dish.
Spoon meat mixture evenly. Top with 3 tortillas, then cheese mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and onions. Bake another 5 minutes.
Before serving, arrange tomatoes and lettuce over casserole.

title: kay's shadywood showdown chili
directions: Heat 1 Tbsp. oil in large skillet over medium heat.
Add half the onions an bell peppers and saute until onions are translucent. Add salt, pepper and garlic powder.
In a separate skillet, brown meat, leaving in chunks; drain fat.

title: banana cupcakes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large mixer bowl place flour, bananas, sugar, eggs, oil, baking soda, vanilla and salt and mix at low speed.
Beat until blended.
Fill paper liners 2/3 full. Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until toothpick comes clean.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Place broth, bouillon, salt, dill, onion powder and pepper in a 2-quart saucepan.
Cook until boiling.

title: muddy buddy
directions: Pour Chex into bowl.
Melt peanut butter, chips and vanilla until smooth.
Pour over Chex, mix until coated.
Put all ingredients into large Ziploc bag.
Shake until Chex are coated with confectioners sugar.
And there you have it!

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Drain pineapple; reserve 1/4 cup juice.
In a 9-inch skillet, with heatproof handle, heat juice, 1 tablespoon of butter and 1/2 cup sugar.
Arrange pineapple, cherries and nuts in skillet.
In bowl, with electric mixer, beat remaining butter and sugar with eggs.
Stir in flour, baking powder, salt, milk and vanilla until smooth.
Spoon into skillet; bake 45 to 50 minutes. Invert onto serving plate.

title: north dakota zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two loaf pans.
Mix all well and bake one hour at 350° or until toothpick comes out clean.
Makes two loaves.

title: my friend kitty's crab casserole
directions: Saute onion in a small amount of butter or oil.
Mix all of the ingredients together, except bread crumbs, parsley and paprika.
Pour into a casserole and top with the bread crumbs, parsley and paprika.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Let sit 30 minutes after baking before serving.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Mix together and top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: veal parmigiana
directions: With a meat hammer, pound the veal until it is extremely thin and then cut it into 6 equal pieces.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix well. Grease tube pan and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken okra gumbo
directions: Cut up chicken; cover with flour, salt and pepper.
Fry until brown.
Then fry okra with tomato and onion in the shortening. Make a roux in heavy skillet with grease from fried chicken and flour; brown roux.
Add fried chicken and vegetables.
Stir for a few minutes; add water.
