Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cook for about 2 hours.
Serves 6.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix together and heat in microwave for 10 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Blend well.
Serve hot with nacho chips.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix and roll in chopped nuts.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Blend the cocoa and water together and let cool.
Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Stir in flour alternately with the milk.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Spread in a greased 10 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: spicy tomato-fish chowder
directions: Heat the olive oil over moderate heat; add the garlic, tomatoes, basil, oregano, cayenne pepper and wine.
Cook, uncovered, for 10 minutes. Add the water. Cover and bring to a simmer, about 3 minutes.
Mix in the cod and shrimp and cook, uncovered, about 5 minutes longer.
Ladle into bowls and add a tablespoon or two of fresh crab meat.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: raisin oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat sugars, shortening, egg, water and vanilla together. Then
add
all
other
ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: layered bean dip
directions: Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Seal with plastic wrap. Serve with Doritos or corn chips.

title: tequila berry salad
directions: Chop lettuce, cauliflower and red cabbage.
Add bacon and put in bowl.
Mix 1 cup Miracle Whip, Parmesan cheese, sugar and milk. Pour over salad and mix.

title: chuck wagon beans
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Drain.
Cook hamburger until brown, adding onions and celery just before meat is brown.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in 2/3 cup boiling water and stir in meat mixture. Add garlic, ketchup, mustad, Mrs. Dash, pepper, beans and bacon. Cook for about 1 hour.
(Slow cooker works great!)

title: lemon jello mold
directions: Mix jello with boiling water.
Add the Marshmallow Creme. Chill until thickened, approximately 1 to 2 hours.
Fold in the whipped cream and pour into a mold.
Chill for several hours. Enjoy!

title: vanilla supreme ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add sugar gradually.
Beat until thickened.
Add creams, vanilla and salt.
Mix thoroughly.
Chill before processing in ice cream freezer.
Omit vanilla if another flavoring or fruit is used.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Layer the items in a baking dish as listed.
Cut margarine in patties and layer over entire dish.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix well. Roll into balls and bake on cookie sheets in a 350° oven about 1/2 hour or fry in frying pan on top of the stove. Can quick-freeze and store in freezer bags to use later.

title: grannie's gingerbread
directions: In large bowl of electric mixer, combine butter, sugar, molasses, salt and all the spices.
Blend well (use medium speed). Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Add to sugar mixture.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add flour, beat until well blended.

title: cowboy stew
directions: Fry bacon in a large kettle until crisp.
Remove and leave grease in pan. Add onion and green pepper.
Cook until translucent. Add ground beef. Cook until meat turns gray.
Add seasonings and potatoes, then add canned vegetables, undrained. Cook until potatoes are soft. Add water as needed. Crumble crisp bacon on top before serving.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Cream oleo and cheese.
Add flour, cayenne pepper and cereal. Make small balls and flatten with fork in crisscross pattern. Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet at 400° for about 12 minutes. Let cool and remove.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Mix cake as directed and bake in 2 layers.
To assemble in punch bowl.
Place one layer in bottom of bowl.
Prepare instant pudding.
Use half of first layer.
Slice bananas over top of pudding.
Pour 1/2 can pineapple (juice and all) over whipped topping.
Begin with other cake layer and repeat layering, ending with whipped topping.
Sprinkle pecans on top and refrigerate

title: aunt ellen's scalloped scallops
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease baking dish.
Combine cream and sherry.
Put layer of crumbs in bottom of dish.
Add a layer of scallops.
Pour half of the cream mixture on top.
Repeat layers and end with another layer of crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Season with salt and paprika.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: hungarian chocolate frosting
directions: Melt chocolate; add hot water.
Blend.
Add eggs and sugar; remove from heat and stir until slightly thickened.
Add butter. Store in refrigerator until needed. Very good.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Blend all ingredients well.
Cook on low in slow cooker. Serve with corn chips.

title: corn bread tamale pie
directions: Preheat the oven to 425°.
Saute together the ground beef and onion.
When the meat is lightly browned, add the soup, water, pepper, 1 teaspoon salt, chili powder, corn and green pepper. Simmer all together for 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, mix together the corn meal, flour, sugar, 1/2 teaspoon salt and baking powder. Moisten with egg and milk.
Mix lightly and fold in the cooking oil.
Place meat mixture in a greased 2-quart casserole and cover with the corn bread topping.
(When I'm in a hurry, I omit the last 3 steps and just use a Jiffy boxed corn bread mix.)
Place in oven and bake for about 20 to 25 minutes or until corn bread is brown.

title: curried seafood salad
directions: Combine tuna and shrimp, chill.
Mix mayonnaise, lemon juice, curry powder, celery and olives.
Pour this over tuna and shrimp, toss and chill.
Mix oil, lemon juice, garlic, salt and parsley; pour over rice, toss and chill.

title: butterscotch candy
directions: Melt butterscotch chips and peanut butter on low heat in saucepan.
Stir constantly.
Pour onto 9 x 13-inch cookie sheet. Melt Hershey's chocolate and put on top, zigzagging across until covered with chocolate.
Cool. Cut in squares and eat.

title: cheese ball
directions: Grate the 2 cheeses.
Cut green onions in very thin slices. Mix all ingredients.
Wet hands and mold into ball shape.

title: whiskey cake
directions: Beat eggs well, add cake mix, oil, milk and orange flavoring. Beat 1 minute, add pudding mix and nuts.
Pour over cherries, which are cut up and in bottom of greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
In pan, melt 1 stick oleo, take off heat and add 1/3 cup whiskey and sugar.
Pour half over cake in pan.
Let set 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and pour remaining mixture over cake.

title: sausage cannonballs
directions: Put baking mix, sausage and grated cheese in a large mixing bowl.
Mix well.
Use your hands to blend together.
Form into walnut-size balls and place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen balls.

title: ritzy green bean casserole
directions: Mix green beans and corn in a 2-quart casserole. Mix soup, sour cream, onion and cheese together; spread on top of vegetables. Mix margarine with crackers and crumble on top. Sprinkle with almonds. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: play dough
directions: Sift dry ingredients in a heavy aluminum pan.
Mix liquids and add to dry ingredients.
Blend well.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring constantly, until dough pulls away from pan or until it can be squeezed without feeling sticky.
Turn out on board and knead.
Add a few drops of mint and any coloring you want.
Put in plastic bags and store for loads of fun.
Old-time recipe.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: In a small bowl, with mixer at medium speed, beat softened cream cheese, vanilla and salt until smooth.
Gradually beat in confectioners sugar and milk until thick spreading consistency.

title: piccadilla
directions: Brown the ground beef in a skillet.
Add the onions, green pepper, garlic, tomato paste, tomatoes, salt and pepper and cover. Simmer for at least 1 hour, adding water if necessary.
Serve over rice.
You can also serve fried plantains, green bananas, as an accompaniment.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Break lettuce and place in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add celery, cauliflower, broccoli and green onions.
Sprinkle green peas over top.
Mix Miracle Whip and sugar thoroughly.
Spread over top and seal edges with salad dressing.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top, then sprinkle on bacon, broken into small bits.

title: old time vinegar pie
directions: Crumble butter into flour; add sugar and nutmeg.
Add vinegar and water; stir.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then at 350° until bubbles form on top.

title: rancho grande
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add tomato sauce, instant rice and chili beans.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes.
Pour mixture into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Place sliced tamales on top.
Top with cheese and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: sauce for 4 boneless chicken breasts
directions: Mix ingredients together; brush half of sauce on one side of chicken breasts; broil or cook on grill 8 to 10 minutes.
Turn and brush sauce on other side; cook until tender.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Mix together milk and pudding mix; add ice cream.
Pour into crust and top with Cool Whip.
Use 9 x 13-inch pan.
Freeze.

title: hot rolls
directions: Heat milk, butter and sugar until warm to the finger.
Then mix the flour and yeast together.
Pour milk and keep adding flour until biscuit is thick.
Take out and knead until elastic.
Then put back in buttered bowl and place in refrigerator.
Take out 30 minutes before baking.
Melt butter in pan.
Roll out dough like biscuits.
Dip in melted butter.
Bake at 350° until brown.
(Can keep dough in refrigerator up to a week.)

title: scalloped potatoes in cream sauce
directions: Layer potatoes, salt, pepper, onion and cheese.
Sprinkle flour over each layer.
Pour milk over all.
Bake at 350° until potatoes are done, but not mushy.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients together well and pour over chicken. Marinate 2 to 3 days in a covered dish.

title: lace cookies
directions: In a bowl, put flour and nuts.
In saucepan, melt butter; add sugar and Karo.
Combine the two mixtures and add vanilla.
Bake at 350° on foil until done (approximately 8 to 10 minutes).
Take foil out; let cool approximately 2 to 3 minutes on cake rack, then peel from foil and let cool on paper towels on another cookie rack.
Enjoy!

title: delectabites
directions: Mix butter, sugar and vanilla.
Gradually stir in flour and nuts.
Shape into crescents.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets. Bake at 350° in upper third of oven for 10 minutes or until firm, but not brown.
Gently roll each cookie in powdered sugar.
Cool on wire racks.
Drizzle with melted chocolate.
Let stand on waxed paper until chocolate is firm.

title: pasta fruit salad
directions: Cook and drain pasta according to package directions.
Drain pineapple, saving juice.
Drain oranges.
Refrigerate fruit. Combine pineapple juice, sugar, flour and eggs in saucepan.
Cook until mixture thickens.
Pour mixture over cooked pasta; cover and refrigerate overnight.
Add fruit and Cool Whip.
Stir until well mixed.

title: tallarine
directions: Brown meat, onion, bell pepper, chili powder and garlic salt. In	large
baking
pan, layer ingredients starting with noodles, then meat (1/2 of whole amount), about 1/2 of grated cheese,
then go
to
tomatoes
with
green chilies and corn, putting
of contents
at
a
time.
Repeat layers except cheese
and save balance of cheese to put on top.
Put foil on top
to
keep cheese from burning.
Place in oven for approximately 1 hour at 325°.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Chop chicken, celery and eggs.
Mix all ingredients, except cheese and potato chips.
Put in casserole dish.
Mix cheese and crushed potato chips.
Sprinkle over top and bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Set aside about 3/4 cup.

title: king ranch chicken (enchilada pie)
directions: Boil hen until tender; debone and cut into small pieces.
Mix with onions, bell pepper and pimentos.
Wilt tortillas in chicken broth (reserved from boiling hen).
Place in 9 x 13-inch greased Pyrex dish.
Alternate with the chicken mixture.
Mix the soup with taco sauce.
Season with pepper and chili powder.
Pour over chicken and tortillas.
Sauce may be thinned with chicken broth, if desired.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix well and bake in greased and floured loaf pan for about 1 hour at 350.
If you use small pans, it makes eight loaves.

title: chili
directions: Mix all ingredients except hamburger in large saucepan.
Cook over medium-low heat.
Brown hamburger; drain off grease and add hamburger to other mixture.
Cook over medium-low heat for approximately 30minutes.

title: sour cream dip for fresh fruit
directions: Mix cinnamon, nutmeg, allspice and salt with sugar.
Stir into sour cream.
Add extracts and mix well. Chill 2 hours to allow flavors to blend.
Serve with fresh fruit (strawberries, Bing cherries, green grapes, apples and bananas).
Makes 1 cup.

title: perfection salad
directions: Add
boiling water, cold water, vinegar and lemon juice to gelatin, sugar and salt.
Chill until partially set and add cabbage, celery, green pepper, pimento and green olives.
Pour into loaf pan until
set.
Invert
on
platter.
Garnish
with carrot curls, ripe olives and mayonnaise.

title: crock-pot brunswick stew
directions: Combine ingredients in crock-pot and cook on high for 3 1/2 to 4 hours.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Put sugar, oleo, cocoa and milk on stove and cook about 3 minutes.
Stir all the time.
Add the rest of the ingredients. Drop on wax paper by teaspoon.

title: buttermilk scones
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In large bowl, stir together the flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Cut butter into 1/2-inch cubes and distribute them over flour mixture.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles crumbs.
In a small bowl, stir together the buttermilk, egg and vanilla.
Add buttermilk mixture to flour mixture; stir to combine.
Stir in dried fruit (if desired).

title: almost candy bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, cut butter into cake mix with fork or pastry
blender until crumbly.
Sprinkle evenly over bottom of 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan; press lightly.
Sprinkle with butterscotch chips, chocolate chips, coconut and nuts.
Pour sweetened condensed milk over all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until light golden brown.
Cool completely. Cut into bars.

title: oyster cracker treats
directions: Mix together oyster crackers and vegetable oil. Sprinkle on Ranch dressing, lemon pepper and garlic salt to taste. Toss until coated. Give time to absorb, then enjoy.

title: whipped potato casserole
directions: Peel and cook potatoes until tender.
Drain and mash well. Beat cream cheese and sour cream together, add to potatoes, blending well.
Add more sour cream and a little milk if potatoes are too stiff.
Spoon into a 2-quart casserole and season and brush top with melted butter and sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and put it in refrigerator, covered, until ready to use.
Bake 40 minutes at 300°, uncovered.
Serves 12 generously.

title: million dollar pineapple pie
directions: Mix milk, lemon juice and pineapple.
Fold in Cool Whip and pecans.
Pour into 2 graham cracker crumb crusts and chill for at least 1 hour before serving.

title: do nothing cake
directions: Mix all ingredients with undrained pineapple.
Do not use mixer.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: deviled crab
directions: In a heavy skillet, saute onion, green pepper and celery in 1 1/2 tablespoons of the butter until softened.
Stir in crab, mayonnaise, green onions, 2 tablespoons of the bread crumbs, Worcestershire sauce, minced parsley, roasted red pepper, cayenne and salt to taste.
Divide mixture between 2 large or 4 small scallop shells or ramekins.
Sprinkle remaining bread crumbs over; drizzle with remaining butter,
melted.
Bake mixture on rack of broiler pan in upper third
of preheated 400° oven for 10 minutes. Garnish and serve.
Serves 4.

title: dirty rice casserole
directions: Chop vegetables and cook with ground beef.
In a separate skillet, cook sausage and save the drippings.
In meantime, cook rice.
Drain ground beef and add sausage and sausage drippings to beef and vegetables.
Add cooked rice.
Fry all in a skillet for 15 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Soften the cream cheese and mix with powdered sugar.
Stir in Cool Whip; pour into crust.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Top with cherry pie filling before serving.

title: slumgullion
directions: This was a woodsman's and covered wagon dish, cooked in one pot.
This was cooked until all was tender and served in cups or bowls.

title: pea salad
directions: Drain peas.
In a bowl, combine peas, eggs, onion, sweet relish and mayonnaise.
Keep refrigerated.

title: easy white bread
directions: Scald milk; add honey, salt and butter (set aside).
Combine yeast and water while milk is cooling to lukewarm, then add together.
Add enough flour to make a thick batter (like pancake). Cover and let rise about 1 hour, until double.
Beat down with a wooden spoon and let rise again.
Add enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Knead 8 to 10 minutes.
Put dough in lightly greased bowl and let rise until double.
Knead 2 to 3 minutes.
Split dough and put into loaf pans.
Let rise.
Bake at 375° for
45 minutes. Lower temperature to 350° and bake until tops are golden brown and bottoms sound hollow when tapped.

title: ranch-style baked beans
directions: Brown beef.
Add all ingredients and bake 1 hour at 350°, covered.

title: rhubarb salad
directions: Cook rhubarb (no water).
Add sugar and strawberry gelatin. Stir until dissolved.
Add lemon juice and cold water.
Let set until slightly thickened.
Add diced celery, crushed pineapple and nuts.

title: connie's raspberry jam strips
directions: Mix butter, sugars, egg and vanilla.
Stir in flour and baking powder.
(If dough is soft, cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour.)
Heat oven to 350°.

title: monterey chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts between two sheets of waxed paper and pound until thin.
Lightly sprinkle with salt, pepper and flour. Melt 1/4 cup butter in a skillet and quickly saute breasts until golden.
Remove and set aside.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt remaining butter in same skillet and saute onion, garlic and mushrooms slowly until vegetables are cooked, but not brown.
Stir in flour, celery powder, chicken stock and wine.
Cook over low heat, about 4 to 5 minutes.
Stir in 1/2 of cheese, blending well. Arrange breasts and spoon mixture on top.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Wet hands with cooking oil to form into a ball.
Roll in chopped pecans.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt butter, peanut butter and chocolate chips.
Fold in cereal until coated.
Pour sugar in plastic Ziploc bag.
Place cereal mixture in bag and shake.

title: new mexico frittata
directions: In bowl, combine tomato, zucchini, cucumber and taco sauce. In skillet, melt butter.
Add onion.
Cook over medium heat until onion is wilted, 2 to 3 minutes.
Add spinach and basil.
Turn heat up to high.
Beat eggs with water.
Add to skillet and immediately begin lifting egg from bottom of skillet, allowing uncooked egg to run under.
Cook until set.
Turn off heat. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover; let stand 5 minutes until cheese is melted.
Cut into wedges.
Spoon tomato mixture over and serve.

title: baked dilled salmon a la maytag
directions: Tired of cooking the same old way?
Polly Wilson shared this recipe with me for salmon steak.
(The recipe was given to her by a Danish woman over a Montreal fish counter!)
Put a salmon steak on slightly greased aluminum foil and sprinkle with dill weed. Drop a few drops of water on top to steam.
Seal foil tightly, making a "tent."
Put on top rack of dishwasher and run through 2 dryer cycles and it will be perfectly baked!

title: mexican casserole
directions: Cook onion, pepper and ground turkey until brown.
Add rice, picante sauce and enchilada sauce mix.
Stir well.
Pour in a pan that's 8 x 8-inch.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.
Add Cheddar cheese and bake 5 more minutes.
(Can use ground chuck.)

title: chicken tortilla soup
directions: Mix all ingredients together and simmer.
Serve with grated cheese and tortilla chips.
Can be done in crock-pot also.
Canned mixed vegetables can be added.

title: ham, cheese and broccoli bake
directions: Spread potatoes in deep Pyrex pie plate (10-inch).
Season. Almost cover with cream.
Bake for 2 hours at 250°.

title: date nut bread
directions: Mix dates, water, butter, sugar and
salt
together
and let cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at	375°
for about 45 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves of bread.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash broccoli; cut in small pieces.
Cook bacon and crumble. Mix together broccoli, bacon, raisins and onion.
Mix together mayo, sugar and cider vinegar.
Pour mayo, sugar, vinegar dressing over broccoli mixture.
Stir well.
Cover until serving.
Tastes best if refrigerated for at least 8 hours.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Drain corn and mix the corn and chili in a bowl, mix well with spoon and pour into dish.
Put chips in a plastic bag and crush, then spread the chips evenly over the chili and corn mixture.
Grate cheese and spread over chips.
Bake in oven for 30 minutes.

title: lentil loaf
directions: Steam onion with the savory and marjoram.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake in a loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour. Cool a few minutes and turn out of pan onto serving platter. Garnish and serve.

title: cranberry-grape spritzer(punch)
directions: In punch bowl, gently stir together cranberry juice cocktail concentrate and club soda; add sparkling grape juice. Garnish with orange slices. Serve immediately in ice-filled glasses. Makes about 15 (3/4 cup) servings.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Cook broccoli until tender and drain.
Mix all ingredients together and bake at 400 degrees for 20 - 30 minutes.

title: cake layers
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes four layers.
Use any type of frosting.

title: crock-pot brunswick stew
directions: Mix all ingredients in crock-pot and cook until potatoes are tender.

title: sweet potato sonker
directions: Peel and slice sweet potatoes.
Cover with water.
Cook until tender.
Line pan with biscuit dough.
Put potatoes and water potatoes were cooked in to lined pan.
Add sugar, butter, ginger, vanilla and milk.
Cover with top crust, sealing edges.
Sprinkle a little sugar over top crust.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: Slightly beat eggs.
Add to other ingredients and mix well. Pour into a 9x13-inch baking dish and bake at 400° for 30-40 minutes.

title: butterscotch dessert
directions: First you have to catch one!!
Many a good husband is spoiled in the cooking.
Some women keep them constantly in hot water, while others freeze them with conjugal coolness.
Some smother them with contention, others keep them in a pickle all their lives and serve them with hot tongue sauce.
Husbands so treated will rarely be tender and good.

title: chinese cranberry dip
directions: In a small bowl, thoroughly blend mustard and vinegar. Add water and blend until smooth. Set aside 10 minutes.
In a small saucepan, over medium-low heat, stir cranberry sauce until melted. Remove from heat. Stir in mustard mixture and lemon juice.
Serve at room temperature with mini egg rolls.

title: maple sugar divinity
directions: Combine first five ingredients in 2-quart heavy saucepan. Cook, stirring, until sugar is dissolved.
If sugar crystals form on side of pan, wipe them off.
Continue cooking, without stirring, to hard ball stage (265°).
Spread on greased cookie sheet.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix together with electric mixer the pudding mix, milk, Eagle Brand milk and 3/4 of the Cool Whip.
Layer wafers, bananas and pudding mixture.
Top with remainder of Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package.
Drain.
Meanwhile, melt butter over low heat.
Blend in flour and salt.
Gradually add milk and 1 cup of the cheese.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until sauce is thickened and cheese melted.
Add cooked macaroni; mix well.
Turn into buttered 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle remaining cheese over top.
Bake in 375° oven for about 20 minutes. Serves 6.

title: cherry chocolate cake
directions: Combine ingredients and mix until well blended.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, or until cake springs back when lightly touched.
Cool. Serve with chocolate topping.

title: stir-fry
directions: Melt butter in a large frypan on medium heat.
Add meat and brown until well cooked.
Add vegetables; stir all together.
Add water and teriyaki sauce, stirring repeatedly.
Cover for 15 minutes.
Fork your vegetables to see if they're done.
Serves 4 to 6, depending on the quantity of meat and vegetables you add.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and foamy.
Add oil and sugar and mix well by hand.
Add zucchini and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to batter.
Stir in nuts.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Spread hamburger in bake dish.
Slice potatoes over meat. Thinly slice onion over potatoes.
Mix other ingredients; pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: fried deer steak
directions: Cut meat into small pieces, no larger than 3-inches in diameter.
Using sharp knife, cut across each piece approximately 1/16-inch from left to right, then from top to bottom.
Repeat on other side of piece.
Avoid cutting through meat.
This process tenderizes the meat.
Meat will look like a waffle.
Sprinkle garlic salt liberally on meat.
Roll meat in flour and lay in skillet with warm grease.
Increase heat gradually but do not fry too fast.
Remove meat when thoroughly browned on both sides. Drain on paper.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 3 tablespoons warm water and set aside. In large bowl, mix eggs, sugar, Crisco, salt and water. Mix well. Add yeast mixture, stirring slightly. Add flour. Cover bowl and place in refrigerator overnight or a few hours. Roll out and brush with melted butter. Do not knead them. Cut out rolls, fold over and brush again with melted butter. Let rise about 2 hours in a warm place. Bake at 450° until golden.

title: rice krispie treats
directions: Melt margarine and marshmallows over low heat in a large saucepan.
Reduce heat as low as possible and add Rice Krispies. Press mixture into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch buttered pan.
Cover and let cool.
Around holidays, sprinkle with colored candy or sugar while still warm.
Makes approximately 24 squares when cut.

title: spring dinner
directions: Brown onion, garlic, fat and ground beef.
Cook until brown. Add rice and water.
Simmer, uncovered, 40 minutes.
Then add potatoes and carrots.
Continue simmering, covered, 20 minutes, until tender.
Season with soy sauce, salt and pepper.
Serve hot, garnished with parsley.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Melt butter and mix with pretzels.
Press in 9 x 13-inch pan. Cook for 10 minutes at 400°.
Cream together cream cheese and sugar.
Spread over cooled pretzels.
Spread 1/2 of Cool Whip on top.
Dissolve jello with hot water and add thawed strawberries. Let jell in separate bowl.
After jelled, pour over pretzels.
Top that with Cool Whip.
Keep refrigerated; so good!

title: rickshaw rice
directions: Brown luncheon meat in butter or margarine.
Drain pineapple, reserving 3/4 cup syrup.
Add pineapple, reserved syrup, rice, peas and dill weed in skillet.
Cover the skillet; reduce heat and simmer for 4 to 5 minutes or until peas are tender.
Stir in tomatoes.
Top with sour cream.
Cover and simmer the rice mixture for 2 minutes.

title: frozen passion
directions: Combine ingredients in ice cream freezer can.
Proceed according to freezer instructions.
For refrigerator freezer:
In large bowl, combine ingredients.
Pour into 2 (13 x 9-inch) pans. Freeze to a firm mush (about 1 hour).
Turn into chilled large mixer bowl and break into pieces.
Beat until fluffy, but not melted.
Quickly return to pan.
Cover with aluminum foil and freeze until firm.
Makes about 3 1/2 quarts.

title: party punch
directions: Add sugar to taste.
Mix together and stir well.

title: hush puppies
directions: Put egg, onion and milk in blender.
Put rest of ingredients in bowl.
Mix the blender mixture with mixture in bowl.
Drop by spoon into hot grease.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl. Best if chilled before serving.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Scald evaporated milk with water.
Beat eggs slightly in large bowl.
Stir in pumpkin, sugar, spice and salt.
Beat in scalded milk mixture.
Pour in pastry shell.
Bake 50 minutes at 350° or until center is set, but still soft.
Top with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: chopped beef stroganoff
directions: Cook ground beef and onion in skillet over medium-high heat until onion is tender.
Stir in soup mix, flour and water.
Bring to a boil over high heat.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer on low for 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream; heat through.
Do not boil; serve over hot noodles.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes until almost tender.
Drain.
Add 1 stick of butter, salt, pepper, soup, sour cream, onion and cheese.
Blend together and pour into greased 5-quart casserole dish.
Top with cornflakes mixed with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lite shrimp and pasta
directions: Combine soy sauce and 1 cup water in small saucepan; bring to boil.
Add shrimp and cook 2 minutes or just until shrimp turns pink.
Reserving liquid, remove shrimp and keep warm.
Heat butter in large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add green onions and garlic; saute 2 minutes.
Meanwhile, combine cornstarch and lemon juice; stir into skillet with reserved shrimp liquid and basil. Bring to boil and simmer 1 minute.
Add sauce, shrimp, parsley and pepper to hot pasta; toss to combine.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: watermelon rind pickles
directions: Peel the rind and cut in cubes, combine cold water and lime. Let stand for 1 hour with rind in it.
Then wash two times, cover with fresh water and simmer for 1 1/2 hours until rind is tender; then drain water off.
Combine vinegar and sugar; heat until sugar dissolves.
When sugar has dissolved, add spices and rind; simmer 2 hours.
Pack rind in hot sterile jars and fill with the vinegar and syrup.
Seal jars.
Eat with any kind of meat or veggies.

title: best sweet potato pie
directions: Peel potatoes.
Cook until tender.
Drain well.
Put all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Beat well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 minutes.

title: lazy frenchman's dirty rice
directions: Stir all together.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour at 400°.

title: chicken nuggets
directions: Put it in the stove and cook it about 10 minutes.
Then eat it with ketchup.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating well. Add egg yolks, beating well. Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture. Mix well after each addition.

Stir in vanilla. Beat egg whites (at room temperature) until stiff peaks form; fold into batter. Pour batter into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pans 10 minutes; remove layers from pans and let cool completely. Frost with Minute Fudge Frosting.

title: perch italian style
directions: Wipe
fillets
with paper towel.
Cut fish into serving pieces.
Cook
parsley
and
garlic
in hot oil in skillet for 3 minutes.
Add
hot water and bring to a boil.
Add fish and seasoning.	Cover and bring again to boil and cook for 5 to 10 minutes or until fish flakes easily.
Serve with liquid.
Very good over rice.

title: penny's hawaiian cake
directions: Place all ingredients together, mix well.
Pour into buttered baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until golden brown.

title: dill-garlic mayonnaise
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients, cover and refrigerate.
Garnish, if desired, with fresh dill weed.
Yields 1/2 cup.

title: cheesecake for diabetics
directions: Blend all ingredients together; save skim milk until last. Beat at medium speed for 3 minutes or more until smooth.
Add enough skim milk to aid in smooth blending.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
Serve chilled.

title: strawberry preserves
directions: Wash, cap and slice strawberries.
Add 1 1/2 cups of sugar to the berries and boil 5 minutes.
Add remaining sugar and boil 10 to 15 minutes longer (a watery fruit must cook longer).
Turn mixture into an earthenware jar and let stand 24 hours; stir occasionally.
Seal cold in sterilized jars.
The small quantity of fruit and the short cooking period are the secret of the preserves.
You may do as many quarts as the jar will hold, but cook only 1 quart at a time.
Berries may be frozen, unsweetened, in quart bags and used as needed to make preserves.

title: no bake rice pudding(makes enough for 8 to 10 people)
directions: Put rice in a large pot; put enough water in just to cover rice.
Boil for a few seconds.
Add the sugar and canned
milk, mixed with 1 can water.
Add about 1 1/2 quarts milk; cook slowly until thickened, about 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add more milk if needed. Add the vanilla and raisins when done.
Put cinnamon and nutmeg on top, if desired.

title: col. sanders' style kentucky fried chicken
directions: Wipe chicken dry.
Make paste of first 5 ingredients; brush to coat chicken evenly.
Stack pieces in bowl.
Cover and refrigerate several hours.
One and one-half hours before serving, heat 1/2-inch oil in 2 large skillets so chicken won't be crowded.
Dip pieces in milk, then in pancake mix, mixed with paprika, sage and pepper; coat well.
Dust off excess.
Lightly brown about 4 minutes each side.
Place in 1 layer in shallow pans.
Spoon remaining milk over pieces.
Seal with foil.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. Uncover; bake 10 minutes at 400° to crisp chicken.
Baste with milk again.
Serves 8.

title: easy fried rice
directions: In a skillet coated with nonstick cooking spray, saute green pepper and garlic until pepper is crisp-tender. Add egg substitute; cook and stir until egg is completely set. Chop egg into small pieces. Add rice and soy sauce; heat through.

title: quick noodles
directions: Bring water and 1/2 tablespoon butter to a hard boil.
Boil noodles until barely done (5 to 6 minutes).
Drain all but 2 tablespoons water off noodles.
Add other 1/2 tablespoon butter, chicken flavored base, parsley flakes and black pepper and stir until blended.
On a very low burner, simmer with lid on for about 30 seconds.
